 (3808, 2, '2013-11-21 22:36:37', '2013-11-21 22:36:37', '<p dir="ltr">Dear EESTECers,</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Short story: Excited about NEW things? We can do better than that. This Autumn, <b>LC Bucharest</b> gives you<b> RENEWABLE energies</b>!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Long story: Energy Always a Challenge is an event with a lot of history in our LC, because it’s the first international workshop we have ever organized. This autumn, between the 24th of November and 1st December, we’re having the 4th edition of this event, focusing on renewable energies.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The workshop consists of two parts:<b> three days of conferences </b>on different topics regarding our planet’s green resources and their exploitation potential and a ‘hands on’ week, in which the participants will work in teams to integrate a renewable power plant into the national energy system using the <b>SCADA software</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you are passionate about this subject, if you want to take part in an interactive experience combining fields like: energy management, electrical engineering, IT and programming - you’re the right person for this workshop!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Prior SCADA knowledge is welcome, but not necessary.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The myth: All work and no play make EESTECers dull boys and girls.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The truth: Is that we totally agree with the myth. Therefore, while we will be working hard on our projects, we’ll party with the same amount of enthusiasm! We have prepared for you a week of hardcore entertainment, starting with the <b>City Rally</b> (a thrilling race in which you’ll discover the history and landmarks of our city, such as the largest administrative building in the world, the Palace of the Parliament) and ending with the <b>motivational weekend</b>, where you’ll get a breath of fresh air <b>outside Bucharest</b> -  not to mention the <b>daily parties and outings</b>, the incredible food and the <b>brain-melting traditional drinks</b> (ţuică, palincă).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Bucharest is well known for its <b>flourishing nightlife</b> and <b>fun people </b>(translation: hot girls and boys), so we can guarantee you that you’ll never spend a dull moment during this workshop.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We are waiting for your applications <span style="color: #000000;">u</span><span style="color: #000000;">ntil</span> the<b> 22nd of October 2013</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We’ll work hard to make sure that it’s going to be an unforgettable experience for you :D</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Long story short: APPLY!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Hope to see you soon in Bucharest!</p>', 'Energy Always a Challenge 4', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3163-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:36:37', '2013-11-21 22:36:37', '', 3163, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3808', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3809, 2, '2013-11-21 22:36:56', '2013-11-21 22:36:56', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The wait is finally over!</div>\r\n<div>LC Ljubljana is happy to announce its dual workshop "<strong>Facebook</strong> <strong>CPR</strong>"!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That\'s right.</div>\r\n<div>This year we\'re offering you not one, but TWO ways to improve your skills in EESTEC!</div>\r\n<div>Coding or Public Relations.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Have you ever organized an event? Do you know how to use modern media to communicate with the public? Are you interested in what the public has to say and want to maintain a healthy dialogue? If you are interested in the above activities, you might have what it takes to become a Public Relations specialist. At our workshop you can choose to become a master of PR and learn how to inform, communicate with, captivate and even amaze the public. Such skills are extremely valuable in every EESTEC LC, not to mention they will make you look awesome and super attractive to future employers.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>What is the topic?</div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to acquaint the attendees with all the tools needed to maintain proper public relations. We will focus mostly on social network usage because this has become a staple of PR communication. The workshop will include cooperation with successful companies which will help you improve on all areas of PR. You will also work on other aspects, such as public speaking, working with an international team, general communication and leadership skills. The end result will of course be powerful and useful new knowledge that is also directly applicable to any future EESTEC projects.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>But that\'s not all! We at LC Ljubljana know that a student\'s mind can\'t work properly without some kind of release. A head full of knowledge can collapse under its own weight. So we took care of that too! We have prepared a number of fun social activities that take care of your mind and soul. On top of that you will be able to explore the beautiful streets of Ljubljana, enjoy its charming and vibrant nightlife and even attend the legendary City Rally!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That has to be it, right?</div>\r\n<div>WRONG!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After the workshop, you\'ll also get to attend the International Motivational Weekend. It is a huge EESTEC event with people all across Europe. It includes soft-skill training, socializing with EESTECers from numerous LCs, crazy themed parties and best of all: it\'s free for all workshop attendees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 19th (arrival day) to the 27th (departure day) of October 2013 and become part of another unforgettable EESTEC experience here in Ljubljana, Slovenia.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We\'re hearing some rumours (hint: 404) that <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> still doesn\'t function as it\'s supposed to, so we\'ve put up a <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1m1sO7hb5M0pw32stqKFi64ZSNmxSQNVTueiGew1TyTU/viewform" target="_blank">form where you can apply</a>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>See you all in Ljubljana!</div>\r\n</div>', 'Facebook CPR: PR Tools', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3142-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:36:56', '2013-11-21 22:36:56', '', 3142, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3809', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3810, 2, '2013-11-21 22:37:48', '2013-11-21 22:37:48', '<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Would you like to end this summer with the best exchange of EESTEC history?</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We know that many of you are thinking ‘Of course I would love to come to Ankara, the capital city which is in the heart of the Anatolia but how about somewhere by the sea to get refreshed?’. Well, you don’t have to worry much longer because LC Ankara is asking you to occupy<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marmaris" target="_blank"> Marmaris</a>!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">LC Ankara is taking you to Marmaris, situated in the southwest coast of Turkish Riviera. Marmaris is one of the most beautiful cities of Turkey and also one of the biggest touristic centrals. The harbor and the marina, the beautiful old town and the <a href="http://www.kulturvarliklari.gov.tr/Resim/32522,muze01jpg.png?0" target="_blank">historical castle</a> are just a few of the greatest things that make it irresistible. Besides that, there is the crazy night life of Marmaris with non-ending foam parties, discos at the beaches and the bar street with lots of clubs. In addition, we will take you to a Turkish night where you will have the chance to taste <a href="http://galeri.uludagsozluk.com/8/rak%C4%B1_20990.jpg" target="_blank">Turkish Raki, </a>eat<a href="http://www.nationalturk.com/en/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/turkish-kebab-nationalturk.jpg" target="_blank"> Kebab</a> and maybe even see <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hCP0yeuo4QQ" target="_blank">belly dancers.</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Of course you won’t spend all your time in the city center. One day we will go to a <a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?hl=en&amp;authuser=0&amp;site=imghp&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=hp&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=664&amp;q=tekne+turu&amp;oq=tekne+turu&amp;gs_l=img.3..0j0i5l2j0i24.2042.3163.0.3709.10.8.0.0.0.0.244.1102.2j5j1.8.0....0...1ac.1.19.img.5mkbu_RvkMQ#hl=en&amp;authuser=0&amp;site=imghp&amp;tbm=isch&amp;sa=1&amp;q=marmaris+boat+trips&amp;oq=marmaris+boat+trips&amp;gs_l=img.3..0j0i5j0i24l4.20890.27785.10.27934.20.14.6.0.0.1.254.2020.1j12j1.14.0....0...1c.1.19.img.t54EAmJgxCY&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;fp=59f2cb1f24a4b371&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=664" target="_blank">boat trip </a>where we will swim in 5 different bays, see the<a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?gs_rn=17&amp;gs_ri=psy-ab&amp;tok=vdBjoKuU2GvzBcTk45oNWQ&amp;pq=fosforlu+ma%C4%9Fara&amp;cp=17&amp;gs_id=1e&amp;xhr=t&amp;q=fosforlu+ma%C4%9Fara+marmaris&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;ion=1&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=1mncUcznIMrYtAbgj4CACA" target="_blank"> phosphoric cave</a> , walk through 2 villages and will barbeque on the boat. In the meantime you can try some <a href="http://tripsinmarmaris.com/turlar/water-Sports/1.jpg" target="_blank">water sport</a>s too. This trip is called ‘Lazy Trip’ because we will have many time to swim, to sunbathe, to drink and to dance. Another day we will go to <a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?q=marmaris+jeep+safari&amp;ion=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=h3LcUZDSHsnWOaPhgYgN" target="_blank">safari trip</a> where we will be taken from our hotel with jeeps and climb up to the mountains. Afterwards we will dive into cold waterfall ponds,<a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?q=k%C4%B1z+kumu&amp;ion=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=iGncUbCIL4OetAbpk4G4BQ" target="_blank"> walk through the sea</a>, have lunch at traditional villages and many more.  At the last day of the exchange we will go to the<a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;q=marmaris+milli+park%C4%B1&amp;ion=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=KmrcUde1GoLWtAadkoFA#um=1&amp;hl=tr&amp;authuser=0&amp;tbm=isch&amp;sa=1&amp;q=marmaris+milli+park%C4%B1+g%C3%BCnn%C3%BCcek&amp;oq=marmaris+milli+park%C4%B1+g%C3%BCnn%C3%BCcek&amp;gs_l=img.3...1220.3312.2.3530.4.4.0.0.0.0.151.457.1j3.4.0...0.0.0..1c.1.17.img.4t5Q9CZboLI&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;fp=f73320e873d882bf&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643" target="_blank"> Marmaris Natural Park</a> and there will be many surprises waiting for you.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">With all these attractions we will also have an educational part with 3 interesting trainings from EESTEC’s and ESTIEM’s trainers. As well as Motivation and Body Language, we will give you a training on Turkish Language which will help you in many ways ;)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Don’t forget to take a look at this video as well : <a href="http://vimeo.com/56977743" target="_blank">http://vimeo.com/56977743</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Last but not least, don’t worry you will be selected or not, we are preparing a great unofficial package for you guys as well!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">So prepare your swimsuits and bags to have the greatest time of your life!</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Mail: <a href="mailto:ankara@eestec.net" target="_blank">ankara@eestec.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n<div>Application: via sending <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">this form</a> to <a href="mailto:ankara@eestec.net" target="_blank">ankara@eestec.net</a> until <a href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> is reachable again.</div>', '#occupyMarmaris', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3132-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:37:48', '2013-11-21 22:37:48', '', 3132, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3810', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3811, 2, '2013-11-21 22:37:57', '2013-11-21 22:37:57', 'Dear EESTEC-ers,\r\n\r\nWe are proud to invite you to our traditional event “JAZZ DO IT!”, because it’s 3<sup>rd</sup> edition! It was great previous times, so we have decided to do it again! That\'s why you are welcome to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and Eastern Europe "<a href="http://www.nisville.com/" target="_blank">Nišville jazz festival</a>". Together we will enjoy the good jazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchange can provide. Organized in the medieval <a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" target="_blank">fortress</a> and visited by more than <b>100.000 people</b> only last year, Nišville hosted some of the biggest stars of jazz music: Hans &amp; Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke, Benny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell, Rick Margitza and many others. World’s best jazz musicians and 50 other bands will jazz up on 5 different stages for us!\r\n\r\nParticipants will also have unique opportunity to participate at <a href="http://www.nisville.com/index.php/en/workshop" target="_blank">workshops</a> held by the best jazz musicians.\r\n\r\nRegular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you are getting it for <b>free</b> :)\r\n\r\nBut, that’s not all. The City of Niš has great cultural and historical heritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most important persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Niš (roman name <b>NAISSUS</b>) in 272AD. We are very proud of him, because he was the greatest among all Roman emperors and certainly the person who changed the course of human civilization. And this year is very special because we celebrate 1700 years of issuing the Edict of Milan, which proclaimed religious tolerance in the Empire and stopped numerous persecutions. He had also built a new imperial capital Constantinople, was first Christian emperor in Europe, his mother Saint Helena found True Cross. And by being a birth town of such important person, Niš is also called imperial city. You are going to visit his villa <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediana" target="_blank">Mediana</a> and many other sights that testify rich history of this place between East and West.\r\n\r\nYou will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni%C5%A1_Fortress" target="_blank">Fortress of Niš</a>, where “Nišville jazz festival” takes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. It’s in this condition since XVII century, and now it’s one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe. In Niš exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was built from skulls of the warriors who died in the Čegar battle. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_%C4%8Cegar" target="_blank">Čegar monument</a> where this famous battle took place. We’ll show you one very nice relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" target="_blank">Niška Banja</a> spa which has radioactive healing water and we’ll go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!\r\n\r\nAnd if you think that we only have history, you’re wrong, because Niš is known as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old hedonist legacy! You will enjoy the best Serbian food (world-known barbeque, special burek of Niš and many others), drinks (rakija, wine etc.) and of course a lot of good music. There won’t be a single moment that you’ll be hungry, because Serbs like good food in big quantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient at the special night in <b>kafana</b>. You will certainly learn what is traditional southern <b>merak</b>.\r\n\r\nThis event is completely financed with grant given by Serbian Oil Company <b>NIS</b>, the most profitable Serbian company, so you will be treated like emperors in imperial city!\r\n\r\nSo the crazy summer cocktail with... traditional Serbian drinks and food… plenty of great music… nice town… a lot of EESTEC spirit… Mix all that in a summer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.\r\n\r\nWhat are you waiting for?\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://img404.imageshack.us/img404/5156/jazzdoitcopy.jpg" target="_blank">JAZZ DO IT!</a></span>\r\n\r\n<b>Application </b>by sending this <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">form</a> to <a href="mailto:nis@eestec.net" target="_blank">nis@eestec.net</a>; later maybe via <a href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>', 'Jazz do it 2013!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3129-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:37:57', '2013-11-21 22:37:57', '', 3129, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3811', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3812, 2, '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '<div>\r\n\r\n“<i>When we define the Photograph as a motionless image, this does not mean only that the figures it represents do not move; it means that they do not emerge, do not leave: they are anesthetized and fastened down, like butterflies.</i>”\r\n\r\nRoland Barthes define the photograph with these sentences in Camera Lucida. I’m sure that most of you interested in “Photography” in some way, try to save some memories and feelings in frame, look to huge world from a little viewfinder.\r\n\r\nNow, LC Eskişehir organizing an amazing workshop about Photography for the second time. We’re proud to invite you to “Photosynthesis 2” We’re offering you an amazing week, lots of fun, useful trainings, great parties, delicious Turkish food and chance to recognize other cultures with photography.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nIn this workshop, you will get basic knowledge and useful tips about photography and then you will practice on historical and cultural places. And at the end, best photos will be displayed in the most popular place in Eskişehir. On the other hand, you will be able to explore Eskişehir’s nightlife, historical places around Eskişehir, Turkish cuisine and beauties of a student city.\r\n\r\nOne more thing; as you know we applied to Grant for this workshop. But results hasn’t been announced. If it will be accepted, we can pay to you your travels costs’ %70 as a standard procedure. We will share the news with you as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSee you in Eskişehir.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Apply : </b>As you know <a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> is not reachable. So you can fill this <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">form</a> and send us to apply until <a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> is on again.\r\n<div><i>For additional information please contact me.</i></div>', 'Photosynthesis 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3112-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '', 3112, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3812', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3813, 2, '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '<p dir="ltr">Ladies and gentlemen,</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The rumours you heard are true. EESTEC LC Skopje is proud to announce its second summer exchange, EESTECers Gone Wild 2. Motivated from the successful last year exchange, this time we offer you even more rocking summer.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">What is better time for exam get-away then summer? Sunny days, traveling round the country, tones of fun, parties 24/7 and all that with EESTECers from around Europe are just a few of the things included in our EESTEC vacation. Start planning now your wild get-away time!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Well Eestecers, the only thing that is obligatory to bring is your EESTEC spirit.The rest you can do is pack your swim suits and get your camera, because it’s time for shooting priceless moments from the wildest trip in the history.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir="ltr">Let us present you the unknown cities you will visit...</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/skopje.nspx" target="_blank">Skopje</a> (2 days)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- Probistip (1 day fun in the <a href="http://www.aquaparkmacedonia.mk/gallery-wts/?lang=en" target="_blank">Aquapark</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://travel2macedonia.com.mk/destinations/kavadarci" target="_blank">Kavadarci</a> (2 days tasting Macedonian wine and rakija)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/krusevo.nspx" target="_blank">Krusevo</a> (1 day breathing fresh mountain air with a stop in <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/prilep.nspx" target="_blank">Prilep</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/ohrid.nspx" target="_blank">Ohrid</a> (4 days - all night, all day, partying with participants from International Motivational Weekend)</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir="ltr">For more details, visit this <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1hkXjhrJ60qKPPN0xXEM_jr-yAbNrfMgtidNCz2AaxLQ/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">link</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Just to be on clear, during this EESTEC vacation we provide all the logistic and organization, but we can not provide the food and the accommodation. On this <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0Ahm5dmgMu2KBdERlMkV5bUtqZ1pDdlhLdjFTWlJ3SWc#gid=0" target="_blank">link</a> you can find price list for  average prices for the food, drinks and other expenses.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you are brave enough to be part of EesteCers Gone Wild 2, then fill this <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1nqTmy1YRZf5C6d5IWKHG28x6YgvQs9V6ZqlnonSnPGE/viewform" target="_blank">form</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Let your spirit do the walkin\' through the party rockin\'!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you have any kind of question or maybe suggestion or wishes what to visit or what to do you can contact us :  <a href="mailto:lcskopjecontact@gmail.com" target="_blank">lcskopjecontact@gmail.com</a></p>', 'EESTECers Gone Wild 2 - LC Skopje', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3108-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '', 3108, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3813', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3814, 2, '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\nEESTEC Chairpersons\' Meeting is the second biggest event of EESTEC. This year it will be held by <strong>LC Tallinn </strong>from <strong>3-9 November</strong>. Each LC, JLC and Observer has the right for<strong> one place</strong> on ECM. Therefore, we would kindly ask you to discuss with your Local Board and decide on the representative.\r\n\r\nApplications must be submitted via eestec.net and by sending an email to chairwoman[at]eestec[dot]net with the following information:\r\nFull name, LC, Position in your Local Board or LC\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you use the following tags in the subject of your email:\r\n[ECM\'13][Representative Application][LC \'NAME OF LC\']\r\n\r\nDeadline for applications is the <strong>7th of September</strong>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Main Goals of ECM 2013</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe main focus of ECM 2013 is both Local and International Level. First goal is to strengthen the (J)LCs and Observers by educating Board members via trainings and by sharing knowledge. Second goal is to improve the international awareness and involvement of the members.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to reach those Goals?</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nFollowing sessions/trainings will be held during ECM 2013 :\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n- GMs : 2 GMs will be held this year. Reports on the activities of the association on the past six months as well as RoP change proposals will be presented.\r\n\r\n- International awareness session : This session will be designed in 2 levels. The beginner level session, destined for less experienced representatives, will be an introduction to the structure and international projects in EESTEC. The advanced level, destined for experienced members, will be an introduction to challenges that EESTEC faces and also discussions will be held on how to overcome them.\r\n\r\n- LC Hangout : Evening Hangout with all LCs, where they can discuss with each other.\r\n\r\n- Open Space Technology (OST) : During this session, representatives will suggest topics to be discussed. Afterwards, they will vote on the topics they want to discuss and the most voted ones will be analyzed.\r\n\r\n- Trainings : 3 Soft Skills trainings for less experienced participants. Topics of those trainings will be announced later on.\r\n\r\n- Working sessions : In parallel with the Trainings, the experienced members will be invited to collect best practices of LCs into a document which will be presented and shared with the rest of the members at the end and after ECM. The topics of the working sessions will be announced later on.\r\n\r\n- EDUDay will be held on the 5th of November.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Profile of participants of ECM</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nConsidering the fact that there is only one place per LC and important decisions will be taken during ECM, the chairperson is highly recommended to attend. However, if it is not possible, then an experienced member or a future candidate for your board should attend.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>For any questions or clarifications, please send an email at board[at]eestec[dot]net.</div>\r\n</div>', 'EESTEC Chairpersons\' Meeting 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3144-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '', 3144, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3814', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3815, 2, '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The wait is finally over!</div>\r\n<div>LC Ljubljana is happy to announce its dual workshop "<strong>Facebook CPR</strong>"!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That\'s right.</div>\r\n<div>This year we\'re offering you not one, but TWO ways to improve your skills in EESTEC!</div>\r\n<div>Coding or Public Relations.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Are you a programmer? Do you want to become one? If you value order, structure and problem-solving, you can choose to enter the fun and innovative world of Facebook apps! Programming is one of the most valuable abilities a person can have today and the market is becoming huge! Imagine! The next Angry Birds might just as well be yours.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>What is the topic?</div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to teach attendees a basic understanding of facebook app programming and acquaint them with the developmental options that facebook supports. As a participant you will get a chance to develop your own application and implement facebook supported functions as well as work closely with professionals from successful app companies. You will also work on other aspects, such as public speaking and teamwork. Although you can join without any prior knowledge of programming, a basic understanding of HTML and Javascript is appreciated. The workshop itself will consist of lectures and programming sessions, where you will team up with other EESTECers to work on your application.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>But that\'s not all! We at LC Ljubljana know that a student\'s mind can\'t work properly without some kind of release. A head full of knowledge can collapse under its own weight. So we took care of that too! We have prepared a number of fun social activities that take care of your mind and soul. On top of that you will be able to explore the beautiful streets of Ljubljana, enjoy its charming and vibrant nightlife and even attend the legendary City Rally!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That has to be it, right?</div>\r\n<div>WRONG!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After the workshop, you\'ll also get to attend the International Motivational Weekend. It is a huge EESTEC event with people all across Europe. It includes soft-skill training, socializing with EESTECers from numerous LCs, crazy themed parties and best of all: it\'s free for all workshop attendees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 19th (arrival day) to the 27th (departure day) of October 2013 and become part of another unforgettable EESTEC experience here in Ljubljana, Slovenia.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We\'re hearing some rumours (hint: 404) that <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> still doesn\'t function as it\'s supposed to, so we\'ve put up a <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1J6zrtOzwy89qMmjsQSdU74yGlMYL2oZO6vPkp6xN9as/viewform" target="_blank">form where you can apply</a>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>See you all in Ljubljana!</div>\r\n</div>', 'Facebook CPR: FB Apps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3140-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '', 3140, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3815', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3816, 2, '2013-11-21 23:29:07', '2013-11-21 23:29:07', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAfter the success of LC Hamburg\'s last workshop - "The EesteCube", we are presenting our brand new production “DiscoTech”\r\n\r\nThe curtains haven\'t been raised yet, but our short "trailer" will give you some hints of what awaits you.\r\n\r\nIn the main role are starring ten (eventually more) professional Eestecers.\r\n\r\nAgain the story takes place in the greenest and probably most beautiful city in Europe - Hamburg.\r\n\r\nThe plot consists of unforgettable nights at the famous ‘Reeperbahn’ street, a trip to one of the biggest airline companies - Lufthansa, as well as, visiting the second biggest harbor in Europe. Moreover, there will be an adventurous city rally and a canoe ride in our favorite lake in the middle of the city - the Alster, all accompanied by "tasting" of German beer. And all these amazing scenes will be enlightened by the unique devices that our smart main characters are going to build.\r\n\r\nRegarding the academical part, this time the actors will have to show how music and lights combine through technology. Their task will be to make frequency analysis of audio files and with the help of digital signal processing and some RGB LEDs make the music shine. Therefore, you can take your talent our of the closet, record yourself singing, playing your favorite instruments, or just making silly noises.. eestec style.. and see what kind of beautiful enlightment would come out.\r\n\r\nThe scenario will be presented by our professors and co-students, however in order to pass the casting the actors should have basic C programming knowledge.\r\n\r\nSo put your costumes and makeup on, get your mp3 players and apply for this fascinating workshop.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">We are waiting for you!</span>', 'DiscoTech', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3135-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:29:07', '2013-11-21 23:29:07', '', 3135, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3816', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3817, 2, '2013-11-21 23:31:35', '2013-11-21 23:31:35', 'Dear Eestecers,\r\n<div>It has come to our knowledge that the period between <strong>July 18th</strong> to <strong>July 21th</strong> is the time you will have the most fun this summer, period full with tourists and a lot of parties. Well, probably because it’s time for LC Skopje to announce and invite you to its first International Motivational Weekend, held in Ohrid, one of the most beautiful cities in Macedonia.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc" target="_blank"><strong>Ohrid</strong></a> is known as the pearl of the Balkan and if you want to party until the morning hours it is definitely a place to be with its numerous beach parties. Because of the uniqueness of Ohrid Lake and the city, they are part of UNESCO, as one of the few places on the list “World Inheritance”.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>This IMW is extremely important for our LC, not only because we are organizing for the first time but also this year we are celebrating our “The number of your fingers” Birthday :P So we will be very pleased if you come to celebrate it with us on EESTEC commonly known way :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>It’s not only our birthday associated with the number 10. This year is coming <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/143474625847806/?context=create" target="_blank"><strong>EESTECers Gone Wild 2</strong></a> , but this time even wilder :P The adventurous crew of LC Skopje is offering you 10 days (including the IMW) of crazy summer vacation and a chance to see the nature beauty of our country.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The participation fee for the IMW is <strong>50€</strong> and it includes both ways ticket from Skopje to Ohrid, accommodation, 3 meals per day and of course drinks. Also it includes a little surprise which we guarantee you will like it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>So EESTECers, this means all you have to do is apply, bring yourself here in Macedonia and take your EESTEC Spirit with you to have a wild summer break.</div>\r\n<div>We promise you will feel all summer joys…</div>\r\n<div></div>', 'IMW: 10 years LC Skopje', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3106-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:31:35', '2013-11-21 23:31:35', '', 3106, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3817', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3818, 2, '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Dear  EESTECers,</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Have glamorous events and movie spotlights always been out of reach? Have you always dreamt of experiencing the spirit of Hollywood? If so, you’re in luck! LC Sarajevo will provide you the ideal opportunity to learn everything you have ever wanted to know about movies: producing, editing, acting and much more.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Europe\'s most awesome LC is proud to invite you to the <b>3rd eMovie Academy</b>, which is becoming a tradition appealing to many potential artists and movie fanatics. We are offering you a week of fun, a week of glamour, a week of learning and most of all a week of <b>EESTEC Spirit</b>! Join us from <b>15th to 22nd of August </b>and enjoy the best experience of your life!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">The academical aspect will contain lectures and workshops about elements of movie making. You will learn to use professional software tools for movie-making, and at the end you will be able to make your own movie!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">In the period from 16th to 24th of August Sarajevo will gather movie elite from all over the world in one place, and bring them closer to fans and movie lovers. This is the period of one of the most respected movie festivals in Europe - the <b>Sarajevo Film Festival</b>. During the festival, Sarajevo becomes the center of Europe\'s best cinema and entertainment! Movie stars such as Angelina Jolie, Morgan Freeman, Brad Pitt and Kevin Spacey are amongst the lucky people who have experienced Sarajevo at its best - don’t miss this opportunity to become one of them!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">But that’s not all! You will be able to explore Sarajevo’s nightlife, cultural diversity, our delicious food, and the hospitality of our citizens. If you\'re still having second thoughts, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" target="_blank">take a look at the atmosphere during eMovie Academy \'11</a>!</span></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">We guarantee you a week of unforgettable experiences, education and excitement!</span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Feel free to ask any questions you might have, and dare to join us in this adventure!</span>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">We are waiting for you!</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'eMovie Academy \'13', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3104-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '', 3104, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3818', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3819, 2, '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '<p dir="ltr">Welcome on board to flight 86 to Chalkidiki (<em><a href="https://maps.google.gr/maps?q=poseidi&amp;gbv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=el&amp;authuser=0" target="_blank">Possidi</a></em>). This is your captain <strong>LC Athens</strong>. We will be cruising at a crazy student altitude where everybody has fun and unforgettable memories at a “halara” (hint: relaxed, cool)  airspeed of reggae rhythm and not only... The weather is clear and sunny and with the tailwind on our side we are expecting a high temperature which will increase as more and more people apply for this <strong>IMW</strong>. If the parties cooperate we should get a great view of the city as we descend... The cabin crew will be coming around to offer you a snack and a drink, and the experience of your lifetime will begin shortly after that. I\'ll talk to you again before we reach our destination.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Translation:\r\nYes, ladies and gentlemen you are already on a plane or on a bus (or who knows where else) and you are heading to Possidi where the <em>IMW of Greece Me Up vol.2</em> is going to be held.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Possidi is the camp of the university of Thessaloniki and as you can imagine, it is full of students who want to take a rest after a tough year and have some fun...like you! You will have the chance to enjoy the greek sunny weather, the beach, crazy activities, awesome parties and of course the Greek hospitality.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The participation fee is 50€ without the tent and transportation from Thessaloniki to Possidi and backwards. Concerning transportation to and from Possidi, it will be announced near the deadline, but arriving with your own means of transport is acceptable.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to be a part of this awesome experience apply now in <a href="https://gmuv2-unof-form.typeform.com/to/ON9pUS" target="_blank">this form</a>  in which you can find all the information and the details you may need.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Until then, sit back, halara (hint: relax) and enjoy the rest of the flight.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>P.S.</strong> You can find more information in our site <a href="http://greecemeup.net/" target="_blank">http://greecemeup.net/</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><b>Contact mail:</b> Giannis Sotiropoulos (C.P.): <a>js.lcathens@gmail.com</a>\r\nEleni Santorinaiou (H.O.)   : <a>elsantor8@gmail.com</a></p>', 'IMW in Greece 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3099-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '', 3099, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3819', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3821, 2, '2013-11-21 23:47:01', '2013-11-21 23:47:01', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAre you ready to Cross the Line with LC Podgorica one more time?\r\n\r\nBe prepared, this year there will be more action, more excitement and even more lines to cross! You will experience 7 days of unforgettable atmosphere, EESTEC spirit and memories for a lifetime.\r\n\r\nLC Podgorica is taking you to <b>Kotor</b>, which is situated in Europe\'s southernmost <a title="Fjord" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fjord" target="_blank">fjord</a> called - Boka Kotorska (The Bay of Kotor, or Boka Bay). Kotor is one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast (UNESCO protected) . You will be able to experience Mediterranean spirit, see one of the most beautiful bays in Europe during the cruise that we will organize, and visit Gospa od Škrpjela (Our Lady of the Rocks) island.\r\n\r\nYou will see <b>Budva</b>, a pearl of Mediterranean, and a <a title="Luxury yacht" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_yacht" target="_blank">luxury yacht</a> <a title="Marina" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marina" target="_blank">marina</a> <b>Porto</b> <b>Montenegro</b>. Beside sightseeing and city rally, you will also have a chance to enjoy your stay in Montenegro on beautiful beaches of Budva, Tivat and Kotor and do summer activities with us.\r\n\r\nBut wait, that’s not all... The most important thing is the <b>Kotor Carnival</b>, one of the biggest and craziest carnivals in Europe! We are preparing many more surprises that will remain a secret for now... Sooo APPLY !\r\n\r\nThis event will also have an educational part. Considering that you are probably tired of engineering, we decided to make  workshops on photography, journalism  and filmmaking where you will be able to release your creativity. Summer and sunny days will surely inspire you! Also two EESTEC trainers will give you some innovative and damn interesting trainings, in order to motivate and relax you more and more...\r\n\r\nSo pack up your swimsuits, good mood, EESTEC Spirit and <b>Cross the Line</b> in Montenegro! We are waiting for you!', 'Cross the Line 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3044-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:47:01', '2013-11-21 23:47:01', '', 3044, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3821', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3822, 2, '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Dear EESTECers,\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">LC Belgrade is proud to announce its first <a href="http://tinyurl.com/cd2zv47" target="_blank">International Motivational Weekend</a>, which will be held from 17th to 19th May! We are bringing the participants of our workshop <strong>„World Beyond Tomorrow",</strong> as a conclusion to a great event! The best way to participate at the IMW is to apply for our workshop!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Prepare yourself to enjoy in the youth camp Đerdap, located in the tourist region Karataš, just in the period in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring! You will have the chance to enjoy in our beautiful countryside, visit Hydroelectric Power Station „Đerdap 1" - the largest and first producer of hydroelectricity in Southeast Europe, take part in many fun activities like the games without limits, indoor soccer tournaments, beach volleyball, beer pong in the evening, have great fun at the parties and a lot of other funny things!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">The participation fee is <strong>55€</strong>, which includes return journey from Belgrade to Karataš, accommodation, 3 meals a day, drinks and free theme parties. At the IMW we will be accompanied by members of association <i>ESTIEM LG Belgrade</i>, so we definitely need all of you to join us and show them our EESTEC spirit! Also, you can ask us to book a room for you at the hostel in Belgrade, if you want to stay few more days.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Our bus will leave Belgrade at 09:00 am on Friday and back from the location on a Sunday afternoon.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">We promise you won\'t regret it! <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/belgrade/imw-belgrade-2013" target="_blank">See you in Serbia</a>!</span></p>', 'IMW Belgrade 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2910-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '', 2910, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3822', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3823, 2, '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe’re proud to announce the second edition of a workshop entitled ‘Smart Energy for a Better World’, in cooperation with ABB Corporate Research Centre, which will be held in Krakow from 7th till 13th of July 2013.\r\n\r\nThis study tour is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science. The event will be a unique opportunity to visit one of the most advanced ABB Research Centers in the world and to broaden your knowledge on:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advanced numerical simulations</li>\r\n	<li>Power electronics</li>\r\n	<li>Transients phenomena</li>\r\n	<li>Smart Protection</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced diagnostics</li>\r\n	<li>Ferroresonance phenomena</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll students from European Universities are invited to join us in Krakow, one of Poland\'s most renown cities. This event will be a great occasion to meet experts on energy, electrical sciences and to visit Poland\'s well-known tourist attractions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are waiting for applications from students who have:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>electrical engineering profile</li>\r\n	<li>good academic results</li>\r\n	<li>good command of English</li>\r\n	<li>completed at least 3 years of university education</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMore information about the lectures and lab excercises can be found on the website of the event <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeel the EESTEC Spirit and join us in Kraków. See with your own eyes the beauty one of the biggest city in Poland with its historicial treasures and vivid nightlife. You’ve got an unusual opportunity to visit i.a.:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the Wawel Royal Castle - located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;</li>\r\n	<li>the Underground of the City’s Main Market Square – unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will go on a tour to Kryspinów lake, barbecue at the biggest student campus in Poland or have a bowling night. We won’t reveal all of the spicy attractions we’ve prepared. We can say you’ll certainly experience the amazing nightlife and many other activities so you won’t get chance to get bored. Apply now or regret through the lifetime.\r\n\r\nHow to apply:\r\n\r\n1. EESTEC members: via eestec.net, where you should write down your motivational letter and send your CV to <a href="mailto:krakow@eestec.net">krakow@eestec.net</a>\r\n\r\n2. Non-EESTECers: via website: <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">smart.eestec.pl</a>\r\n\r\nWe’re waiting for You in Krakow! ;)\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<a id="parent-fieldname-eventUrl" href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">More information about this event…</a>', 'Smart Energy for a Better World 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2673-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '', 2673, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3823', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3824, 2, '2013-11-21 23:48:10', '2013-11-21 23:48:10', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe, LC Delft, are proud to announce our next workshop “Tie Another Day – A challange from Mars”,\r\n\r\nFirst of all, welcome to the <strong>Mars rover project</strong>! In this powerful workshop we give you a directive to design a complex system. We have taken a top-down approach. This way you can understand the operation of the increasingly larger parts within the whole system.\r\n\r\nIn the first part of the workshop you will design a mobile robot (the Mars Rover) in a group of students. This robot has to be able to search for a line and then track the line and take turns. Some <strong>additional intelligence </strong>has to be added as well. The design steps are not only useful for this workshop, but also for complex systems in general. First you focus at the problem as a whole, and then the problem is divided into even smaller parts which are then implemented. This is the so-called top-down approach.\r\n\r\nIn the design you have to deal with operation and readout of input signals (sensors), output actuators  the motors) and a controller. The robot is programmed in VHDL. VHDL is a Hardware Description Language (HDL), a language which is used to help design digital circuits.\r\n\r\nIn order to test the Mars Rover, <strong>a complex maze</strong> is available. Your Mars Rover has to find the way out as fast as possible. As an added challenge, the maze contains instructions for the Mars Rover for making sharp turns that allows a faster traversal of the maze.\r\n\r\nThe second part of the workshop focuses on the <strong>power supply of the Mars Rover</strong>. In the first part of the workshop, the robot will use batteries as its power supply. If the batteries run out of power, you can easily replace them. However, on Mars this would pose a problem. In order to be able to use the Mars rover for an extended amount of time, an alternative energy source is needed. On Mars it is possible to use solar energy to power the Mars rover. In the second part of the workshop you will examine a solar cell and design additional circuits in order to use the solar energy as the power supply of the Mars rover.\r\n\r\nObvious this is not everything in the weekend and at every evening there will be time to explore other things like Delft and The Netherlands.  So don’t hesitate and apply before Friday the 19<sup>th</sup> of april.\r\n\r\nFor Questions don’t hesitate to contact <a href="mailto:cp@etv.tudelft.nl">cp@etv.tudelft.nl</a> for further questions.', 'Tie Another Day - A Challenge from Mars', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2670-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:48:10', '2013-11-21 23:48:10', '', 2670, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3824', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3825, 2, '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Hello dear friends, students and other members of NGOs!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Leadership Summer School is coming!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Do you want to inspire people? Do you have plans to lead a project in your NGO? Do you think that the word “leader” describes you?</i></b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Interested?  </i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Apply to LSS`13.</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><i><span style="color: #000000;">Our project will help you discover your potential!</span></i></b>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Together we can change the world!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">==============================<wbr />==========================\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b> ==What is LSS?===</b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The Leadership Summer School is an intensive learning event and a networking platform, aiming at increasing skills and readiness of youth NGO leaders, sharing best practices and improving leadership skills among prominent members of each participating organisation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What are we looking for?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">We are looking for <b>70 highly motivated and active students and youth</b> who will participate to a challenging learning event.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> <b>===When and Where?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Sofia (Bulgaria)<i> f</i></span>rom <b>21st till 30th of July 2013</b>\r\n\r\n<img alt="Inline images 2" src="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/?ui=2&amp;ik=6c33839bd5&amp;view=att&amp;th=13dad4cf0ee7a16d&amp;attid=0.1&amp;disp=emb&amp;realattid=ii_13dad39a8865b14e&amp;zw&amp;atsh=1" width="420" height="310" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What about the fee? ===</b> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The fee will be <b>190 EUR </b>which includes:\r\n</span>- accommodation;\r\n- food (3 meals per day + coffee breaks);\r\n- transport for LSS activities;\r\n- and some social activities.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">If selected to participate in the event, it will be requested from you to pay 50% of the fee (95 EUR) as participation confirmation: this amount is <i><b>not refundable</b></i>. The rest can be paid anticipatively or at the event itself. More details will be communicated at that moment.</span>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;">We are not able to provide scholarship or any form of discount.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></i>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===How to apply?===</span></b>\r\n\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></b>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Fill the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1zqu6fpLsWGk9QtI5Ln72Pzlx2BWv9xWiEF6Ha19Qn2A/viewform" target="_blank">LSS 2013 Application form</a>.</span>\r\n<div><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<div><i><b>Deadline to apply: April  14th 23:59 CET</b></i></div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===And now ===</span></b>\r\nWe are looking forward to reading your applications and if you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to contact us by mail: <a href="mailto:contact@leadershipsummerschool.org" target="_blank">contact@<wbr />leadershipsummerschool.org</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Leadership Summer School 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2664-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '', 2664, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3825', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3826, 2, '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are proud to announce our next workshop. After a long tradition of successful workshops, we are still trying to do better and improve our offer! This time we will amuse you with a workshop related to Green and Eco Friendly Technologies.\r\nFuture Technologies are coming to be more and more green. Our lectures will deal with Green Computing technologies, having a deep practical insight: we will have the honor to host some successful StartUp in this field, that will explain how it works in real life.\r\n\r\nGreen Economy is the new challenge, and we are ready to catch it!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMoreover this year there will be an exclusive news! Our workshop will be held in collaboration with ESTIEM Association (European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management). Green supply chain will be the other topic that you will have the opportunity do deal with.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt means a double opportunity to meet and melt with Students from all Europe!!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAcademics activity will be just a short (but heaped) bracket in your experience here in Cosenza.\r\nCosenza is the biggest Campus in the South of Italy. A neighborhood made up exclusively of 2000 Students and 200 Erasmus Students, offers one of the most brave and challenging night life! <strong>Get ready for it!!!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou will have also the opportunity to visit the most stunning and breathtaking landscapes of our land! The land of the sun, the sea and the good food! All this delved in a rich cultural background ( don\'t forget that Pitagora was born in Calabria ;) ).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCalabria is waiting for you, see you there!!! :D\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPS: We will provide you a detailed programme as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'GECO (Green Engineering COmputing)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2652-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '', 2652, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3826', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3827, 2, '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '<div> Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>All of you probably remember one of the most known Latin phrases: "Historia est Magistra Vitae" :) We sure do and we are proud to announce our workshop which pretty much bases on this phrase. If you apply for “Back in Time” we can promise you won’t regret it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Have you ever wondered how stuff worked before almost everything went digital and computer controlled? All those interesting and smart solutions everyone has forgotten about? In Zagreb you will have a chance to get familiar with them. Old principles of automatics, programming, power engineering and wireless technology can always come in handy to today’s modern engineers. We will make comparisons between old and new, and make conclusions with pros and cons for each individual technology/solution/approach.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Now let’s get to the more interesting part of the workshop – our beautiful city of Zagreb. You will get in touch with every part of Croatian culture and have an opportunity to taste our delicious cousin and our inspiring drinks. Also, you will get a chance to enjoy our beautiful Adriatic coast and our crystal clear sea ;)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Our museums are going to give you a very good insight into our culture and you will spend time exploring Zagreb in a really interesting way. We will make sure you have enough time to enjoy the city and relax.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>And the most important part – you’ll attend the most awesome parties in Zagreb and we can assure you that you will remember them for your life.</div>\r\n<div>So, don’t hesitate to apply to our super duper workshop! We promise you good time :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>If you have any questions or need more convincing just contact us.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>With love from LC Zagreb &lt;3</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><br clear="all" /> </span></span></span></div>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Xsz49mzCVg0" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Back in Time', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2650-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '', 2650, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3827', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3828, 2, '2013-11-21 23:50:10', '2013-11-21 23:50:10', 'Greetings from The North.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEverything today is driven by computers, bigger or smaller ones. Almost everything that has any kind of electronics includes a computing unit also. So what are these, why they make so complex things work? We try to find this answer for you as we open the world of digital technology for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAND SO! We proudly announce our new workshop  "Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79". Our fellows at computer techlab are more than welcoming to take you for a tour in the world of computing with ones and zeros.<b></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor one week our LC is happy to host you to enjoy our beautiful city of Tampere, the northernmost LC in eestec. If you think this is going to be one of those easier workshops where you can sleep between lectures then you’re gravely mistaken. We indeed take our education seriously but we take our parties even more seriously. In one week we will introduce you to the whole new world of sauna, singing, Finnish culture, city life of “small town” and the right Finnish way of doing things wrong.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo, everyone who has any interest in digital designs, embedded systems, computers or just generally is trying to find something interesting to study, we openly welcome you.\r\n\r\nWe’d really appreciate those applications that have some information about what you generally study and what you know about digital designs and computer technologies as our professor may want people to have some degree of knowledge about the area.', 'Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2488-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:50:10', '2013-11-21 23:50:10', '', 2488, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3828', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3829, 2, '2013-11-21 23:50:30', '2013-11-21 23:50:30', 'Hey Everyone!\r\n\r\nGreetings from the island where Aphrodite born, where Shakspeare’s Othello Castle is, where the one of the longest beach of world, where the place that caretta carettas choose to live, and where the place of our workshop that we are inviting you,\r\n\r\nLadies (and maybe Gentlemen!)\r\n\r\nSunnydays by LC Famagusta : )\r\n\r\nAll came from the stars, they said, and we came from our star, the Sun. Now, we have the technology to produce energy that our civilization desperately needs. So, the workshop Sunnydays is all about that. We got seminars and lectures about solar energy and also a visit to recently built photovoltaic power station.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to entertainment, we got some “hot” plans for you. The spring festival of our university will take place at same time with this event so the city will never sleep ! We are inviting you over to share the great fun in our tropical campus with more than 15000 students including people from 68 different countries. Yacht Party, City Rally, Windsurfing, Karaoke Parties, Discos, Sea, Sun, Beach Parties, Beaches and Beaches… what else do you need?\r\n\r\nSo prepare your swimming suits and apply !\r\n\r\nPlease don’t hesitate if you have questions. We will be more than glad to answer them .', 'SunnyDays', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2216-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:50:30', '2013-11-21 23:50:30', '', 2216, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3829', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3830, 2, '2013-11-21 23:52:43', '2013-11-21 23:52:43', 'Prepare every single cell in your body, cause you are going to become time traveller in Belgrade, and we will give our best to be great companions in this journey. We\'re happy to announce that this May you could be the part of "World Beyond Tomorrow".\r\n\r\nGuiding you through a regular family day, twenty years from now, lecturers will introduce you with new necessary technologies. Familiar with all the details and needed knowledge about 4G, hologram, must-have robots, and all innovations that strive to become a part of our everyday life, the future will seem like the present to you. In cooperation with ESTIEM, the organisation for European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management, we will show you admirable landscapes of our country and the way we define word <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=--c03roM4nI" target="_blank">party</a>. So, you will also have the opportunity to meet with members of their event which would be held side-by-side with our workshop.\r\n\r\nAfter a long time, we decided to show you the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Zu_tkk9be0" target="_blank">White city</a> in the period when you can see it in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring. Ada Ciganlija, oasis of nature in the busy city life, is waiting for you, as well as Kalemegdan, Skadarlija, Nikola Tesla Museum, Knez Mihailova street... You will have the chance to enjoy traditional <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" target="_blank">Serbian cuisine</a>, gibanica, ajvar, pljeskavica and of course rakija.\r\n\r\nApply now, and enjoy in knowledge and party time warp! :)\r\n\r\nSee you in Serbia,\r\nAnita Jović.', 'World Beyond Tomorrow', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2562-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:52:43', '2013-11-21 23:52:43', '', 2562, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3830', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3831, 2, '2013-11-21 23:57:13', '2013-11-21 23:57:13', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nThis May, Madrid will be the place to be. We proudly present our yearly workshop, with a brand new name: <b>Going Green!</b>, based in the challenging field of Green Technology.\r\n<p align="JUSTIFY">We live in a society with a higher demand of energy. This increasing necessity has become a real problem, directly affecting our environment and natural resources. Accordingly, it is not a surprise that companies have started pursuing a maintainable productive model and investing part of their incomes in this new Green Technology. However, what is then Green Technology? Just the application of technology and echo sciences to the preservation of our ecosystem. Green technology is a field of new, innovative ways to make changes in daily life. Currently, this Clean Technology is in the beginning stages of its development, so the future will only bring bigger and better things.</p>\r\nUnder this green theme, lectures will deepen into the subjects of energetic efficiency, sustainable development or echo-friendly buildings. Furthermore, the week will be completed with visits to some of our University laboratories, other companies’ researching centers and even real examples of sustainable houses. So, <b>from 5th to 12th of May </b>participants will have the chance to enlarge both their theoretical and practical knowledge in the matter.\r\n\r\nBut wait, there is more. We don’t forget about our city, Madrid, and its major and minor secrets. During afternoons, history, through monuments and buildings, will be revealed before our eyes, while nights will be dedicated to explore the meaning of “fiesta”. The capital of Spain is known for its never-sleeping life, and we will invite you to discover it with us (would you be willing to try your own limits? <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" /> ).\r\n\r\nTo end the event with the best sensation, we prepared a special weekend in the countryside. Two days, lost in the rural area of a near mountain. Time to relax, time to nature and, again, time to party. What else can you ask for ??\r\n\r\nPerhaps we could add some of our Spanish spirit to the mixture … Drinking sangría or eating tortilla and jamón, along with our natural cheerful attitude will bring you closer to our lively culture. Don’t hesitate and apply <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":D" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" /> , you have till <b>24th of March </b>to make up your mind\r\n\r\nFinally, as we always say…We are so sorry to have to say this, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although last years were faultless <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" /> , we expect an exemplary attitude from all of you and we friendly ask you for cooperation and comprehension. Irresponsible attitudes won’t be tolerated and in case it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.\r\n\r\nWhen it is time to party, we party (and trust me, we will! ;D), but when it’s time to work, we must work (and later we have party! ^^).\r\n\r\nYou don’t wanna miss this!!!\r\n\r\nHope to see you all in Madrid!\r\n\r\n<b>Follow us</b><b>: <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.eestec.es\']);" href="http://www.eestec.es/" target="_blank">Website</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.facebook.com\']);" href="http://www.facebook.com/#%21/pages/Eestec-Eurielec/115934218476771" target="_blank">Facebook</a> </b>and<b> <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://twitter.com\']);" href="https://twitter.com/#%21/eestecLCMadrid" target="_blank">Twit<wbr />ter</a></b>', 'Going Green! Engineer your future', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2219-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:57:13', '2013-11-21 23:57:13', '', 2219, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3831', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3832, 2, '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After a very successful last year&#8217;s exchange we decided to go further and create an even more memorable event for you. This time we did our best to enable more of you to come &#8211; we hope for 18 enthusiastic EESTECers to visit us and spend the <a href="http://youtu.be/opqZAXJ4t0o" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://youtu.be\']);" target="_blank">best week</a> of spring 2013 in the city with a largest student community in Poland – which of course means the greatest student’s traditions . It is our pleasure to announce that Krakow’s gates are opening for you again!</p>\n<p>You will experience living in the biggest student’s campus in Poland - <a href="http://youtu.be/SiMHTK15Pik" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://youtu.be\']);" target="_blank">it’s over 9000</a> people! Besides, we will present to you the <b>most important parts of Krakow</b> and a bit of <b>Polish history</b>.</p>\n<p>Since there is only a small academic part planned, you will have plenty of time to relax and recharge your batteries for the rest of semester. However, we prefer active leisure time, so prepare for an <b>intensive week</b>. There will be no opportunity to get bored! We have an awesome programme for you, including a bike tour ending with an open-air beer-tasting evening, a legendary lasertag competition and many, many more&#8230;!</p>\n<p>Wait, have we mentioned the parties? Believe us, no two nights are going to be the same. We prepared a variety of night-time activities for you: outdoors, student-only clubs, theme parties – whatever you can think of <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>But more to that! If this is not enough for you, at the end of the week we will <a href="http://youtu.be/432iaBjdgjI" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://youtu.be\']);" target="_blank">travel to Zakopane</a> – a beautiful city at the foot of Tatra Mountains, known as &#8220;the winter capital of Poland&#8221; and also a center of Gorals culture.  There, you will have a chance to enjoy the beauty of the highest Polish mountains and local folklore.</p>\n<p>We promise amazing atmosphere with EESTEC Spirit, great company and many surprises! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Curious about how student life should be like? <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/krakow/charge-up-in-krakow-2013-spring-exchange-2013" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">Apply now! </a><br />\n<b>CU in Krakow</b></p>\n<p><i>NOTE: When booking tickets, please keep in mind that we will be back in Krakow (from Zakopane) on Sunday at noon. If you intend to go to EESTEC Congress afterwards, there is a cheap connection (from 50 €) with Munich by variety of transport means. We can help with arranging additional nights and buying tickets.<br />\n</i></p>\n', 'Charge Up in Krakow – Spring Exchange 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2218-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '', 2218, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3832', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3833, 2, '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '\n<div></div>\n<p>Dear EESTECers,The wait is over! RoboMAC has been announced&#8230; and this years edition of the annual robotics competition carries the much creative title: RoboMAC 2013.</p>\n<p>RoboMac 2012 was quite&#8230; well&#8230; an absolutely awesome event! Building robots and having good time &#8211; perfect recipe for one of the best weeks of my life. Thank you, dear Organizers! &#8211; Daniel Materowski</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re brave enough to click &#8220;the button&#8221; and apply, your skills and knowledge will be tested in different categories depending on your interest. If you are ready to enter a week full with hi-tech stuff: flying quadcopters, intelligent vehicles, walking humanoids, and not so mobile participants you know where is the flashy button we&#8217;re talking about.During this awesome week we will gradually introduce you into the world of robotics, up from the basis to the very next frontier of this field. At the end of the week the teams will have the chance to stand against each other and compete with their creations in front of an demanding audience.<br />\nBest week ever. Legendary. &#8211; Ismail Morgenegg</p>\n<p>Ahh and the non-academic part&#8230; The crew at our LC as always, are here well prepared<br />\nfor introducing you to the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=ju0lU9fzEsE" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">beauties of Skopje,</a> introducing to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=CRgLmCQzEAo" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">our cuisine</a> and showing you everything that Skopje has to offer, imagination is yours!<br />\nVisit <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/skopje/robomac-2013-1" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/skopje/robomac-2013-1</a> to apply now!</p>\n', 'RoboMAC 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2220-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '', 2220, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3833', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3834, 2, '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Tuzla proudly presents our newest workshop!\r\n\r\nMicrocontrollers? Sounds familiar, right?\r\nIf not yet, then at some point during your studies you will get a chance to work with one. Later on there’s a huge chance you might even get to play with one at your office.\r\n\r\nThe application of microcontrollers in order to improve the efficiency of energy systems is something new. That is why EESTEC LC Tuzla decided to organize a workshop on “Rapid Instrumentation for Customized Energy Efficient Systems”.\r\nDon’t worry, you will not spend all of your time listening to lectures. We have provided brand new microcontrollers just for you to play with in the laboratory.\r\nThe knowledge you will gain will, with no doubts, ensure you the ticket to enter the big world of microcontrollers.\r\n\r\nSo are you ready to explore Energy Efficient Systems TEChnology, or as we like to call it EESTEChnology?\r\nNot yet?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWell good, because we haven’t told you everything.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLC Tuzla has prepared a truly unique experience for you. If you want to enjoy the famous Bosnian atmosphere, an elegant blend of traditional and modern, East and West, then the “Salt city” is the right place to visit. Just imagine, you are sitting on the shores of the Pannonian lake, the only salt lake in Europe, looking at the mosque and church standing next to each other in the background while the nice sound of traditional Bosnian music comes to your ears.\r\nYes, we have so much salt that we made salt lakes. You will learn all about it while visiting the Salt factory and Museum of Salt.\r\nBeing tired from lectures and the city atmosphere you will also have a chance to spend one day in pure nature, at the famous tourist resort near our city, Zlaca.\r\n\r\nLast, but not least and perhaps most important  – Bosnian cuisine! All of the ćevapi, pie and dolma lovers will come to the right place. Those who aren’t yet will definitely become one after this trip.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDo you need more reasons to come, learn and have fun with us?\r\n\r\nLC Tuzla is waiting for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHave a look at these videos about Tuzla and Bosnia and Herzegovina:\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EPtjxx1ht5Y" target="_blank">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EPtjxx1ht5Y</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rinQSOVUvrU" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rinQSOVUvrU</a>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'EESTEChnology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2221-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '', 2221, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3834', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3835, 2, '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe are very glad to officially announce Congress 2013 registration period. From now and till 5th of March all LCs, JLCs and Observers have a chance to register their representative for Congress which will take place from 23rd till 30th of April in Munich, Germany.\r\nEach LC, JLC and Observer have a right for at least one place on Congress. If you do not register your representative till the deadline, Int. Board will assign place for your LC to BAs, Trainers, IT members and other international teams.\r\n\r\nPlease do not miss the deadline 5th of March for your registration!\r\n<strong>What kind of participants are expected at the Congress?</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nIt’s totally up to the LC/JLC/Observer to decide who you want to send on Congress as your official representatives. Representatives should be experienced, familiar with EESTEC structure and ready to participate actively on Congress.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>What do we expect from participants during Congress?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe expect that every LC has at least one representative during every General Assembly (GA) sessions. It is inexcusable to miss any GA since we are going to have discussion on very important topics for EESTEC such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>  EESTEC projects</li>\r\n	<li>  Board and Bodies report</li>\r\n	<li>  Promotion and degradation of LCs and JLCs</li>\r\n	<li>  RoP changing</li>\r\n	<li>  Election of the new International Board and Bodies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>What you should do besides the registration on eestec.net:</strong>\r\n\r\nTo select and manage the applicants we kindly ask you to fill in the following form after you have applied on EESTEC.net. If you do not, your application won’t be considered as valid.\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://docs.google.com\']);" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dDhXREFYUW1jWi12RElld2hqMjNaV3c6MA#gid=0" target="_blank">EESTEC Congress Munich – Application Info</a>\r\n\r\nFurthermore, please fill in another form with which we collect information about the universities to be represented on the Open Day. Please do this task as soon as possible, since we need the information for printing them on the Open Day booklet.\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://docs.google.com\']);" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dFJhTkItTFBtMS1CWW5uNGM0VzN1LXc6MQ#gid=0" target="_blank">Open Day – University Facts</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis year we will also have Open Day as part of Congress 2013. Open Day can be counted as a “fair” where there are booths for participating companies, universities, EESTEC local committees and international Board, and every representative are free to visit each others’ booths for information exchange about any idea or opportunity. You can check how OpenDay looked like on previous Congress <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9Y69aQeeHcg" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What do you need to bring for Open Day?</strong>\r\n\r\nEvery LC representative should bring on Congress:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>  Informational materials of your University-Faculty (this is most important)</li>\r\n	<li>  Informational materials of your LC (also very important)</li>\r\n	<li>  Promo materials of your LC activities (posters, flyers, bookmarks…)</li>\r\n	<li>  LC flag (only if you have one, don’t need to make if you don’t have)</li>\r\n	<li>  Prepare ınformational (at least 1 page) documents or presentation/slides which includes:</li>\r\n	<li>  Your recruitment Strategy (how you get new members every year)</li>\r\n	<li>  What makes your LC successful? (your successful projects, activities…)</li>\r\n	<li>  How you keep motivations of your members? (motivation strategies, tips and tricks)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><em><strong>To sum up and again the most important, don’t miss deadline for registration,</strong></em><strong> 5th of March, </strong><em><strong>since after that deadline, International Board will give your places to Bodies.</strong></em>Waiting for your registration,</div>\r\nEESTEC International Board and LC Munich\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n–\r\n\r\nFor questions please contact:\r\n\r\nCongress-CP: Wataru Oshima, coc2013munich(at)gmail.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nInformation about unofficial participation will be sent in the next days.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<a id="parent-fieldname-eventUrl" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://congress.eestec.net\']);" href="http://congress.eestec.net" target="_blank"> More information about this event…</a>', 'EESTEC Congress 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2222-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '', 2222, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3835', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3836, 2, '2013-11-21 23:59:12', '2013-11-21 23:59:12', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Munich is honored to present you the sequel of our <em>Women in Engineering </em>workshop from <strong>April 23rd </strong>until <strong>April 30th</strong>. As always, the event goes hand in hand with a second event which will be the EESTEC Congress 2013!\r\n\r\nOur department for Gender Studies will give an interactive four day seminar. Female students will learn how to use their voice, express themselves and prove themselves in a working environment. It is a fact that women earn less money, are treated worse and hold less important positions in a company. Often, these facts lead to prejudice against women and they don’t even try to stand up for themselves, seeing that “it is just as it is”. So all you girls, use your voice and <em>Speak Up!</em> Our seminar will show you how to grasp opportunities and broaden your prospects for your future working life. Besides, together with all the participants you should work out <em>your</em> personal road to success.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, there will be a womens’ contact forum during where you’ll have the opportunity to interact and exchange experiences with other women working in engineering jobs. On April 25th, you will get the chance to join the EESTEC OpenDay where you can establish contacts with representatives of companies or other sponsors and foreign universities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nApart from the lectures, we will introduce you to the lovely Bavarian capital, Munich. We look forward to showing you our Bavarian culture, Munich nightlife and our charming hospitality. The workshop will take place during the weeks of<em>spring festival </em>which is the “little sister” of our Oktoberfest and, of course, we don’t want you to miss this event either!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDo not hestitate and apply now! LC Awesome is waiting for you!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Note:</strong> <em>Evening activities are together with the Congress participants and you will also get the chance to get a glimpse on the Congress, nevertheless your main focus should be this workshop. This is an Exclusive Workshop and to ensure your motivation, we are taking into account your motivational letter. Following criterias will be assessed: Motivation, Progress of Studies, Level of English. The letter should consist of 500 to 1000 words.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>For question regarding WiE please contact andreas.albrecht(at)<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://fs.ei.tum.de\']);" href="http://fs.ei.tum.de" target="_blank">fs.ei.tum.<wbr />de</a>. </em>', 'Women in Engineering 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2223-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:59:12', '2013-11-21 23:59:12', '', 2223, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3836', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3837, 2, '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> 2 spoons of creativity,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> 1 cup of teamwork,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> 1 teaspoon of technology,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> 2 bottles of fun,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> 15 spirits of EESTECers</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Preheat your processors to 60-80 degrees C (140-176 degrees F). Lightly bend your screen for perfect sight. Open up some space in your hard disk.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Separate EESTECers into teams.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Load technology to the memory. Mix creativity, teamwork and fun. Bake in preheated processor for one week. Finally add some cheat.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Enjoy your game!</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">You have the recipe, you have the spirit. Just heat up your processors and mix up to the new workshop of LC Eskisehir! Our event, “Just Cheat It”, will be held between 16th – 23th March.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Subject of the event is video game development (especially mobile ones). You will be trained to obtain the necessary knowledge to make a mobile game from scratch. Lectures will cover both theoretical and practical parts of video game development. After the basics of game design is introduced theoretically, game programming using Unity3d game engine will be experienced practically.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">We will group you into teams to build your games, some art students from Anadolu University will also join to the teams in this phase. Then you will have time to develop your games in a relaxed development environment.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">While you are building your games in days, evenings are going to have awesome parties and activities to refresh you! Traditional EESTEC events like multi-culture night and city rally are planned for you to feel the spirit. As you will taste well-known Turkish tastes (rakı, baklava, kebab, Turkish delight) from its source, you will also reveal some more tastes which may still be secret to you like tantuni, simit, künefe…</span></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">If you want to have an highly productive week full of fun and EESTEC spirit, you are invited to Eskişehir!</span></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Oh and please don’t forget to mention about your programming background in your  application, it’s not strict but a basic knowledge in programming is preferable.</span></span>', 'Just Cheat It', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2224-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '', 2224, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3837', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3838, 2, '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '\n<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\n<p>Dear EESTECers<br />\nHave you ever wondered what Switzerland looks like? Have you ever wanted to experience the fascinating contrast between a busy banking hot spot and the calmness of the mountains not even an hour away from Zurich but don&#8217;t have the time to come here for the whole week? Or just looking for an amazing place to spend some time before the congress and get some good chocolate? EESTEC LC Zürich hereby invites you to its first international motivational weekend in the Swiss mountains!<br />\nArrivals will be on Thursday, so you will experience our legendary<strong> tramparty</strong> with the participants of our simultaneously happening workshop. On Friday, we will move to the mountains and have some <strong>fun activities</strong> and a <strong>Swiss night </strong>just to break the mountain night&#8217;s silence with a<strong> LC Zurich style surprise party</strong>. The next day you will also spend with lots of fun program, good food and finish the weekend with the <strong>amazing farewell party! </strong>Unforgettable moments are guaranteed!<br />\nAfter featuring the motivational weekend in our workshop last year for the first time, we decided to open it up to all of EESTEC. Why? Because you guys are just amazing and we want you to party with us! As travelling in Switzerland is pretty expensive, the participation fee will be relatively high. So this year, we have a strongly limited number of participation spots to evaluate the interest in an international motivational weekend in Zurich. In case of success (which we are convinced of) we will organize the weekend next year in a much bigger scale.  So, use this unique chance and apply, apply, APPLY! With your participation you will be part of the kick start to a whole new amazing EESTEC tradition!<br />\n<strong>The costs for the weekend will be published soon!</strong> We figure on around 120-150 Euros all incl.<br />\nSee ya soon in Zurich!<br />\n<em>PS: If needed, we will be able to accommodate you until the start of congress and organize your travel there (Munich is just about a 3 hour trip from Zurich).</em></p>\n</div>\n', 'IMW Zurich 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2226-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '', 2226, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3838', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3839, 2, '2013-11-22 00:02:29', '2013-11-22 00:02:29', 'Dear EESTECers\r\n\r\nNot too long ago, LC Zürich hosted an amazing pack of EESTECers to rebuild the famous smartphone game “Angry Birds” in real life. This made us put ourselves under a lot of pressure to make this year’s workshop even more memorable. After an intense decision making process, we are proud to announce the topic of our next workshop:\r\nIn <strong>“Slot Engines Xtreme”</strong> you will take a close look at the small but fascinating world of slot cars. In this workshop you will compete in small teams to <strong>build the fastest slot car</strong>. Slot cars? Well, we’re sure you were as fascinated by those mini racing cars – built by companies like Carrera – that went from 0 to infinite speed on a push of a button as we were – and still are!\r\n\r\nOf course, this comes with a nice package of<strong> racing performance and electrical engine theory</strong>. So you will not only have the chance to show off your creativity but also your engineering talent. How? You will spend most of your time building your own small electrical engine – the centerpiece of your mini racing car.\r\nIn the end, we will<strong> test your cars at their limit on a big public racing track</strong>. May the best engineers win!\r\n\r\nOf course, that’s not it – by far! As much as we appreciate a great academical part in our workshop we’re also known for some of the<strong> finest cultural activities in EESTEC</strong>. We don’t want to reveal the whole program already but here are some of the higlights:\r\n\r\nFor the first time ever, we will attend the <strong>“Sächsilüüte”</strong> in Zurich. It’s a spring tradition that, in today’s form, dates back to 1902. After a beautiful parade of the guilds of Zürich, the Böögg, a huge snowman spiked with firecrackers, will be burned on a huge bonfire. It is said that the time that passes from the start of the fire until the explosion of the Böögg’s head determines the weather of the summer…\r\n\r\nOther cultural activities include clubbing, our amazing city rally and of course the legendary<strong>tramparty</strong>. If this still isn’t enough EESTEC spirit for you, keep on reading!\r\n\r\nBecause we’re Swiss, we’re trying to plan your stay in Zurich as efficient and fun as possible. So, after a week of excitement and high level performance at both day and night, you will get the chance to relax and enjoy some fun activities on our motivational weekend in the Swiss mountains.\r\n\r\nThis and even more amazing experiences are waiting for you in Zurich! No previous knowledge is required but we do require you to be ready to<strong> have some serious fun </strong>and – what probably goes without saying at an EESTEC event – to be able go without much sleep for a week. If this sounds like you, <strong>welcome to Zurich</strong>! We’re excited to get your motivational letter!\r\n\r\n<em>PS: If you wish, we can organize the transportation to Munich for the congress after our workshop. Accommodation until congress will also be organized.\r\nAlso, we will happily<strong> accept unofficial participants</strong>. Please wait for the respective call after the application deadline.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Arrival Notes:</em></strong> For planning purposes, we want to inform you already about the following arrival/departure guidelines. The event is designed such as you should arrive before 12 o’clock on April 14th in Zurich and depart after 2 pm on April 21st from Zurich. Of course, we will be happy to host you some days before and/or after the event!', 'Slot Engines Xtreme', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2227-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:02:29', '2013-11-22 00:02:29', '', 2227, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3839', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3840, 2, '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '<span style="color: #1a1a1a;">Dear EESTECers,</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are proud to announce you a new workshop organised by <strong>LC Athens</strong>!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNowadays, that Internet has become part of our daily routine, more and more services are available through it. The governmental services cannot be an exception to this!\r\n\r\nTherefore, the topic of this workshop is <strong>e-governance</strong> and during the week the participants will get to know the use of e-governance services through lectures by experienced professors, visits to some Public Services and discussions with experts.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the workshop, participants will use all the acquired knowledge to analyze and present the needs and specifications of an <strong>e-voting system!</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDid you believe that’s all? Well of course not! The participants will have the chance to meet the beautiful city of Athens!\r\n\r\nThey will walk around the historical center, visit Acropolis and its magnificent museum! They will taste our delicious traditional Greek cuisine, drink ouzo and of course meet the never-ending nightlife of Athens! We assure you that Athens’ nightlife will more than satisfy you! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nThere will also be a Motivational Weekend from 15-17 March, in the beautiful and picturesque city of Trikala, which has the best e-governance system in Greece! For our participants, the expenses of this trip are covered by LC Athens.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnd last but not least, since our “Youth in Action” application was accepted, we are really pleased to announce you that about <strong>70% of the travelling expenses for each participant will be refunded</strong>! But the refund is only available for the following (J)LCs and Observers that sent us the Part3 documents:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Ankara, Banja Luka, Belgrade, Bucharest, Budapest, Eskisehir, Hamburg, Helsinki, Istanbul, Izmir, Krakow, Lille, Ljubljana, Madrid, Munich, Nis, Novi Sad, Riga, Sarajevo, Sheffield, Tallinn, Tampere, Trieste</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo what are you waiting for?\r\n\r\nApply and get ready to have the best travelling experience with us!\r\n\r\nSee you in Athens!  :)', 'Govern the Way of Youth', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2228-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '', 2228, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3840', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3841, 2, '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers;</p>\n<p>In cooperation with our  WiE (Women in Engineering) affinity group, we are proud to announce the second &#8220;WiE &#8211; Girls @Business Class-2&#8243; Workshop as LC Istanbul which will be held on 3 &#8211; 10 March 2013, in Istanbul, Turkey.</p>\n<p>In the light of mission of WiE, we will start the discussion the position of women in society and business life and their problems in working places, and, enterprising women in business. In addition to all these issues there are  many special  trainings that contribute our participants the development of their personal and career.</p>\n<p>Wait! We haven’t finished yet. Do you think that we’ve forgotten the best part of our event? We have to confess; making extraordinary parties, knocking around and make people crazy is more and more easy for us when you compare with the academic part : )) You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population ; however,  you ‘ll have an unforgettable 7 days without doubt. Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places and nightlife of course <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':-)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  This city has become the capital of 3 biggest empires of the history (Roman, Byzantium and Ottoman). So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and richness it includes. We are going to take you to Topkapi and Dolmabahce Palaces where the Ottoman Sultans resided, the Hagia Sophia Museum from the 6th century, the Blue Mosque, Basilica Cistern and some more surprise places. Participants will also have the chance to watch both Asian and European Part from the middle of the Bosphorus. And the awesome parties will be held in Istiklal Avenue which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see.</p>\n<p>In addition; to help you to know at least a little about;</p>\n<p>Istanbul, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Istanbul &#8211; 2010 European Capital of Culture</a> , <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iglYVm01RHU" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Istanbul Timeless City</a> and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Turkey</a></p>\n<p>For more feel free to contact us via <a href="mailto:Istanbul@eestec.net" target="_blank">Istanbul@eestec.net</a>. Don’t think too much, apply it!</p>\n', 'WiE &#8211; Girls @Business Class &#8211; 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2229-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '', 2229, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3841', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3842, 2, '2013-11-22 00:03:27', '2013-11-22 00:03:27', 'Dear Eestecers,\r\n\r\nAfter a long silent period, LC Istanbul is proud to announce the upcoming workshop ¨.COM (point of Creativity, Originality and Magnificence) which will be held on 3<sup>th</sup>- 10<sup>th</sup> of March in Istanbul.\r\n\r\nAfter writing has been invented in Mesopotamia by Sumerians, Internet has become the most important invention which will perhaps change the fate of world as writing has done. At that time those who had knowledge to use writing held much more power in society compared to others. Now everyone has knowledge about writing, all of us know how to write, don’t we? What about the Internet which stands at same position once writing had stood? Now those who know of language of Internet will have the same advantages like those who would have knowledge of writing. So we are ready to help you through this way. During the theoretical and practical lectures you’ll learn the twin brothers HTML and CSS (the things that make internet prettier) and also PHP by expert academicians and programmers. Of course we could not do it without the designing part of web programming.\r\n\r\nWait! We haven’t finished yet. Do you think that we’ve forgotten the best part of our event? We have to confess; making extraordinary parties, knocking around and making people crazy are much easier for us when it is compared to the academic part : )) You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population ( in fact no one knows how many people live in Istanbul <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":D" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" /> ) ; however,  you ‘ll have unforgettable seven days without being bored. Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places, night life and, of course crazy people <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":-)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" /> This city had once been the capital of the three biggest empires of the history. (Roman, Byzantium and Ottoman). So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and richness it includes. We are going to take you to Topkapi and Dolmabahce Palaces where the Ottoman Sultans used to reside, the Hagia Sophia Museum which was constructed in 6th century, the Blue Mosque, Basilica Cistern and some other surprising places. Participants will also have the chance of watching both Asian and European continents from the middle of Bosphorus. And the awesome parties will be held on Istiklal Avenue which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see. Can you imagine that three millions people walk on it just in one day?\r\n\r\nFor more information feel free to contact <a href="mailto:Istanbul@eestec.net" target="_blank">Istanbul@eestec.net</a>. Don’t think too much, apply it!', '.COM (point of Creativity, Originality and Magnificence)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2230-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:03:27', '2013-11-22 00:03:27', '', 2230, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3842', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3843, 2, '2013-11-22 00:03:52', '2013-11-22 00:03:52', 'After a long journey, you just arrived in Ankara. You try to call one of the organizers, but you noticed that battery is dead. Thanks to nanotechnology, you used extra efficient solar cells to charge your phone. Rushing for the party, you noticed that you dont have the most important protection tool with you <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" /> No no, I am talking about super hydrophobic spray. With its magical hydrophobic material property, if someone spills a beer or even vomits on your dress, it is no big deal – it will clean itself… Does it sound like Science-Fiction? The recent advancements in nanotechnology made it real: See the <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'download\',\'http://www.nanoteknoloji.tv/?File=MjAxMjAzMDctMDE1MC1raXJ0dXRtYXlhbmF5YWtrYWJpbGFyLmZsdg==&amp;id=109.\']);" href="http://www.nanoteknoloji.tv/?File=MjAxMjAzMDctMDE1MC1raXJ0dXRtYXlhbmF5YWtrYWJpbGFyLmZsdg==&amp;id=109." target="_blank">video</a>!\r\n\r\nLadies and gentlemen, we are proud to invite you to this small (10^-9 small) and amazing nanotechnology world. In this workshop, you will experience the world of nanotechnology including smart materials, nano bio-sensors and nano electro-mechanical systems not only by lectures but also field trips and tech talks.\r\n\r\nOf course this is not all! We all know that an event without the EESTEC traditions is unthinkable. Sightseeing, international night and parties are waiting for you! You will also experience the Turkish life; delicious Turkish cuisine, nargile (waterpipe), rakı, traditional Turkish night and many more… <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />  To sum up, LC Ankara is ready to host you once again!\r\n\r\nWe are also working really hard to arrange a country house in a mountain near Ankara, where you can enjoy the beautiful scene, and even ski. But we don’t promise this, yet!\r\n\r\nWe are waiting for your applications, what are you waiting for ? <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nSee you soon in the ‘halay’\r\n\r\no/o/o/o/o/o/o/o/\r\nI     I     I      I     I     I      I     I\r\n/  /  /   /   /   /   /  /', 'Shrink the World!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2231-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:03:52', '2013-11-22 00:03:52', '', 2231, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3843', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3844, 2, '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>As engineers, we like games. We actually love the challenges they demand us for winning them. Just recall the last time you discovered that so catchy one that almost drove you nuts because of the tangled rules you had to comprehend in order to focus on the strategies for conquering another level. Wasn’t it simpler if you could rather center your attention at the creative side of things than on the frustrating part of reinventing the wheel ?</p>\n<p>Like so in our engineering field. Technology evolves and so do we. New issues need new approaches, particularly straightforward ones. Here, at EESTEC LC Craiova, we use to mock our so frequently low on RAM laptops by advising their owners to water the faint hamster endlessly rolling the wheel J . Would you buy it if we threw on the market a snake that, as it does with living food, makes you readily eat the principles at once leaving your attention open on the so important side of quickly solving your tasks without worrying about those aforementioned tangled rules ?</p>\n<p>Then let the PYTHON byte you ! You’ll never have to worry about type declarations, semicolons or brackets. Just plain indentation. Getting rid of all that annoying clutter makes code clean and understandable for you and others. Easy life, on the short hand. Its name comes, as you might not think, from a movie, Guido van Rossum, who invented it in 1991, being inspired from &#8220;Monty Python&#8217;s Flying Circus&#8221;, a BBC comedy series from the 1970s.</p>\n<p>Become a PYTHONian ! Learn the basics and prepare for Twisted, Pyjamas, SQLAlchemy and many other toolkits and frameworks available for any of your platform independent scripting or programing needs, may it be web, databases or operating systems related. These might have funny names, but Python is so powerful that even Google and Facebook use it !</p>\n<p>Join our early spring trainings starting on 24th of March, lasting till 30th, reborn together with nature with all new programming skills, have fun with us coding the days and partying the nights along with our all around the world famous music and Romanian hospitality and wonder yourself why didn’t you come to this earlier.</p>\n<p>Discover PYTHONIA ! And your imagination gets code wings. *The only boring part is the “Hello, world!” one.</p>\n', 'Pythonia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2232-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '', 2232, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3844', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3845, 2, '2013-11-22 00:04:57', '2013-11-22 00:04:57', '<span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Hello dear EESTEC-ers, LC East Sarajevo is back! We are proud to present you “Jahorina Spring Break 2013″, unforgettable event that will take place from 19th to 26th of March 2013.\r\nAcademic part will be held on Jahorina (our Olympic mountain), where International Scientific Symposium – Infoteh 2013 will take place. You will have opportunity to listen lectures from the experts, scientists, engineers, researchers and students that deal with information technologies. We provided hotel accommodation for our participants, transport to Infoteh and back.</span>\r\n\r\nNon academic part will be quite hedonistic and relaxed, but full of various activities, such as swimming, bowling…or just lazy sitting in pub and drinking beer/coffee/juice/rakija/whatever…\r\nWe will also visit Orlovaca cave and beautiful well of Bosna river. Sightseeing and visiting city landmarks are also part of the program. During these 7 days you will taste our traditional food and drinks. We will organize traditional Serbian night with our live music, and people dressed in traditional Serbian clothes.\r\n\r\nAnd at the end, thing that you are waiting the most…….YES! Parties will be every night on various places!\r\n\r\nAs you could see, this is a life time opportunity. Millions of people would kill for it, so don’t hesitate to apply! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nSee you in East Sarajevo!<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><br clear="all" /> </span></span>', 'Jahorina Spring Break 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2233-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:04:57', '2013-11-22 00:04:57', '', 2233, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3845', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3846, 2, '2013-11-22 00:05:06', '2013-11-22 00:05:06', '\n<p>Hello dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>Have you ever wondered how green energy is made? Or especially bright and green solar energy? How does it work ? And why it’s the best alternative energy? How is it implemented in our nearby environment? If the answer is yes, yes and YES! Then it’s solar time in LC NOVI SAD!</p>\n<p>We will take you through the best journey of your green life.</p>\n<p>On the lectures, we are going to learn more about alternative energy and especially solar energy: how it is implemented, what technology is behind it and see it in use &#8211; generating clean Watts right on the spot, at our Faculty of Technical Sciences. The same group of people who created our small photovoltaic power plant CRESPQ, are the ones who will be holding the lectures for you.</p>\n<p>With all this in mind there&#8217;s nothing other left for you to do but to apply, hopefully start packing and get ready to soak up the Sun!</p>\n<p>Once you arrive, you will be welcomed to Novi Sad, a city that merges the north and the south, that unites the east with the west. Novi Sad (also known as: Нови Сад, Neoplanta, Neusatz, Újvidék, Nový Sad) has a rich history that dwells around our beautiful and world wide known Petrovaradin fortress overlooking the Danube.</p>\n<p>Check out these galleries to get to know YOUR future home city better:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DG7T1cQsJrI" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DG7T1cQsJrI</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.novisad.rs/eng/petrovaradin-fortress-7" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.novisad.rs\']);" target="_blank">http://www.novisad.rs/eng/petrovaradin-fortress-7</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.novisad.rs/eng/novi-sad-2" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.novisad.rs\']);" target="_blank">http://www.novisad.rs/eng/novi-sad-2</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.novisad.rs/eng/streets-novi-sad" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.novisad.rs\']);" target="_blank">http://www.novisad.rs/eng/streets-novi-sad</a></p>\n<p>But don’t think that&#8217;s all there is. Not only do we have a great history and picturesque streets, but also a rich and vibrant night scene, which you will discover along with fellow EESTECers, and patry hard until the sunrise!</p>\n<p>See you with the sunrise!</p>\n', 'It&#8217;s solar time!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2238-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:05:06', '2013-11-22 00:05:06', '', 2238, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3846', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3847, 2, '2013-11-22 00:05:38', '2013-11-22 00:05:38', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLet’s fast forward a little bit through the time, not very far in the future, but some where in the middle of December 2012.\r\n\r\nSuddenly you find yourself in a hotel room, with an open suitcase right in front of you. As you’re packing your bags and apparently getting ready to head home, you wonder yourself: “Why am I constantly smiling and feeling happy? And even though I am trying, I still can’t remove this distinct happy expression off my face…” Oh, it is simple, almost two months ago by joining the event “Code App, level up” by LC Skopje you made your best decision this year.\r\nOK, press the Stop button, let’s go back to the beginning, why did you click that APPly button!?\r\n\r\nThe almost radical growth of the world-wide smartphone community consequently affects the growth of need for mobile applications. These factors are opening new windows of possibilities for exploiting that market by the programmers from all around the world. That’s why LC Skopje is hosting a week of quality trainings and place where you will be able to implement your gained knowledge and creativity into practical work. “Code App, level up” is a workshop that through courses will bring you close to this programming field and will create a chance to code real applications for real clients. Level UP yourself!\r\n\r\nBut it’s not all about coding!(<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ltjT25GyXTM" target="_blank">?</a>) All of you PARTYcipants just prepare to get to know with  the famous Macedonian hospitality. By rallying our capital, the city of Skopje, you will experience the unique fusion of the West with the Orient. You will have taste of our <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CRgLmCQzEAo" target="_blank">extraordinary cuisine</a> and for sure you will enjoy the “Lozova Rakija” that will keep you warm in the long nights of December. But wait until you experience the rich nightlife Skopje is offering and you won’t be asking for anything else…\r\n\r\nSo all of you programmers on the EESTEC network, don’t hesitate, make your “future you” smiling like crazy on the 15<sup>th</sup> of December. <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" href="http://eestec.net/lc/skopje/code-app-level-up" target="_blank">Join a hell of a coding party</a>', 'Code App, level Up!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2234-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:05:38', '2013-11-22 00:05:38', '', 2234, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3847', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3848, 2, '2013-11-22 00:05:57', '2013-11-22 00:05:57', '\n<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Explo<span style="color: #ff0000;">RED </span>Planet</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Mission of workshop</span>: Finding out about space exploration with a spotlight on &#8220;Mars Science Laboratory&#8221;&#8230;</p>\n<div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br />\n</span></div>\n<div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="color: #222222;">Dear </span><strong><span style="color: #cc0000;">RED</span></strong><span style="color: #222222;"> people,</span></span></span><span style="color: #222222;">We are thrilled to announce that this workshop will be one giant leap for an eestec-kind in space exploration. The focus will be on the Red Planet and the latest mission related to it, which is called <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BudlaGh1A0o&amp;feature=plcp" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">&#8220;Mars Science Laboratory&#8221;</a>.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">The idea is to give you a closer look to the technological aspects of Curiosity rover which<a href="http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/mission/overview/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov\']);" target="_blank"> landed on Mars in August 2012</a>. Part of the lectures and practical part will be devoted to the study of this <a href="http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/mission/rover/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov\']);" target="_blank">rover</a> as a robot that operates in specific conditions. The main fields are the power and energy efficiency of the robot, the materials from which is made, how it is communicating with the base on the Earth and other telecommunications devices which is equipped with. You will also find out about history of space research and technology that made this possible. Therefore, this will be an exciting week for astronomy lovers and inquisitive engineers.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">As we never forget about eestec spirit, you will have enough time to discover all the beauties of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QJsvxsViG_k&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">our capital</a> and to get to know with its nightlife. Over here, every day is treated as Friday, in regard of fun. When you add theme parties which we are planing for you, then Belgrade is definitely <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OtQywygjdfc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">&#8220;the-place-to-be&#8221;</a> this winter. You will also have the chance to spend a few days out of the city and experience admirable landscapes and attractive nature in the country with reach legacy in history and art, among <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">abundant kitchen and warm hospitality</a>.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">Having so many things left for your amazement, we invite you to follow your curiosity and participate in this excellent workshop we are preparing for you.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">Sincerely,</span></p>\n</div>\n', 'ExploRED Planet', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2235-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:05:57', '2013-11-22 00:05:57', '', 2235, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3848', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3849, 2, '2013-11-22 00:06:24', '2013-11-22 00:06:24', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nwe are announcing our 4th International Motivational Weekend, happening between the 9th and 11th of November 2012.\r\n\r\nWe’re bringing the participants of our workshop »Bad cars gone electric 2« there as a conclusion to a great event and we’re going to have soft-skills trainings during the day, followed by even more awesome theme parties to keep us up till early morning.\r\n\r\nThe event includes accommodation, transport from Ljubljana, 3 meals a day and free theme parties. At the IMW we will be accompanied by members of other associations, so we definitely need all of you to join us and show them them our EESTEC spirit.\r\n\r\nThe venue is the same as last year and year before that, Kranjska Gora, where you can enjoy our beautiful countryside.\r\n\r\nAnd remember, the best way to participate at the IMW is to apply for our workshop!\r\n\r\nIf you are still in doubt about whether to come or not, ask anyone that has ever participated in an IMW to tell you about it.\r\n\r\nWe promise you won’t regret it for a second!\r\n\r\nSee you there!\r\n\r\nP.S. For more information regarding the event please contact <a href="mailto:demjan.vester@eestec-lj.org" target="_blank">demjan.vester@eestec-lj.org</a>', 'International Motivational Weekend 2012', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2236-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:06:24', '2013-11-22 00:06:24', '', 2236, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3849', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3850, 2, '2013-11-22 00:06:31', '2013-11-22 00:06:31', '<a href="http://bcge2.eestec-lj.org"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1742" title="Bad Cars Gone Electric 2" alt="" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/logo1.png" width="570" height="70" /></a>\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nyou may stop worrying now!\r\n\r\nLC Ljubljana is proud to announce this year’s workshop, a continuation of last year’s amazing electrically powered adventure. Yes, we’ve upgraded the concept and invite you to a more awesome, more sophisticated “<a href="http://bcge2.eestec-lj.org/" target="_blank">Bad Cars Gone Electric 2</a>”!\r\n\r\nWe invite you to join us from the 3rd (arrival day) to the 11th (departure day) of November 2012 for another unforgettable EESTEC experience brought to you by LC Ljubljana.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the topic?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe topic of the workshop will once more be electric cars, so we’re going to spend the week learning about how they work, general implementation into the current infrastructure, obstacles industries are facing for instance recycling, efficient energy usage, the batteries etc…\r\nWe’ll also talk about clean energy, specifically solar power, where some experts from both fields will explain the areas that the media sometimes doesn’t want to talk about. Is the field of clean energy a black/white or yes/no topic? Is there a “best” clean energy? Can any of them replace fossil fuel permanently and sustainably?\r\n\r\nBut lectures aren’t the only thing on the schedule. If the topic are electric cars, why not just make some of our own? Well we will!\r\nAbout half of the academic part will be spent building electric cars from scratch (But in a fun, relaxed and amusing way).\r\n\r\n<strong>What else is in it?</strong>\r\n\r\nDo you know what EESTEC Spirit is? What makes a true EESTECer?\r\n\r\nWell we do!\r\n\r\nAnd you get a wonderful opportunity to visit the very place we breed true EESTECers: <a href="http://bcge2.eestec-lj.org/city/" target="_blank">Ljubljana, our beautiful city</a>, where you will see what makes an EESTECer full of energy, tireless and awesome at all times!\r\n\r\nThere will also be a surprise trip in the middle of the workshop, where you will be able to relax and breathe in some fresh air.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is that all?</strong>\r\n\r\nIt’s still not over…\r\n\r\nWe don’t just end our events like that, we end them in style!\r\n\r\nSo you aren’t just coming to participate in our workshop, you are coming to participate at our International Motivational Weekend as well.\r\nTaking place the final weekend of the event, this is one of the largest EESTEC events organized each year, where we gather in the countryside to network, socialize and participate in soft-skills trainings.\r\n\r\nAll of this, free of charge for our participants!\r\n\r\nThere is really nothing more to add, except that places will fill up fast, and we have a limited amount…\r\n\r\nApply now!', 'Bad Cars Gone Electric 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2237-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:06:31', '2013-11-22 00:06:31', '', 2237, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3850', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3851, 2, '2013-11-22 00:06:50', '2013-11-22 00:06:50', '<strong>What is the EESTEC Training Team? What are Trainings?</strong>\r\n\r\nEESTEC Training Team is an official EESTEC body which is providing different services for EESTEC and through those services, based on trainings, constantly improving the work of EESTEC on international and local levels!\r\n\r\nMain goal of trainings is transfer of knowledge in an advanced way through different activities, techniques and methodologies.\r\n\r\nMore information about the Training Team, Training System and Trainings you can find in the Official Training Team Document <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" href="http://eestec.net/lc/workspaces/training-team/training-material/Training%20Team%20Official%20documents/1st%20Official%20Training%20Team%20Document.pdf/view?searchterm=training%20document" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is T4T? Why is T4T being organized?</strong>\r\n\r\nT4T – Training for Trainers is an international training event whose purpose is gaining new EESTEC trainers and it is the starting point for EESTECers to become a trainer.\r\n\r\nEESTECers which participate in T4T will go through intensive trainings, working sessions and practical parts and learn how to transfer knowledge, which methodologies to use and, very important, how to deliver trainings!\r\n\r\nAs the transfer of knowledge is crucial for EESTEC, T4T is an event which assures new generations to continue with developing and providing Training Team services to EESTEC members. It is a stage through all Training team members have to go in order to gain different soft skills like: leadership skills, presentation skills, communication skills and much more!\r\n\r\nUsing these skills for transferring knowledge in EESTEC provides greater quality of different activities which are being organized in International and local levels.\r\n\r\nDuring T4T, 9 days of a lot of work is waiting for you so you will need to bring <strong>a lot of positive energy</strong> and <strong>enthusiasm</strong> in order to be effective all the time and to be able to endure the T4T.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why become a Trainer? Why should you apply?</strong>\r\n\r\nThere are definitely a lot of reasons to apply. Becoming a trainer gives you an opportunity to contribute to EESTEC International, to contribute to LCs and to contribute to yourselves!\r\n\r\nAs a trainer candidate (and optionally trainer) you will work in and create a positive atmosphere during T4T and after. If you become a trainer (for what you need to fulfill certain tasks) you will work on the transfer of knowledge to other EESTECers and you will have an opportunity to improve on personal level in different aspects.\r\n\r\nThe skills you gain while being a trainer are needed in all aspects of life today and so in EESTEC. Because of that, members who participate in T4Thave a big opportunity to develop themselves and to give a great contribution to the development of EESTEC!\r\n\r\n<strong>Organizing Committee LC Istanbul</strong>\r\n\r\nLC Istanbul is very proud to organize such an important EESTEC international event – the 5th Training for Trainers!\r\n\r\nThis will be the first event of many for us in this academic year. So we are eagerly looking forward to offer the famous Turkish hospitality to our motivated participants and preparations are nearly complete to entertain you in this historical, amazing and spectacular city of İstanbul. Please don’t hesitate to apply!\r\n\r\nSee you in Istanbul, very soon <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nA Short Movie about city : <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://goo.gl\']);" href="http://goo.gl/Sl4RZ" target="_blank">http://goo.gl/Sl4RZ</a>\r\nApplication form: *** <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" href="http://eestec.net/publications/cp-area/forms/t4t-application-form" target="_blank">here</a> ***\r\nSend motivational letter to: <a href="mailto:trainings-coordinator@eestec.net" target="_blank">trainings-coordinator@eestec.net</a>', 'The 5th Training for Trainers – T4T', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2239-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:06:50', '2013-11-22 00:06:50', '', 2239, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3851', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3852, 2, '2013-11-22 00:06:59', '2013-11-22 00:06:59', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>We are proud to announce the 7th EESTEC Chairperson Meeting which will be held in <strong>Lisbon, Portugal from November 18th 2012 until 25th</strong>. The registration period is now open and so until the <strong>September 30th</strong>.<br />\nEach LC, JLC and Observer have a right for <strong>1 (one)</strong> place on ECM!</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>What is the main goal of this year’s ECM?</strong></span><br />\nInternational Board is focused on raising academic level in EESTEC, as well as improving communication between LCs. Based on this, main part of ECM will be educating members about International projects and the possibility for their contribution in these projects. Participants will have the chance to attend one or more sessions, where they can learn about projects and contribute to them. Sessions outcomes will be presented at the end of the ECM.</p>\n<p>Besides sessions, we will have soft skills trainings, where participants will have chance to improve their communication, project management and knowledge transfer in LCs.</p>\n<p>Based on the success of the General Meeting last ECM, International Board decided to have General Meeting this year. We will discuss about current Rules of Procedure, Board report and the progress of projects.</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>What will be done in ECM?</strong></span><br />\nWe will have the following sessions:<br />\n- FR session<br />\n- External cooperations<br />\n- Observer guidance session<br />\n- PR guide session<br />\n- Rules of Procedure session<br />\n- IT session<br />\n- Conference project session<br />\n- Design session<br />\n- Trainings</p>\n<p>Trainings that will be delivered on ECM are following:<br />\n- Project management<br />\n- Handover training<br />\n- Board training<br />\n- International awareness<br />\n- International FR training</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>What will be the profile of participants in ECM?</strong></span><br />\nConsidering the aim of this ECM and the fact that there should be one participant per LC, the chairperson should attend the ECM, however if it’s not possible for the chairperson to attend, one of the experienced member should take the delegation.<br />\nLC representation is of the highest importance as focus will be on the working sessions. JLC and Observer representations are also important, and for them focus will be on the training sessions.</p>\n<p>Important!!! Don’t miss the deadline for registration: <strong>30th of September! Link for registration</strong>: <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/lisbon/7th-eestec-chairpersons-meeting-lisbon" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/lisbon/7th-eestec-chairpersons-meeting-lisbon</a></p>\n<p>We cannot wait for your registration and we are eager to welcome you all in the beautiful city of Lisbon!</p>\n<p>Best regards on behalf of International Board and LC Lisbon!</p>\n', '7th EESTEC Chairperson Meeting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2240-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:06:59', '2013-11-22 00:06:59', '', 2240, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3852', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3853, 2, '2013-11-22 00:07:21', '2013-11-22 00:07:21', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>We were penguins last year and what about this one?</p>\n<p>Isn’t the time to expand our horizons and look in the sky? We think it is.:)</p>\n<p>So, after the last year exciting and successful workshop it is both our honor and a privilege to announce this year’s on topic of Inertial Navigation Systems or as we like to call it &#8211; <strong>INSoBLia</strong> (<strong>I</strong>nertial <strong>N</strong>avigation <strong>S</strong>ystems <strong>O</strong>ctober 2012<strong>B</strong>anja <strong>L</strong>uka <strong>I</strong>n <strong>A</strong>ir) <span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>from 21st until 27th October</strong></span>.</p>\n<p>First two days of lectures will cover the basics of flying from historical, technical and licensing point of view. Later on, we will get into serious technical details of the navigation systems that aircrafts are using. In the afternoons, we will be paying visits to the nearby airport, aero club and the helicopter service. By visiting these places, you will be able to see how theory is applied in practice.</p>\n<p>As always, one day in our beautiful city is reserved for exciting rafting on our beauty Vrbas where the European Championship 2005, Euro Cup 2007 and World Championship 2009 had been hosted.</p>\n<p>Already sounds interesting? Well, we are not done!</p>\n<p>The highlight of the week is your practical work in our laboratory for electronics. After attending lectures and hearing about inertial navigation systems, you will be able to make one! You&#8217;ll get to play around with accelerometers and microcontrollers, the actual components of an inertial navigation system. Of course, since the workshop focuses on the INS, it is required that you are already familiar with the basic concepts of a microcontroller and here is a site that could help: <a href="http://mucrofe.blogspot.com/2011/03/basic-concept.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://mucrofe.blogspot.com\']);" target="_blank">http://mucrofe.blogspot.com/2011/03/basic-concept.html</a>.</p>\n<p>Apart of the lectures, visits, and playing in laboratory, you’ll get to know our city, delicious and traditional meals and of course Banja Luka’s well known night life.</p>\n<p>Do not hesitate, apply now! <strong>LC Banja Luka is waiting for YOU!</strong></p>\n', 'INSoBLia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2241-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:07:21', '2013-11-22 00:07:21', '', 2241, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3853', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3854, 2, '2013-11-22 00:07:39', '2013-11-22 00:07:39', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Munich/Awesome is proud to announce the <strong>Oktoberfest Exchange</strong> 2012 from <strong>October 1st</strong> until <strong>October 7th</strong>.\r\nYou will have the honor of drinking the world’s finest beer in the world’s finest city with the most sophisticated soon-to-be engineers in Europe.\r\n\r\nBesides all these tempting facts we are also planning a cultural program, a City-Rally, sightseeing, and clubbing. There won’t be any lectures, however plenty of entertainment during your stay in Munich is guaranteed.\r\n\r\nSince hostel prices are ridiculous during Oktoberfest, we will be accommodating you privately. Unfortunately we have to ask for a <strong>participation fee of 100€</strong>. This includes meals, local transportation and some entry fees. We have to warn you though, Munich is generally an expensive place during Oktoberfest. A liter of beer is<strong> 9.10€ to 9.50€</strong>! But as usual, everything except for drinks is included for our participants. No need to worry, we will not be spending the entire week at Oktoberfest itself, and you will have a lot of chances to get cheaper beer! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\n<strong>This is a once in a lifetime chance to experience Oktoberfest at such affordable prices!</strong>\r\n\r\nAgain, this is the opportunity of your life to enjoy the world’s biggest beer festival (and party) with your fellow EESTECers! We strongly encourage you to apply! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nP.S. Loving beer is a must <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nSee you in Munich,', 'Oktoberfest Exchange 2012', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2243-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:07:39', '2013-11-22 00:07:39', '', 2243, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3854', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3855, 2, '2013-11-22 00:08:29', '2013-11-22 00:08:29', '\n<p>Dear EESTEC-ers,</p>\n<p>We can proudly invite you to our traditional event <span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>“JAZZ DO IT!”</strong></span> . Since it was great all years before, we&#8217;re making it again! That&#8217;s why we are asking you to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and Eastern Europe <strong><a href="http://www.nisville.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.nisville.com\']);" target="_blank">&#8220;Nišville jazz festival&#8221;</a></strong>. Together we will enjoy the good jazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchange can provide. Organized in the medieval <a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://img704.imageshack.us\']);" target="_blank">fortress</a> and visited by more than <strong>100.000 people</strong> only last year, Nišville hosted some of the biggest stars of jazz music: Steve Hans and Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke, Benny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell&#8230; This year there is no exception because Lollo Meier Quartet, Get The Blessing, Tacuma &amp; Joseph Bowie Defunkt Funk Expirience, Opus 5, Maria Joao, David Linx, Brussels Jazz Orchestra and 50 other bands on 5 different stages will jazz it up for us!</p>\n<p>Regular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you are getting it for <strong>free</strong> <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>And you will also learn some things about acoustics and making music.</p>\n<p>But, that’s not all. The City of Niš has great cultural and historical heritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most important persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Niš (roman name <strong>NAISSUS</strong>) in 272AD.</p>\n<p>You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niš_Fortress" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Fortress of Niš</a>, where “Nišville jazz festival” takes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. That’s because Niš is on the road that connects Europe with Middle East (in roman times this road was called VIA MILITARIS), so many civilizations passed here and they left some trace in the fortress. It’s in this condition since XVII century, and now it’s one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe.</p>\n<p>In Niš exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was built from skulls of the warriors who died in the Čegar battle in the 1809. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Čegar" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Čegar monument</a> where this battle took place.</p>\n<p>We’ll show you one relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.nistourism.org.rs\']);" target="_blank">Niška Banja</a> spa which has radioactive healing water and we’ll go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!</p>\n<p>And if you think that we only have history, you’re wrong, because Niš is known as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old hedonist legacy! Are you brave enough to try our traditional drink <strong>rakija</strong>? And the best BBQ in the world including pljeskavica will help your body to work well with all that alcohol. There won’t be a single moment that you’ll be hungry, because Serbians like good food in big quantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient at the special night in <strong>kafana</strong>. If you don’t know what <strong>merak</strong> is (that word has no translation to other languages), you will learn here!</p>\n<p>So the crazy summer cocktail with&#8230; traditional Serbian drinks and food… plenty of great music… nice town… a lot of EESTEC spirit… Mix all that in a summer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?</p>\n<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">JAZZ DO IT!</span></strong></p>\n', 'Jazz do it! 2012', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2244-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:08:29', '2013-11-22 00:08:29', '', 2244, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3855', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3856, 2, '2013-11-22 00:08:39', '2013-11-22 00:08:39', 'We promise to offer you the best Summer School ever, if you are brave enough to risk spending a week in summer LEARNING! EESTECers will have the opportunity to attend a high quality academic event combined with the awesome EESTEC Spirit. You will have the chance to get in touch with top expertise speakers and participants.\r\n\r\nThe School will have two main topics: <strong>“Graphic Design and Web development”</strong>, each with its own classes schedule. In addition there will also be a common schedule, to let participants work in <strong>teams</strong> and be involved in innovative and constructive challenges.\r\n\r\nWe are also planning a competition between teams of 5, picked randomly from both designers and developers. The winning team <strong>will of course be awarded</strong>… <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";-)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nOn Saturday you will all attend a very special photography class… No more details … it is a surprise!\r\n\r\nWe will work hard, but we will have fun too! No worries about this…you will be in Italy, DON’T FORGET IT!\r\n\r\nFor more details visit our website <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://ts.eestec.it\']);" href="http://ts.eestec.it/ess/" target="_blank">http://ts.eestec.it/ess/</a>\r\n\r\nPresentation event: <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://ts.eestec.it\']);" href="http://ts.eestec.it/ess/eestec-summer-school-presentation/" target="_blank">http://ts.eestec.it/ess/eestec-summer-school-presentation/</a>\r\n\r\nSummer School program: <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://ts.eestec.it\']);" href="http://ts.eestec.it/ess/ess-program/" target="_blank">http://ts.eestec.it/ess/ess-program/</a>\r\n\r\nWe hope to see you all in Trieste! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nGreetings from LC Trieste!', '1st EESTEC Summer School 2012 “Graphic Design & Web Development”', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2245-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:08:39', '2013-11-22 00:08:39', '', 2245, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3856', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3857, 2, '2013-11-22 00:10:18', '2013-11-22 00:10:18', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Last summer, we moved some boundaries of EESTEC events and we made one epic event. But this summer be prepared for more&#8230;.double the action, triple the excitement&#8230; and more of the excitement&#8230;be prepared to <strong>Cross the Line</strong> with LC Podgorica.</p>\n<p>We offer you 7 days of unforgettable atmosphere, 7 days of EESTEC spirit, 7 days and seven nights of our parties and memories for a lifetime.</p>\n<p>We will spend 7 days in Kotor, one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast (UNESCO protected) . You will be able to experience Mediterranean spirit, see one of the most beautiful bays in Europe during the cruise that we will organize around Boka bay. But the most important thing is the Kotor Carnival, one of the biggest and craziest carnivals in Europe. We plan to appear as a group mask, and the theme of our mask is secret for now <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  .</p>\n<p>This event will also have an educational part. Considering that you are probably tired of engineering, we decided to make a workshop on photography, journalism and filmmaking. You will be able to choose one of those three and show your creativity. Beside of this we will organize workshop where we will design our performance for carnival.</p>\n<p>Priority will be given to those who write a motivation letter, or those who make a motivational video and show us EESTEC spirit, good energy and creativity. Also if you have some special talents or motivation your are more than welcome to express them and you will get bonus points for that.</p>\n<p><strong>Important notice</strong></p>\n<p>If you want an ordinary summer or you consider yourself as non creative or boring person, <strong>DO NOT APPLY</strong> for this event <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Cross the line', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2246-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:10:18', '2013-11-22 00:10:18', '', 2246, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3857', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3858, 2, '2013-11-22 00:10:41', '2013-11-22 00:10:41', '\n<p>Let me ask you this, you want to go on a vacation this summer but you’re still wondering where? Let me tell you this, it is not late, it is the best time for wondering.</p>\n<p>An idea pops out in your head, having an EESTEC vacation?!?<br />\nYou are scratching your head saying naah, where would you find that kind of thing? Those guys rock and those ladies jazz. That would be awesome, but is there something like EESTEC vacation?!?</p>\n<p>Well guess what, there is!<br />\nBring on your spirit and become a fellow EESTECer with that wild crew from LC Skopje. Have the summer of your life, while round trippin’ their country.<br />\nAnd you know what you are already accepted; because this is not exchange, it&#8217;s a vacation, everybody is accepted. We provide all the logistics and planning of this awesome vacation, but we can not provide the accommodation and the food.</p>\n<p>Our plan is to show you our country, every day different dish, every day different club, every day different kafana, every day different breathtaking sights. We will visit 5 cities that will show you why do we love to live here, and reminding you that when the day ends the games may begin!</p>\n<p>The trip goes like this &#8211; 2 days in Skopje, 2 days on Tikves Lake (with one stop on the way in the town called Veles to eat tasty pastrmajlija (the grandma of the Italian pizza)), 1 day in Bitola and 5 days in Ohrid. During this holiday will be touring you showing off with our nature, being proud of our history, architecture and culture all in all days to remember, and nights even more or not. We will be visiting (the schedule is in the link below):</p>\n<p>Skopje:</p>\n<p>The Old Bazar, this is something, time-travel to the middle ages in our Charshija:<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6</a></p>\n<p>The Biggest Cross in the world on the top of mount Vodno. Have a cup of coffee on the top of the mountain with a view of the whole Skopje area. Also the biggest statue of Alexander the Great in the world and its fountain below:<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cyj3brd" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cyj3brd</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/d3k9fdd" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/d3k9fdd</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/c2zgx9t" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/c2zgx9t</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cq4toh6" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cq4toh6</a></p>\n<p>Bitola (also known as the city of the consuls):<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/d87ywkt" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/d87ywkt</a></p>\n<p>Heraklea (antient Roman city):<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cxv9lw5" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cxv9lw5</a></p>\n<p>Tikves Lake where we will be spending 2 days in the famous wine region and enjoy the beautiful nature(motivational weekend of the holiday) :<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cfovnzr" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cfovnzr</a></p>\n<p>Ohrid &#8211; the pearl of the Balkan (the pictures are enough to show you the beauty of the town):<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/bm87nuh" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/bm87nuh</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/c8f6fm8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/c8f6fm8</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/d3xj7eu" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/d3xj7eu</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cwh96uc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cwh96uc</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/buvxfvx" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/buvxfvx</a> (pictures from Feel the Energy 2, when we spend 3 days in Ohrid)</p>\n<p>Because this is a holiday, we can alternate the plan, but be fast, apply and tell us your suggestion. The maximum amount of money that we estimate that you will need to bring with you and enjoy to the max, from the moment you enter our country, to the moment you exit is 350 euros (here we calculated the food, accommodation, traveling expenses, alcohol). But that is maximum, that is why we provided the price list for the common expenses (in the link bellow).</p>\n<p>You can find the schedule and the price list on the following link:<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFZEemNTLUJvQm9zVkFCVnZQY0g4b2c&amp;pli=1#gid=0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://docs.google.com\']);" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFZEemNTLUJvQm9zVkFCVnZQY0g4b2c&amp;pli=1#gid=0</a></p>\n<p>Put your application on the following link:<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc6MQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://docs.google.com\']);" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc6MQ</a></p>\n<p>You can see the other participants in real time (wow real-time?!?) here:<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://docs.google.com\']);" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc</a></p>\n<p>Facebook Group:<br />\n<a href="http://www.facebook.com/groups/383347785033668/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.facebook.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/groups/383347785033668/</a></p>\n<p>Facebook Event:<br />\n<a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/294062514017607/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.facebook.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/events/294062514017607/</a></p>\n<p>You can send us as many questions you have, you can spam us, and bore us to death with suggestions on this mail:<br />\n<a href="mailto:contact@eestec-sk.org.mk" target="_blank">contact@eestec-sk.org.mk</a></p>\n<p>You are still here? Go to that Google doc and put your name in the list of the lovely people!</p>\n', 'EESTECers gone wild', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2247-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:10:41', '2013-11-22 00:10:41', '', 2247, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3858', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3859, 2, '2013-11-22 00:10:56', '2013-11-22 00:10:56', '\n<p>The most exciting summer exchange for 2012 is finally here!</p>\n<p>LC Athens is taking you to the second largest city in Greece, Thessaloniki, also known as the queen of the North! Who hasn&#8217;t heard of one of the best party cities worldwide, that combines the ancient with the new! The White Tower, the roman forum, the famous delicious pastries (it is impossible to leave the city without visiting its bakeries!) , the relaxed way of living of its people, even a walk down the seaside promenade are only some of the city&#8217;s treasures&#8230;</p>\n<p>Also, we have planned a day trip to the site of Vergina, the burial site of the kings of Macedon including Philip II, and also to Edessa, a town that&#8217;s famous for the waterfalls and the amazing scenery it provides.</p>\n<p>But that doesn&#8217;t stop there! Our participants will get the chance to attend our International Motivational Weekend (yes, you read correctly!) with no charge, taking place during the last 3 days of our exchange in Chalkidiki!<br />\nGet ready for camping, endless sun, parties&#8230; Get ready to GREECE U UP!!</p>\n', 'Greece Me Up', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2248-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:10:56', '2013-11-22 00:10:56', '', 2248, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3859', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3860, 2, '2013-11-22 00:11:09', '2013-11-22 00:11:09', '\n<p><strong>Dear EESTECers</strong></p>\n<p>Ever interested in what <strong>Plone</strong> has to offer? Ever wanted to learn more about a technology that could mean well paid work and tons of contacts? Here&#8217;s your opportunity! Moreover, there will be experienced members of the International EESTEC IT Team that can teach you how to get involved in the team to put all this new knowledge into action, with the best mentors to guide you. Are you a professional coder? Have you never touched a programming language before? Everyone interested in contributing is welcome! All you need is a laptop and a UTP cable since this is an advanced skills workshop.</p>\n<p>Interested in helping out the EESTEC IT team? You want to improve <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> but you just don&#8217;t know how to? This is your chance! JLC Antwerp organizes an ITT event as its first event in cooperation with Plone, the powerful and flexible system powering <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>. During this event, you will have the opportunity to learn about the system from professional developers and contribute both to EESTEC IT projects and even to the plone system itself. You can also work on other EESTEC IT projects such as Lykeion, we provide the infrastructure for a week of IT activity.</p>\n<p>Of course we will also provide the relaxation after the coding, and show you the beautiful city of Antwerp! The largest city of Belgium, featuring nice places such as the &#8220;Groenplaats&#8221;, the &#8220;Meir&#8221;, the &#8220;Keyserlei&#8221;, and a cathedral. Additionally we have a harbor, French fries (lots), traffic, a river, the tallest building in Belgium, waffles, chocolate, and much more. You will also see the University of Antwerp and it&#8217;s happy students. Additionally, we will also introduce you to Belgian beer and &#8220;cantus&#8221; which is a traditional student singing night.<br />\n<strong>Extra requirements</strong>: basic programming experience, preferably in object-oriented programming. The aim of the workshop is to introduce participants to Plone, so no previous Plone/Zope knowledge is required. However, it is necessary to have basic programming notions to fully understand all the sessions during this workshop, which include parts with code examples.<br />\nTo check those requirements are fulfilled, all applicants must fill the following form after applying through the website: <a href="http://eestec.net/workspaces/board/it-workshop/view" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/workspaces/board/it-workshop/view</a>. This form will serve as a standardized CV to measure your skills.<br />\nIn addition to the CV, a motivational letter is also required and can be written in the application form in <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>.</p>\n<p>As for the extra requirements: <strong>don’t worry, we are not looking for professional programmers!</strong> We just want to ensure the quality of the event by setting a minimum level of IT knowledge. All sessions will be easy to understand, and will be adapted to the level of the final participants.</p>\n<p><strong>Don’t let this requirement keep you from applying!</strong> Even if you think you don’t have enough experience, give it a try. In the end we will judge whether that’s true or not. The most important thing is being motivated and wanting to learn.</p>\n<p>EESTECers can apply through the system, if you are a Plone professional, contact Joni Orponen.</p>\n', 'IT Workshop', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2249-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:11:09', '2013-11-22 00:11:09', '', 2249, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3860', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3861, 2, '2013-11-22 00:11:22', '2013-11-22 00:11:22', '\n<p>It&#8217;s time for the <strong>second Grant Team Operational Conference (GToc)</strong>, which is an operational event for educating the new EESTEC Grant Team members!<br />\nSince the Congress in 2011, when GT became an official EESTEC Body, through months of hard work, the results have been very successful. In order to expand, the GT needs motivated people from various LCs that want to get involved in the rather difficult, yet very promising area of grants.</p>\n<p>During this event, participants will get familiar with the grants that EESTEC can benefit from, be introduced to the concept of grants and the technical details around them, and they will also be given the opportunity to join Grant Team as junior members, since GToc is the only way one can become official member of the GT.</p>\n<p>But let&#8217;s not forget about the place where GToc will be held! The beautiful city of Athens awaits you!<br />\nLC Athens will host the event and show everyone how Athens is great during the day and night! Sightseeing in our beautiful historical centre, the Acropolis and its brand new museum, places where you can taste traditional greek dishes and enjoy greek hospitality, and of course night parties (because Athens nightlife is something worth finding out <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  ). During the weekend, we will have the chance to visit a beautiful island called Aigina, in order for the participants to regain their strength.</p>\n<p>So, if you&#8217;re interested in getting involved with the Grant Team, make sure you apply <strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">before May 20th</span></strong>, along with a <strong>motivational letter</strong> with any past experience you have with grants and the reasons for your interest in the GT.<br />\nThe selection of the participants will be made by both the Int. Board and the Grant Team, in order to ensure the proper continuation of the GT.</p>\n<p>Last but really not least, we&#8217;re really pleased that our application for the <strong>&#8221;Youth in Action&#8221;</strong> programme was accepted, so about <strong>70% of the travelling expenses will be refunded!!</strong> So, this goes for the following LCs that sent us a Part3 document: Ankara, Banja Luka, Belgrade, Bucharest, Budapest, Delft, Eskisehir, Krakow, Ljubljana, Lille, Madrid, Nis, Novi Sad, Podgorica, Trieste, Zagreb, Zurich.</p>\n<p>See you in sunny Athens! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', '2nd Grant Team Operational Conference', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2250-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:11:22', '2013-11-22 00:11:22', '', 2250, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3861', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3862, 2, '2013-11-22 00:11:47', '2013-11-22 00:11:47', '\n<p><strong>Dear EESTECers,</strong><br />\nLet us invite you to the Advanced Skills Workshop (a new terminology in EESTEC since this year’s Congress) organized by LC Budapest this summer, called TANDEM.</p>\n<p><strong>Technology and Design in Motion</strong> (TANDEM) is an 8 days long workshop held in Hungary between the 19th and 27th of June that <strong>brings together students with different backgrounds</strong> to discover the use of <strong>Kinect</strong> and brainstorm on projects using <strong>Natural User Interfaces</strong> (NUI), with an emphasis on <strong>bringing new ideas to life</strong>. The participants will include 20 motivated EESTECers from all over Europe and 10 Design and Arts students from a number of high-profile universities in Hungary. You will have to work together in teams during the whole week, which not only gives you a unique chance to experience completely different work styles, but also creates an inspiring environment and fosters you to think outside of the box.</p>\n<p>During the workshop we will introduce you the necessary technical knowledge to use the Kinect, give introductory lectures to the Designers about programming in general and also invite experts to give inspirational talks. After this you’ll form mixed teams, choose a problem that you’d like to work on, and yes, you’ll actually implement a working prototype of your solution as well!</p>\n<p>But did you really think working is all that we care about? 30 youngsters in a city with a <strong>unique atmosphere and unmatched nightlife</strong> under the supervision of our superb LC guarantees those sleepless nights you’re dreaming of. We believe Budapest is also <strong>one of the most beautiful capitals in Europe</strong> and we’ll do our best to show you as many faces of it as we can. We’ll also take you to our beloved <strong>Lake Balaton</strong> to get tanned and include a few adventure and sports programs to energize you even more. Not trusting us would probably be the biggest mistake you could make, so we really hope to see you in Budapest <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>So, who should apply? We’re looking for people with <strong>some experience in programming</strong> (preferably Java or C#, but this is not a strict requirement) and <strong>enough motivation to do some real work</strong> during the day instead of just sleeping at the lectures. This does not mean however that we miss any of the traditional EESTEC values &#8211; <strong>awesome parties, cool people, laying on the beach, a city rally, a few free rounds and some surprises</strong> are all important aspects of the event <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>In order to apply please use the <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> site as you always do <strong>AND</strong> fill in <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/budapest/test/tandem" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">THIS INTERNAL FORM</a> as well! It’s a little bit longer, but not as long as it looks at first sight, and not difficult at all, so go ahead, give it 20 minutes so that we can host you on this one-of-a-kind event <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Looking forward to seeing you here,</p>\n<p><strong>The Extremely Enthusiastic OC</strong></p>\n', 'Technology and Design in Motion ASWS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2251-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:11:47', '2013-11-22 00:11:47', '', 2251, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3862', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3863, 2, '2013-11-22 00:12:09', '2013-11-22 00:12:09', '\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>LC Sarajevo is organizing an exchange from 30th April to 6th May &#8220;High5 for LC Sarajevo!&#8221; and during it we invite all of you who are not participants of our exchange to join us on our birthday weekend (4th and 5th May). Our LC is celebrating 5 years of its existence, and we are doing our best to make this week more memorable than any event that you have ever participated before and with your appearance we are sure we will succeed! This is an awesome opportunity to explore Bosnia and Herzegovina and its rich cultural background, especially the city of Sarajevo, to make new acquaintances, share EESTEC spirit and have an unforgettable time! We invite you to participate in our birthday ceremony which we proudly make for our honorable guests, EESTECers, professors and students!</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As you could see before, LC Sarajevo is organizing an exchange from 30th April to 6th May and it goes by the name &#8220;High5 for LC Sarajevo&#8221;! Our LC is celebrating 5 years of its existence, and you should consider it to be a great reason for a big FIESTA <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We are doing our best to make this week more memorable than any event that you have ever participated before and with your appearance we are sure we will succeed! This is an awesome opportunity to explore Bosnia and Herzegovina and its rich cultural background, especially the city of Sarajevo, to make new acquaintances, share EESTEC spirit and have an unforgettable time! Oh, who am I kidding&#8230;We are going to make the best parties and we will offer you fascinating experiences!!! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Here are some videos which can show you even more <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9Imf56AJn0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9Imf56AJn0</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As for the informal part, you can expect lots of different parties at various locations, interesting activities during the day and hopefully, you can get the picture of our way of living and tradition. All of you should feel like home during the visit because Bosnian people proved to be extremely friendly and helpful. Besides all of this one thing is certain, you will not get enough sleep <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Also, on behalf of the LC Sarajevo, we invite you to participate in our formal ceremony which we proudly make for our honorable guests,EESTECers, professors and students!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For participation fee of only <strong>20 €</strong> you will have next things included:</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">· accommodation for two nights, 4th and 5th of May</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">· breakfast included for two days</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">· birthday dinner party (dinner &amp; one drink)</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">· free drinks on farewell party <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For those who want to come to Sarajevo earlier it&#8217;s additional 10 € per night (breakfast included).</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We invite you all to be our guests and make our birthday celebration more special with your presence <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Deadline for application is <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>April 10th</strong></span>, so don&#8217;t hesitate. We want you! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For any questions feel free to contact:</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="mailto:elmica.bh@gmail.com" target="_blank">elmica.bh@gmail.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">See you all soon <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'LC Sarajevo&#8217;s 5th Birthday', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2252-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:12:09', '2013-11-22 00:12:09', '', 2252, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3863', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3864, 2, '2013-11-22 00:12:33', '2013-11-22 00:12:33', '\n<p><img class="alignleft" title="Manage your Project" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-prn1/532483_342471049141109_339478169440397_821007_1848878874_n.jpg" alt="" width="206" height="170" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">LC COSENZA is proud to announce you our next Workshop, “Manage your Project, Manage your Future”. It will be held from 7th to 14th May, 18 participants.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You can have good knowledge in your engineer field, but do you know how to work in a team? How to behave in project work? How to coordinate the work of more people? How to respect deadline? How to spend less money and time?</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This year we will focus on Project Management. It is the science and art to implement successfully projects. It is a science because it is based on techniques and methodologies to follow, and is considered an art because it is necessary to have different skills and know how. It is important because it allows to address any project in an effective, structured and repeatable.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In our workshop we will:</p>\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\n<li>Explain the fundamentals of Project Management, a topic of great relevance for all those organizations who see the &#8220;project management&#8221; as an important tool for change and innovation;</li>\n<li>Provide information on basic skills that project managers and their team should have for the exercise of its functions;</li>\n<li>Identify the &#8220;soft skills&#8221; to manage a team and exercise their leadership;</li>\n<li>Provide information on the major certification programs exist</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Furthermore, you will be offered our warm Italian hospitality as well as funny times and parties.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Are you still waiting to apply? LC COSENZA is ready for you!!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yr8L5CU_iXk&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;a" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yr8L5CU_iXk&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;a</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fprezi.com%2Fcotp6dhgxrrw%2Fmanageyourproject%2F&amp;h=NAQEXp90R" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.facebook.com\']);" target="_blank">http://prezi.com/cotp6dhgxrrw/manageyourproject/</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Apply via eestec.net with your motivational letter before the deadline!!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.asiunical.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.asiunical.org\']);" target="_blank">More information about this event…</a></p>\n', 'Manage your Project, Manage your Future', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2253-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:12:33', '2013-11-22 00:12:33', '', 2253, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3864', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3865, 2, '2013-11-22 00:12:40', '2013-11-22 00:12:40', '\n<p><strong>Study tour which is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Krakow is organizing a workshop entitled &#8220;Smart energy for a better world&#8217; in cooperation with ABB Corporate Research Centre which will be held in Krakow from 8th till 15th of July 2012. This study tour is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science. The event will be a unique opportunity to visit one of the most advanced ABB Research Centers in the world and to broaden your knowledge on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Advanced numerical simulations</li>\n<li>Power electronics</li>\n<li>Transients phenomena</li>\n<li>Smart Protection</li>\n<li>Advanced diagnostics</li>\n<li>Ferroresonance phenomena</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All students from European Universities are invited to join us at the ABB Corporate Research Center situated in Krakow, one of Poland&#8217;s most renown cities. This event will be a great occasion to meet experts on energy, electrical sciences and to visit Poland&#8217;s well-known tourist attractions.</p>\n<p>We are waiting for applications from students who have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>electrical engineering profile</li>\n<li>good academic results</li>\n<li>good command of English</li>\n<li>completed at least 3 years of university education</li>\n</ul>\n<p>More information about the lectures and lab excercises can be found on the website of the event <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/workshops.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://smart.eestec.pl\']);" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Apart from educational part of the event, you will have also a chance to see Krakow, the center of cultural and artistic life and one of the biggest cities in Poland. To be more specific you will visit:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the Wawel Royal Castle &#8211; located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;</li>\n<li>the Underground of the City’s Main Market Square – unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are also a laser tag’s competition, football game, barbecue, unforgettable parties every night planned and many others activities to keep you busy for the whole week, but we do not want to reveal all of the attractions now. You have to come to Krakow and see for yourself <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>How to apply:<br />\n1. EESTEC members: via eestec.net, where you should write down your motivational letter and send to me your CV (my email address: <a href="mailto:skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com" target="_blank">skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com</a>)<br />\n2. Non-EESTECers: via website: <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://smart.eestec.pl\']);" target="_blank">smart.eestec.pl</a></p>\n<p>If you have any question, please do not hesitate to ask me: <a href="mailto:skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com" target="_blank">skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com</a>.<br />\nThe website of the event: <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://smart.eestec.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://smart.eestec.pl</a></p>\n<p>Hope to see you in Krakow! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p><a href="http://smart.eestec.pl" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://smart.eestec.pl\']);" target="_blank">More information about this event…</a></p>\n', 'Smart energy for a better world', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2254-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:12:40', '2013-11-22 00:12:40', '', 2254, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3865', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3866, 2, '2013-11-22 00:13:08', '2013-11-22 00:13:08', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>If you have never been to Zagreb, shame on you! You must have heard that our events are just awesome and here is another one to prove that is true! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>The opportunity to apply for our event and come to Zagreb is finally here. Just in case you need more convincing to come (even though I doubt it), read the rest of our invitation!</p>\n<p><strong>Special Note!! No motivational letters needed, but advantage goes to people who send motivational pictures! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We want to SEE why you want to come to our workshop so be creative! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </strong></p>\n<p>This year&#8217;s theme will be <strong>&#8220;Risky business&#8221;</strong> and as you can guess from the name, the event is based on learning about risk management. You will have several very interesting classes held by professors from our faculty and visiting lecturers. But that is not all! If you apply now, you will get a set of knives free of charge! What?? No, you won’t. You will get classes consisted of case studies and the opportunity to apply the acquired knowledge on practical examples. That’s more useful than a set of knives! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p><em>What else we&#8217;ve got you&#8217;re wondering?</em><br />\nOK, if you haven&#8217;t heard about wonderful Croatian nature you are really missing a lot! Google it and look at the pictures&#8230;[5 minutes later] You must be interested now! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We will show you some beautiful sights and that is not all, &#8217;cause you also get to experience the Croatian culture and not to mention our awesome food and drinks!</p>\n<p>Let me repeat that again – experience the culture and our awesome food and drinks! Get it? <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>You will definitely not leave hungry or thirsty (except if you eat or drink really really really lot), but you will be eager to come back to taste Croatia again… <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p><em>You&#8217;re asking yourselves what about the real memorable having fun part which everyone forgets because of too much…hmmm ….too much what? <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </em><br />\nNow that&#8217;s our strongest card, so don&#8217;t come tired or wanting to rest, we are not going to allow that! <strong>You ARE going to party every day and it IS going to be legen&#8230;&#8230;..dary! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </strong></p>\n<p>In the end, it doesn&#8217;t matter where we take you because we will make your time here unforgettable.</p>\n<p>Need more convincing? You really are hard to get! Just contact us on <a href="mailto:cp@eestec-zg.hr" target="_blank">cp@eestec-zg.hr</a> for any other information!</p>\n<p>So come and meet us! We prepared a great week for you, guaranteed!</p>\n<p>And remember, wine is fine but whiskey is quicker!</p>\n<p>LC Zagreb <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Risky Business', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2255-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:13:08', '2013-11-22 00:13:08', '', 2255, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3866', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3867, 2, '2013-11-22 00:13:14', '2013-11-22 00:13:14', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nZurich is back with a new event. ARE YOU READY?\r\n\r\nDo you like fun and parties in a great international city? The experience of constructing a mighty weapon? Smashing birds against walls to subdue the filthy pigs? Taking defencelesse creatures under your patronage? Yes, of course you’re right, we will play Angry Birds!\r\n\r\nIn small groups you will design and program your self-made catapult. At the end, there will be a challenge in which you will proof your skills in the topic „aim and shoot“. Constructed with simple materials and programmed in LabView (will be provided during the week) your war machine is ready to show the little green pigs their master. Who’s laughing now?! To participate, no extensive informatics knowledge is required.. Don’t forget to mention your programming experience in your motivational letter though, so we can plan the groups in advance.\r\n\r\nDespite of the new subject, many of our famous activities will take place! Live “La Vida Loca” on our tram party, experience Zurich on our city rally and enjoy yourself on our Swiss night!\r\n\r\nBesides destroying castles, we will also show you the beauty of Switzerland and its mountains. And have we mentioned yet? Like every year, there will be many legendary parties!\r\n\r\nUnlike the last years, this LC Zurich event takes place in May, so we will be able to have more outside activities. As soon as all the filthy pigs are dead, we will go on a weekend trip to the countryside. We swear, no academical part there! So we will have more time to party! Buckle up and apply!\r\n\r\nOf course we will announce the participant’s list before the Congress!\r\n\r\nBest regards and see you in Zurich!!', 'Angry Engineers', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2256-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:13:14', '2013-11-22 00:13:14', '', 2256, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3867', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3868, 2, '2013-11-22 00:14:40', '2013-11-22 00:14:40', '\n<p>Hello there, dear and amazing EESTECers!</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Now, cutting to the chase, because April is the new March when it comes to EESTEC events, I would like to proudly announce you the first LC Bucharest Workshop in quite some time:</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>&#8220;Embedded Design Conference&#8221;</strong></p>\n<p>We hear so much about <strong>telemedicine</strong>, about integrated systems, about how cool it is to be a bio-medical engineer and how hype embedded systems are. But how about this: how about you do this for a change?</p>\n<p>What will you do during this week in Bucharest more precisely?</p>\n<p>You will assist lectures on the exact equipment that you will be bringing to use;<br />\nYou will get the chance to use up those programming skills that you thought to be gone, or maybe gain some;<br />\nYou will code on micro-controller devices so that you bring the concepts of telemedicine to life.</p>\n<p>And of course, let&#8217;s not forget about the fun part. Yes, the academics involved are quite heavy and interesting. But still, here we&#8217;re talking about an event powered by yours truly LC Bucharest. And you may be too young to remember our last legendary workshop, but you&#8217;re surely not too young to have met us so far or to have heard stories about how we rock the house everywhere we go <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>You will get to enjoy the city in one of the most entertaining days, through a lively program, you will have the chance to taste our amazing traditional dishes and also to party amazingly. And if you don&#8217;t trust me, ask your Congress members from last year about how we took care of them in Bucharest <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>You can bet this event is the one you&#8217;ve been waiting for! So don&#8217;t hesitate, bug your CPs and apply now <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Embedded Design Conference', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2257-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:14:40', '2013-11-22 00:14:40', '', 2257, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3868', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3869, 2, '2013-11-22 00:15:04', '2013-11-22 00:15:04', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers !</p>\n<p>LC Krakow would like to announce you that the 4th edition of our workshop „KrakYourNet” is coming once again this spring! But surprise, surprise <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We have decided it is a time for changes and KrakYourNet4 is going to be only for our domestic students. For you we have a pleasure to present an exchange, organised in parallel with KYN4, named ‘All day, all night, what a Krakow’ which will take place from 14th to 21th of April in the heart of Poland.</p>\n<p>For the ones who has never been in Krakow it will be an opportunity to see everything the best what our city can offer. And if you have already visited Krakow before, now you will have the chance to explore it even more and truly fall in love with this center of academic, cultural, artistic life and one of the oldest and largest cities in Poland.</p>\n<p>To be more specific you will visit:</p>\n<p>Cyfronet Academic Computer Centre &#8211; one of the largest Polish supercomputing and networking centres;<br />\nThe Wawel Royal Castle – located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;<br />\nThe Underground od the City’s Main Market Square – unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages;<br />\nKościuszko Mound – from the top of the mound you can admire the beautiful view of the whole city;<br />\nThe memorial and museum Auschwitz–Birkenau – the concentration camp from the Second World War and one of the symbols of the Holocaust.</p>\n<p>Still want more? Well, there are a laser tag’s competition, football game, bowling, unforgettable parties every night planned and many others activities to keep you busy for the whole week, but we do not want to reveal all of the attractions now. You have to come to Krakow and see for yourself <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>We promise you the time of your life, full of sightseeing and having fun! Don’t wait, apply right now. We are waiting for you!</p>\n<p><strong>Apply via <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>. The deadline for applications is 18th of March. The participation fee is 50 euro. The number of participants may be increased.</strong></p>\n<p>If you have any questions, don’t hesitate to contact me: <a href="mailto:skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com" target="_blank">skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com</a>. See you soon!</p>\n<p>Greetings,</p>\n', 'All day, all night, what a Krakow!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2258-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:15:04', '2013-11-22 00:15:04', '', 2258, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3869', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3870, 2, '2013-11-22 00:15:22', '2013-11-22 00:15:22', '<strong>RIS Workshop will be focused in the impact of robotics and High technologies in our Life. Hopefully you’ll enjoy it</strong>\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nFor the first time in France, JLC Lille is proud to announce you its EESTEC workshop: R.I.S !\r\n\r\nThe environmental awareness and the need of more efficiency led to develop more advanced technologies. Mandatory in all sectors of industry, intelligent autonomous systems are the key to growth of all technology focused companies. This has not only an effect on our environment, but also on our attitude. Whether in transportation, work tools or communication, they’ve became part of our every day life.\r\n\r\nThrough this event, we’ll try to gather students around the theme of technical and technological innovation, and its social and environmental impacts. Participants will attend theoretical presentations from scientists working in the field. They will also be visiting firms and laboratories in different sectors of intelligent systems.\r\n\r\nWe will likewise organize two contests : The Software tournament, and the Robotics tournament in which each participant will be teaming up with a French student.\r\n\r\nRIS will bring a greater effectiveness to the knowledge and the training of the participants, giving them the chance to be in direct contact with the Department of Research in Robotics field.\r\n\r\nAt last, but not the least, we’ll make sure you have a great time in Lille! You’ll have the opportunity to explore the best spots of the city during the City Rally, discover its charming atmosphere during day and night and try tasty French food and drinks!\r\n\r\nDon’t think, don’t wait. Just APPLY! We’ll be waiting for you motivation letters!\r\n\r\nOfficial website is coming soon, but you can find informations and news about the school and the city on\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iRC1znun9J8" target="_blank">Polytech’Lille Video</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jD6k2xmcPsU&amp;feature=related" target="_blank">Nao in polytech’Lille</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.polytech-lille.com\']);" href="http://www.polytech-lille.com/english/polytech-lille-ecole-polytechnique-france-art46.html" target="_blank">http://www.polytech-lille.com/english/polytech-lille-ecole-polytechnique-france-art46.html</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.destination-lille-metropole.eu\']);" href="http://www.destination-lille-metropole.eu/index.php?lang=en" target="_blank">Lille Metropole</a>\r\n\r\nSee you soon in Lille!', 'Robotics and Intelligent Systems (RIS) event', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2259-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:15:22', '2013-11-22 00:15:22', '', 2259, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3870', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3871, 2, '2013-11-22 00:16:05', '2013-11-22 00:16:05', '\n<p><img class="alignnone" title="Tie before you die" src="http://eestec.net/lc/delft/tie-before-you-die/themalogocolor.png/image_thumb" alt="Tie before you die" width="128" height="128" /></p>\n<p>DEAR EESTECERS,</p>\n<p>CAPSLOCK IS CRUISE CONTROL FOR COOL and a tie is cruise control for Delft. All (active) members of eestec LC Delft know that, as has been showed during ECMs and Congresses. We all love that feeling of wearing a tie, you know. Ever wanted to know that feeling, to wear a tie from Delft? We offer you the solution, because you have to <strong>Tie before you Die</strong>!</p>\n<p>After two years of silence LC Delft is back with a wonderful workshop full of educational, cultural and cool activities. We will show you how pleasant Delft is, how great our university is and how flat our country is.</p>\n<p>On the program we have among others:<br />\n- An excursion to the Dutch deltaworks. During a personal tour with some rental vans we will take you to see the stormvloedkering, the haringvlietdam and part of the Rotterdam harbour.<br />\n- A (day)trip to Amsterdam. That is something that can not be missing. When you think of The Netherlands, you think of Amsterdam with the great bars and wonderful sightseeing.<br />\n- A case study of the innovation department of an international company: Omron.<br />\n- Some awesome parties and so called borrels. According to eestec spirit the parties in the night will be awesome ofcourse, but to Delft standards we will also have some nice so called borrels.<br />\n- Informational lectures about our university and what they have to offer.<br />\n- LC Delft members as homestay. Hotels are good, but homestays are better according to us. It will provide a personal touch with our members.</p>\n<p>All activities can be participated while enjoying the sweet touch around your neck of a cool traditional LC Delft tie.</p>\n<p>Concluding I would like to tell you that this will be an awesome event and you should participate, because Delft is waiting for you!</p>\n<p>See you in Delft!</p>\n<p>Paul Marcelis<br />\nEESTEC LC Delft<br />\nContact Person<br />\n<a href="mailto:delft@eestec.net" target="_blank">delft@eestec.net</a></p>\n', 'Tie before you Die', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2260-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:16:05', '2013-11-22 00:16:05', '', 2260, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3871', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3872, 2, '2013-11-22 00:16:15', '2013-11-22 00:16:15', '\n<p><strong>An interactive workshop about the interaction between nano technology and power engineering.</strong></p>\n<p>After our announcement of &#8220;Speak Up!&#8221; two weeks ago, we are happy to present you our second event <strong>&#8220;From Nano to GigaWatts&#8221;</strong> (<strong>28.4.</strong> to<strong> 6.5.12</strong>).</p>\n<p>This workshop will cover many interesting points about the interaction between nano technology and power engineering. Do you know about the existance of solar cells based on nano technology? How these work? How all these futur solar cells influence the power grid? How we can power our homes in the future although there is no sun at night?</p>\n<p>There will be lectures about these topics as well as a hands-on lab on the development of a solar cell on organic basis where you&#8217;ll learn how to build your own functional solar cell. We&#8217;ll be cooperating with two departments in our university, so the lectures will be held by our professors.</p>\n<p>Apart from the lectures, we will introduce you to the lovely Bavarian capital, Munich. We look forward to showing you our Bavarian culture, Munich nightlife and our charming hospitality. The workshop will take place during the weeks of spring festival which is the &#8220;little sister&#8221; of our Oktoberfest and, of course, we don&#8217;t want you to miss this event either!</p>\n<p>As usual, the workshop will conclude with the International Motivational Weekend. This event will be held at a house in the alps. There you&#8217;ll participate in soft-skill training and, not to overlook, some unforgettable parties. (The IMW is free for participants!)</p>\n<p>Do not hestitate and apply now! LC Awesome is waiting for you!</p>\n', 'From Nano to GigaWatts', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2261-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:16:15', '2013-11-22 00:16:15', '', 2261, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3872', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3873, 2, '2013-11-22 00:16:20', '2013-11-22 00:16:20', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich would like to invite you to the IMW 2012, Mühlbach am Hochkönig.</p>\n<p>For everyone, who doesn&#8217;t know what an IMW is:</p>\n<p>An International Motivational Weekend is held to motivate new members (or future members) from all LCs in order to experience EESTEC and get an impression of the EESTEC Spirit. Therefore on Saturday EESTEC Trainers will have Softskill-Trainings with relaxing tournaments and baubleries prepared for all participants. As Friday and Saturday night, please enjoy two awesome theme parties.</p>\n<p>As an conclusion for our events Speak Up! and Nano feat. Power, we will be taking along all of our 30 participants and new members from LC Munich.</p>\n<p>Regarding the location, the house is located in the beautiful alps, next to the spa area Mühlbach am Hochkönig. During your freetime you can go hiking, play volleyball/soccer, explore the area with your friends, or simply relax while watching the hilarious landscape. <a href="http://www.hochkeilhaus.at/englisch/e_index.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.hochkeilhaus.at\']);" target="_blank">http://www.hochkeilhaus.at/englisch/e_index.htm</a></p>\n<p>The participation fee is 55 €, which includes accomodation and full board together with all kind of drinks for the parties on Friday and Saturday. Due to limited flexibility and possibilities, we will have to ask you to come by your own car. Nevertheless, we will try to offer pick-up service for people coming by train, but we can&#8217;t guarantee it. The pick up price will also vary on the location of pick-up (Make requests at eestec.ws@fs.ei.tum.de).</p>\n<p>The easiest way to participate in this event is simply apply for one of our awesome events (Deadlines are March, 15th for Speak Up and Nano feat. Power).</p>\n<p>We are looking forward to meeting you!</p>\n', 'IMW 2012 in Mühlbach am Hochkönig (LC Münich)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2262-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:16:20', '2013-11-22 00:16:20', '', 2262, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3873', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3874, 2, '2013-11-22 00:16:53', '2013-11-22 00:16:53', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich is honored to present you the sequel of our Women in Engineering <strong>&#8220;Speak Up!&#8221;</strong> workshop from <strong>April 28th</strong> until <strong>May 6th</strong>. As always, the event goes hand in hand with our second event which will be announced in the next couple of weeks.</p>\n<p>Our department for Gender Studies will give an interactive four day seminar. Female students will learn how to use their voice, express themselves and prove themselves in a working environment. It is a fact that women earn less money, are treated worse and hold less important positions in a company. Often, these facts lead to prejudice against women and they don&#8217;t even try to stand up for themselves, seeing that &#8220;it is just as it is&#8221;. So all you girls, use your voice and Speak Up! Our seminar will show you how to grasp opportunities and broaden your prospects for your future working life. Besides, together with all the participants you should work out your personal road to success.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, there will be a womens&#8217; contact forum during where you&#8217;ll have the opportunity to interact and exchange experiences with other women working in engineering jobs.</p>\n<p>Apart from the lectures, we will introduce you to the lovely Bavarian capital, Munich. We look forward to showing you our Bavarian culture, Munich nightlife and our charming hospitality. The workshop will take place during the weeks of spring festival which is the &#8220;little sister&#8221; of our Oktoberfest and, of course, we don&#8217;t want you to miss this event either!</p>\n<p>As usual, the workshop will conclude with the International Motivational Weekend. This event will be held at a house in the alps. There you&#8217;ll participate in soft-skill training and, not to overlook, some unforgettable parties. (The IMW is free for participants!)</p>\n<p>Do not hestitate and apply now! LC Awesome is waiting for you</p>\n', 'WiE: Speak Up!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2263-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:16:53', '2013-11-22 00:16:53', '', 2263, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3874', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3875, 2, '2013-11-22 00:17:19', '2013-11-22 00:17:19', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>If you survive EESTEC March events and take a little break in April, we think that in May you will have enough energy for full adventure in Sarajevo.</p>\n<p>We are inviting you to visit our city, <strong>from 30th April till 6th May</strong>, city that had the first full-time (dawn to dusk) tram line in Europe, city with many drinking fountains that share the legend: „if you drink water from them, you will come back to Sarajevo for sure“ (we still think that ćevapi are to blame for that, but drink some water, just in case <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> ), city in which the 14th Winter Olympic Games took place, that organizes one of the greatest film festivals in region every year &#8211; Sarajevo Film Festival, city that was in 2009. chosen as one of the 10 cities in the world you should visit.</p>\n<p>If those facts are not enough, then you are surely going to be intrigued by what EESTEC LC Sarajevo has prepared for you.</p>\n<p>Unforgettable sightseeing, where in the center of the city you are able to see Ghazi Husrev-beg mosque, which is one of the most significant Islamic monuments on Balkan, Ashkenazi Synagogue, third largest synagogue in Europe, Cathedral of Heart of Jesus which is, due to interesting combination of Gothic and Romanic elements different from all others and Orthodox Church which is one of the biggest orthodox temples in Balkans, and all that very close to each other.</p>\n<p>Still not interested? Then, we expect you to change your mind when we say that we have prepared two celebrations for you. First one is the celebration of 1st May, Labor Day, which is traditionally celebrated as a day off in Sarajevo.</p>\n<p>The second one is the celebration we are especially proud of. Two days of event are planned for <strong>celebrating LC Sarajevo’s 5th birthday</strong>. You will have a chance to see all our accomplishments during those 5 years, meet our alumni members and many more EESTECers from all over Europe that are going to be guests of our celebration. It’s, of course, applied that special occasions require special celebration in form of crazy all-night partying in city that never sleeps. We simply have to mention some delicious food that you will have opportunity to try in Sarajevo, such as ćevapi, burek and other pies, baklava and many more &#8211; you can be sure that you are going to enjoy our food very much <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> .</p>\n<p>If you are still second guessing whether to apply or not, there is one <strong>surprise trip</strong> planned&#8230; But, since it is surprise, you have to apply and see for yourself&#8230;</p>\n<p>Sooo? Are we going to meet in a beautiful city surrounded by mountains, beautiful nature and astonishing sights, the home of warm and friendly people and EESTECers waiting to host you and make this one week the most amazing week of your life <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> .</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>25.03.2012</strong>.</p>\n<p>More about our previous event, our city and country :<br />\n<a title="Bosnia and Herzegovina promo video" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9Imf56AJn0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Bosnia and Herzegovina promo video</a><br />\n<a title="Video clip from last event 1" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Video clip from last event 1</a><br />\n<a title="Short video clip from last event 2" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Crjp55vxaRM" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Short video clip from last event 2</a><br />\n<a title="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba" href="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.visitsarajevo.ba\']);" target="_blank">http://www.visitsarajevo.ba</a></p>\n<p><a title="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba" href="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba/" target="_blank"><br />\n</a></p>\n<p>We will send you special invitation for celebrating LC Sarajevo’s 5th birthday, this one is only for the exchange <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact me on <a href="mailto:elmica.bh@gmail.com" target="_blank">elmica.bh@gmail.com</a>. I&#8217;ll be pleased to answer.</p>\n<p>So, don&#8217;t hesitate and apply now for the greatest fun you&#8217;ll have this Spring!</p>\n<p>Can&#8217;t wait to see you all soon in the capital of The Heart-shaped Land!</p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'High 5 for LC Sarajevo', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2264-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:17:19', '2013-11-22 00:17:19', '', 2264, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3875', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3876, 2, '2013-11-22 00:17:56', '2013-11-22 00:17:56', '\n<p>Hello dear EESTEC-ers, after 2 years LC East Sarajevo is back! We are proud to present you &#8220;Jahorina Spring Break&#8221;, unforgettable event that will take place from 20th to 27th of March 2012.</p>\n<p>Academic part will be held on Jahorina (our Olympic mountain), where International Scientific Symposium &#8211; Infoteh 2012 will take place. You will have opportunity to listen lectures from the experts, scientists, engineers, researchers and students that deal with information technologies. We provided <a href="http://www.motel-topalovic.com/hotele.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.motel-topalovic.com\']);" target="_blank">hotel accommodation</a> for our participants, transport to Infoteh and back.</p>\n<p>Non academic part will be quite hedonistic and relaxed, but full of various activities, such as swimming, bowling…or just lazy sitting in pub and drinking beer/coffee/juice/rakija/whatever…</p>\n<p>We will also visit Orlovaca cave and beautiful well of Bosna river. Sightseeing and visiting city landmarks are also part of the program. During these 7 days you will taste our traditional food and drinks. We will organize traditional Serbian night with our live music, and people dressed in traditional Serbian clothes.</p>\n<p>And at the end, thing that you are waiting the most…….YES! Parties will be every night on various places!</p>\n<p>As you could see, this is a life time opportunity. Many people would kill for it, so don’t hesitate to apply! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>See you in East Sarajevo!</p>\n', 'Jahorina Spring Break', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2265-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:17:56', '2013-11-22 00:17:56', '', 2265, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3876', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3877, 2, '2013-11-22 00:18:30', '2013-11-22 00:18:30', 'Hello dear EESTEC-ers, after 2 years LC East Sarajevo is back! We are proud to present you “Jahorina Spring Break”, unforgettable event that will take place from 20th to 27th of March 2012.\n\nAcademic part will be held on Jahorina (our Olympic mountain), where International Scientific Symposium – Infoteh 2012 will take place. You will have opportunity to listen lectures from the experts, scientists, engineers, researchers and students that deal with information technologies. We provided <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.motel-topalovic.com\']);" href="http://www.motel-topalovic.com/hotele.html" target="_blank">hotel accommodation</a> for our participants, transport to Infoteh and back.\n\nNon academic part will be quite hedonistic and relaxed, but full of various activities, such as swimming, bowling…or just lazy sitting in pub and drinking beer/coffee/juice/rakija/whatever…\n\nWe will also visit Orlovaca cave and beautiful well of Bosna river. Sightseeing and visiting city landmarks are also part of the program. During these 7 days you will taste our traditional food and drinks. We will organize traditional Serbian night with our live music, and people dressed in traditional Serbian clothes.\n\nAnd at the end, thing that you are waiting the most…….YES! Parties will be every night on various places!\n\nAs you could see, this is a life time opportunity. Many people would kill for it, so don’t hesitate to apply! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\n\nSee you in East Sarajevo!', 'Jahorina Spring Break', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2265-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:18:30', '2013-11-22 00:18:30', '', 2265, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3877', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3878, 2, '2013-11-22 00:23:56', '2013-11-22 00:23:56', 'Dear EESTECers,\n\nHave you ever wanted to turn lead into gold? Ever wondered how to convince a company of the importance of willingly giving money and stuff to EESTEC? Ever wondered how to get money out of thin air? FRAME IS YOUR EVENT!\n\nIn EESTEC International we’re looking for people with EESTEC Spirit and the nuts to fight to make international events possible, to bring more and more quality to everything we do. Motivation is the cement that keeps us together, that makes us strong to make greatness happen. But the same way we can’t build a palace without bricks, we can’t deploy projects and organize events without money.\n\nEnter FR, the team that will bring stability and a stable economical source to sustain our international infrastructure and make congresses, ECMs, T4T, etc. not only possible but pleasant, not having to worry about tight budgets and loans <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\n\nBut this is not only for International. Think about the experience you might acquire and the boost your local LC FR might get. So let’s work together in a great team for all EESTEC.\n\nAnd this awesome event is going to take place in a beautiful <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niš" target="_blank">City of Niš</a>. It has been gate between East and West. It has great cultural and historical heritage. One of the most important persons in European history, Emperor <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Niš (roman name <strong>NAISSUS</strong>) in 272AD. Because of that, Niš is also known as The Emperor’s city.\n\nYou will visit <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niš_Fortress" target="_blank">Fortress of Niš</a> that exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. That’s because Niš has been gate between East and West, so many civilizations passed here and they left some trace in the fortress. It’s in this condition since XVII century, and now it’s one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe.\n\nWe have rich historical legacy, but we have even richer offer of national foods and drinks. You won’t be hungry at any moment and you will be able to enjoy in our best meals. Don’t forget our traditional drink- rakija!\n\nSerbia is famous of its very live nightlife. So you will have a lot of fun in both traditional places called kafana and in night clubs.\n\nWe’re preparing you unforgettable EESTEC event!\n\nApplying is via <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> site. Motivational letter is required.\n\nFor any additional question, contact <a href="mailto:treasurer@eestec.net" target="_blank">treasurer@eestec.net</a>.\n\nGreetings from Niš!', 'FRAME 2012', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2266-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:23:56', '2013-11-22 00:23:56', '', 2266, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3878', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3879, 2, '2013-11-22 00:24:13', '2013-11-22 00:24:13', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Have you ever wanted to turn lead into gold? Ever wondered how to convince a company of the importance of willingly giving money and stuff to EESTEC? Ever wondered how to get money out of thin air? FRAME IS YOUR EVENT!</p>\n<p>In EESTEC International we&#8217;re looking for people with EESTEC Spirit and the nuts to fight to make international events possible, to bring more and more quality to everything we do. Motivation is the cement that keeps us together, that makes us strong to make greatness happen. But the same way we can&#8217;t build a palace without bricks, we can&#8217;t deploy projects and organize events without money.</p>\n<p>Enter FR, the team that will bring stability and a stable economical source to sustain our international infrastructure and make congresses, ECMs, T4T, etc. not only possible but pleasant, not having to worry about tight budgets and loans <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>But this is not only for International. Think about the experience you might acquire and the boost your local LC FR might get. So let’s work together in a great team for all EESTEC.</p>\n<p>And this awesome event is going to take place in a beautiful <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niš" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">City of Niš</a>. It has been gate between East and West. It has great cultural and historical heritage. One of the most important persons in European history, Emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Niš (roman name <strong>NAISSUS</strong>) in 272AD. Because of that, Niš is also known as The Emperor&#8217;s city.</p>\n<p>You will visit <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niš_Fortress" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Fortress of Niš</a> that exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. That’s because Niš has been gate between East and West, so many civilizations passed here and they left some trace in the fortress. It’s in this condition since XVII century, and now it’s one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe.</p>\n<p>We have rich historical legacy, but we have even richer offer of national foods and drinks. You won&#8217;t be hungry at any moment and you will be able to enjoy in our best meals. Don&#8217;t forget our traditional drink- rakija!</p>\n<p>Serbia is famous of its very live nightlife. So you will have a lot of fun in both traditional places called kafana and in night clubs.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re preparing you unforgettable EESTEC event!</p>\n<p>Applying is via <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> site. Motivational letter is required.</p>\n<p>For any additional question, contact <a href="mailto:treasurer@eestec.net" target="_blank">treasurer@eestec.net</a>.</p>\n<p>Greetings from Niš!</p>\n', 'FRAME 2012', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2266-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:24:13', '2013-11-22 00:24:13', '', 2266, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3879', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3880, 2, '2013-11-22 00:24:28', '2013-11-22 00:24:28', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>One more time, LC Madrid is proud to announce you our last workshop! <strong>Network Society 2.0</strong></p>\n<p>Due to its success last year, we have decided to continue with the topic. It will make you aware of the importance that networking each other has. A networked society allows us to save time, money and energy when trying to communicate each other and it can make things easier in case of necessity. In our workshop we will analyse and treat the presence of networks and communications in every aspect of our lives. Nowadays people is more connected than ever, and a big part of our communication takes part in the so-called &#8220;social networks&#8221;. Most of us have smartphones in our pockets, and couldn&#8217;t think of living without being permanently connected. Furthermore, networks are also present in every other aspect of society, such as health-care, commerce and learning. We can truly speak of a &#8220;Society of the networks&#8221;, the &#8220;Network society&#8221;. For that reason, we have prepared several lectures carried out by different companies just to show you their cutting-edge projects and visits to laboratories and research centres to see exactly how they work.</p>\n<p>It will be held from <strong>22nd to 29th April</strong>, so you have enough time to renew your energy after Congress <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>But that&#8217;s not all!! We have also prepared for you non-academical activities. You will have the opportunity to explore every secret place of Madrid during the City Rally, to taste Spanish food and drinks (I know all of you like Sangría) and feel its atmosphere during day, but specially during night!</p>\n<p>At the end, during the weekend, organizers and participants will stay in the countryside. What we will do there is&#8230;a surprise! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Still thinking to apply?! Seriously?!</p>\n<p>Apply now! You have until <strong>15th of March</strong>! Long time to make up your minds.</p>\n<p>Finally, as we always say&#8230;</p>\n<p>We are so sorry to have to say this, but as we don&#8217;t apply for EU grant, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although last year was faultless <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  , we expect an exemplary attitude from all of you and we friendly ask you for cooperation and comprehension. Irresponsible attitudes won&#8217;t be tolerated and in case it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.<br />\nWhen it is time to party, we have party (and trust me, we will do! ;D), but when it&#8217;s time to work, we must work (and later we have party! ^^).</p>\n<p><strong>Follow us</strong>: <a href="http://www.eestec.es/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.eestec.es\']);" target="_blank">Website</a>, <a href="http://www.facebook.com/#!/pages/Eestec-Eurielec/115934218476771" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.facebook.com\']);" target="_blank">Facebook</a> and <a href="http://twitter.com/eurielec" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://twitter.com\']);" target="_blank">Twitter</a></p>\n<p>We hope to see you all in Madrid! =)</p>\n<p>Greetings from LC Madrid</p>\n', 'Network Society 2.0', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2267-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:24:28', '2013-11-22 00:24:28', '', 2267, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3880', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3881, 2, '2013-11-22 00:24:36', '2013-11-22 00:24:36', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe are very glad to officially announce Congress 2012 registration period. From now and till 29 January all LCs, JLCs and Observers have a chance to register their representative for Congress which will take place from 29th of March till 6th of April in Tallinn and Riga, Estonia and Latvia respectively (First 4 days will be in Tallinn and rest 4 days in Riga).\r\n\r\nEach LC, JLC and Observer have a right for at least one place on Congress. If you do not register your representative till the deadline, Int. Board will assign place for your LC to BAs, Trainers, IT members and other international teams.\r\n\r\nPlease do not miss the <strong>deadline 29 January</strong> for your registration!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What kind of participants are expected at the Congress?</strong>\r\n\r\nIt’s totally up to the LC/JLC/Observer to decide who you want to send on Congress as your official representatives. Int. Board will not interfere in your decision.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What do we expect from participants during Congress?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>We expect that every LC has at least one representative during every General Assembly (GA) sessions. It is inexcusable to miss any GA since we are going to have discussion on very important topics for EESTEC such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>§ EESTEC projects</li>\r\n	<li>§ Board and Bodies report</li>\r\n	<li>§ Promotion and degradation of LCs and JLCs</li>\r\n	<li>§ RoP changing</li>\r\n	<li>§ Election of the new International Board</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis year we will also have Open Day as part of Congress 2012. Open Day can be counted as a “fair” where there are booths for participating companies, universities, EESTEC local committees and international Board, and every representative are free to visit each others’ booths for information exchange about any idea or opportunity.\r\n\r\nWhat do you need to bring for Open Day?\r\n\r\nEvery LC representative should bring on Congress:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>§ Informational materials of your University-Faculty (this is most important)</li>\r\n	<li>§ Informational materials of your LC (also very important)</li>\r\n	<li>§ Promo materials of your LC activities (posters, flyers, bookmarks…)</li>\r\n	<li>§ LC flag (only if you have one, don’t need to make if you don’t have)</li>\r\n	<li>§ Prepare ınformational (at least 1 page) documents or presentation/slides which includes:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>§ Your recruitment Strategy (how you get new members every year)</li>\r\n	<li>§ What makes your LC successful? (your successful projects, activities…)</li>\r\n	<li>§ How you keep motivations of your members? (motivation strategies, tips and tricks)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>To sum up and again the most important, don’t miss deadline for registration, 29 January, since after that deadline, International Board will give your places to Bodies.</strong>\r\n\r\nAlso, you find additional information in the site <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" href="http://eestec.net/news-and-offers/congress-2012-in-general" target="_blank">here</a>\r\n\r\nWaiting for your registration,\r\nEESTEC International board', '26th Annual Congress', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2268-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:24:36', '2013-11-22 00:24:36', '', 2268, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3881', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
 (3882, 2, '2013-11-22 00:25:14', '2013-11-22 00:25:14', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers;</p>\n<p>What about using just a thin LCD except for a 3 kg laptop or a desktop? What if there weren’t any harddisks in your computers? We are proud to announce our upcoming workshop “<strong>CLOCODILE</strong>” (<strong>CLO</strong>ud <strong>CO</strong>mputing and <strong>D</strong>elightful <strong>I</strong>stanbul <strong>L</strong>ife is <strong>E</strong>nclosed) which will be held on 4 &#8211; 11 March 2012, in Istanbul, Turkey.</p>\n<p>Imagine a world that your data would never been lost or a harddisk that does not fit in your pockets. The days that you can reach your data with just one password are not far away. Cloud Computing is going to shape future computers. It is the new trend in IT World which will change all human habits. In this workshop following topics are going to be discussed;</p>\n<p>-What is Cloud Computing?</p>\n<p>-Advantages and disadvantages of Cloud Computing</p>\n<p>-Services of Cloud Computing</p>\n<p>-Attitude of companies</p>\n<p>-Distincts between classical methods and Cloud Computing</p>\n<p>Our goal is to teach what exactly Cloud Computing is and to create ideas for future on this topic which may change the IT World.</p>\n<p>Wait, we haven’t forgotten the craziest part of our event. You’ll forget about any other cities or time you’ve spent anywhere, and you will never forget your most delightful time in your life, of course in Istanbul. You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population; however, you ‘ll have an unforgettable 7 days without doubt. As one of the biggest cities, Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places and delightful nightlife of course. Istanbul has become the capital of 3 biggest empires of the history; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_Empire" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Roman</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byzantine_Empire" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Byzantine</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ottoman_Empire" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Ottoman Empire</a>. So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and historical richness it includes. We are going to take you to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topkapi_Palace_Museum" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Topkapı</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dolmabahçe_Palace" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Dolmabahçe Palaces</a> where the Ottoman Sultans resided, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hagia_Sophia" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Hagia Sophia Museum</a> from the 6th century, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sultan_Ahmed_Mosque" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Blue Mosque</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basilica_Cistern" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Basilica Cistern</a> and some more surprise beautiful places. Participants will also have the chance to watch both Asian and European Part from the middle of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosphorus" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Bosphorus</a> when we are making Bosphorus Tour as a tradition. You will taste <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_Cuisine" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Turkish Cuisine</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nargile" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Nargile</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rakı" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Rakı</a> with Turkish hospitality. Can you imagine a street where about 1 million peopele walks on just in one day? That street’s name is Istiklal and parties will be held in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/İstiklal_Avenue" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Istiklal Avenue</a> which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see. Please do not forget to bring extra SD Cards for your camera, because your card will be full at the end of the first day!</p>\n<p>Are you still waiting to apply ? ? LC ISTANBUL is ready for you ! ! Apply via <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> with your motivational letter before 2nd of February.</p>\n<p>For more information do not hestitate to contact us via <a href="mailto:emrecoskun1036@gmail.com" target="_blank">emrecoskun1036@gmail.com</a></p>\n<p>Our website: <a href="http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr\']);" target="_blank">www.eestec.itu.edu.tr</a></p>\n<p>In addition; to help you to know at least a little about;</p>\n<p>Istanbul, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Istanbul &#8211; 2010 European Capital of Culture</a> , <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iglYVm01RHU" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Istanbul Timeless City</a> and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Turkey</a></p>\n<p>Kind Regards and see you in Istanbul.</p>\n', 'CLOCODILE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2269-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:25:14', '2013-11-22 00:25:14', '', 2269, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3882', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
