 (2271, 1, '2012-01-07 23:00:09', '2012-01-07 22:00:09', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Have you ever thought of attending a seven-days long city rally? Or even better, seven-nights long city rally? No…? Well, this is the right moment to do that!</p>\n<p>LC Belgrade proudly presents you the exchange of all the exchanges… <strong>”Belgrade State of Mind”</strong>… You might have heard of it, or even experienced the part of it, but the fact is… There are no words to describe this feeling… We can just give you a little <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h808DzQMzU0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">glimpse</a> of what to expect this March…</p>\n<p>This exchange will be all about discovering the real soul of one of the oldest cities in Europe. Its secret passages will lead you to the magnificent fortress of Kalemegdan and the Bohemian quarter of Skadarlija. More importantly, you will have the chance to witness how EESTECers take the most out of the world’s famous nightlife. Theatres, interesting museums, countless restaurants and clubs will just help you get use to this never-ending party that’s happening in Belgrade.</p>\n<p>And if that wasn’t even enough… Your adventurous spirit will also be challenged by one of the wildest parts of Serbia, The National park of Tara. Together with Belgraders you will have the chance to explore the wooden city of <a href="http://www.mecavnik.info/wsw/index.php?p=197" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.mecavnik.info\']);" target="_blank">Mećavnik</a>, enjoy the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">soulfood</a> of Serbia and even try out some things you just didn’t know they still exist.</p>\n<p>So if you are ready for some new experience, apply and don’t miss the chance to explore one of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zSKMv6sfBdw&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">the best-kept secrets of Europe</a>.</p>\n', 'Belgrade State of Mind', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'belgrade-state-of-mind', '', '', '2012-01-07 23:00:09', '2012-01-07 22:00:09', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/belgrade-state-of-mind/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2272, 1, '2012-01-07 22:55:35', '2012-01-07 21:55:35', 'Shiny EESTEC’ers,\r\n\r\nAs EESTEC’ers, which are the best students in their faculties, we are all trying to be good engineers in our fields, but do you think only technical lectures we have had is enough to be a good one? If you say “No way!”, <strong>you need the correct TOOL!</strong> LC Ankara is proud to announce a brand-new international event, in cooperation with EESTEC Training Team: <strong>TOOL, a.k.a. Topic Oriented Optimized Learning.</strong>\r\n\r\nTOOL is a week-long soft-skills training and academic lecture series on various themes. The idea was born among EESTEC Training Team, after the first “soft-skills training” event of EESTEC, Tools For Action, also organized by LC Ankara on 2009. The main motivation behind TOOL is <strong>to spread the knowledge within EESTEC and create the future leaders of it!</strong>\r\n\r\nInterested already? Wait for the details…\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter" title="TOOL" alt="" src="http://eestec.net/lc/ankara/tool-engineering-management-economics/tool3_2cokkucuk.jpg/image_preview" width="400" height="267" />\r\n\r\nTheme of this first EESTEC TOOL is “Engineering Economics &amp; Management”. From 10th to 17th of March 2012, EESTEC’ers will attend trainings and lectures on various topics in this frame. The academic part of the event will be divided into two parts:\r\n\r\nFirst part is various soft-skill trainings that will be <strong>delivered by EESTEC Trainers</strong>. If you are interested in this kind of an event, you should have heard about EESTEC Training Team and how well qualified trainers take part of it. So, participants will receive trainings on topics like:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Project Management and Scheduling</li>\r\n	<li>Risk Management</li>\r\n	<li>Strategical Planning</li>\r\n	<li>Organizational Continuity</li>\r\n	<li>Budget Planning</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSecond part will be academic lectures, again on the same theme. Lectures will be <strong>delivered by professors who have worldwide prestige on their fields</strong>. The topics will be:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Engineering Management</li>\r\n	<li>Engineering Economic Analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Decision Analysis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIs it only about to improvement as prospective engineers? Please…\r\n\r\nIf you haven’t met yet, let us introduce you <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_cuisine" target="_blank">Turkish cuisine</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hookah" target="_blank">Turkish nargile</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rakı" target="_blank">Rakı</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belly_dance" target="_blank">belly dance</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_bath" target="_blank">Turkish bath</a> and most importantly, Turkish hospitality!.. The accommodation will be in city center and participants will enjoy parties with a lot of different themes! We won’t forget to have some EESTEC event traditions like sightseeing in historical capital of Turkey and international night as well.\r\n\r\nOne more important detail: <strong>TOOL is supported by EU Youth in Action Programme, which means 70% of travel costs from your city to Ankara will be covered for EU citizens</strong> as well as 100% of accommodation and food expenses as always. However, we will be able to refund <strong>70% of travel expenses for non-EU citizens, only if they choose to use “Balkan FlexiPass”</strong>. Besides, applicants from LC’s which sent Partnership forms to us will have priority in selection process.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter" title="YIA" alt="" src="http://eestec.net/lc/ankara/tool-engineering-management-economics/youthkopya.png/image_mini" width="200" height="125" /><img class="aligncenter" title="YIA" alt="" src="http://eestec.net/lc/ankara/tool-engineering-management-economics/youthen.png/image_mini" width="200" height="80" />\r\n\r\nAn amazing, brand-new event is waiting for you! Apply via <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> with your <strong>motivation letter in English</strong> before <strong>4th of February</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, don’t hesitate to contact us via cp@eestectr.org\r\n\r\nGreetings from snowy Ankara!', 'TOOL: Engineering Economics & Management', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'tool-engineering-economics-management', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:54:33', '2013-03-01 21:54:33', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/tool-engineering-economics-management/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2273, 1, '2012-01-07 22:28:17', '2012-01-07 21:28:17', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After years of silence LC Hamburg is finally back on track and proudly presents its new production:</p>\n<p>“The EesteCube”</p>\n<p>The curtains haven&#8217;t been raised yet, but our short &#8220;trailer&#8221; will give you some hints of what awaits you.</p>\n<p>In the main role are starring ten (eventually up to 20) professional Eestecers.</p>\n<p>The story takes place in the greenest and probably most beautiful city in Europe &#8211; Hamburg.</p>\n<p>The plot consists of unforgettable nights at the famous ‘Reeperbahn’ street, visiting the second biggest harbor in Europe, an adventurous city rally, and &#8220;tasting&#8221; of German beer. And all these amazing scenes will be enlightened by the unique LED Cubes all of our smart main characters are going to build.</p>\n<p>They are going to be 5x5x5 single colored LED Cubes controlled by an ATmega32 microcontroller. Each of the 5 LED layers is driven by a D-Flip Flop. The controlling of this 3D LED matrix will be managed by time multiplexing.</p>\n<p>The scenario will be presented by our professors, however in order to pass the casting the actors should have basic C programming knowledge.</p>\n<p>So put your costumes and makeup on and apply for this fascinating workshop.</p>\n<p>The premier will start on 27th February and end on 5th March 2012.</p>\n<p><strong>Deadline to apply is January 26th!</strong></p>\n<p>LEDs on: 3, 2, 1, action!</p>\n', 'EesteCube', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'eestecube', '', '', '2012-01-07 22:28:17', '2012-01-07 21:28:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/eestecube/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2274, 1, '2011-12-06 08:41:49', '2011-12-06 07:41:49', '\n<p>Hello dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>The time has come for LC Athens to announce its next workshop called &#8216;<strong>&#8216;Think Smart, Act Green</strong>&#8221;, which will be held from <strong>January 29th until February 5th</strong>!</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone" title="Think Smart, Act Green" src="http://eestec.net/lc/athens/think-smart-act-green/think_smart4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="140" /></p>\n<p>The subject of this workshop is (you guessed it right)<strong> renewable forms of energy</strong>, a topic that concerns all of us. So the participants are going to spend the week learning -from our best professors in our faculty-, about how they work, what forms of renewable energy exist, and their importance to today&#8217;s world. But that&#8217;s not all! We&#8217;ll also visit the first energy autonomous village in Greece!!</p>\n<p>Moreover, concerning the practical part, participants will be divided into groups and they will make solar-panel models, where the most effective one&#8217;s team will be awarded! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>There will be also trainings held by our famous trainers Thanos and Grigoris!!</p>\n<p>But really, have you ever met Athens by night??? This is another very important reason to apply for this event! LC Athens will take care of you every night and take you to the best places in Athens! (I&#8217;m not saying anything more, there will be surprises! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  )</p>\n<p>You will also taste traditional Greek food , our famous ouzo and delicious desserts <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>At the end of the workshop, we will have the chance to visit our beautiful countryside and have almost an entire hotel to ourselves! Crazy partying, anyone??!</p>\n<p>Last but really not least, we&#8217;re really pleased that our application for the &#8221;<strong>Youth in Action</strong>&#8221; programme was accepted, so about <strong>70% of the travelling expenses will be refunded</strong>!!</p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for??</p>\n<p>Just apply and take care of your board! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Think Smart, Act Green', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'think-smart-act-green', '', '', '2011-12-06 08:41:49', '2011-12-06 07:41:49', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/think-smart-act-green/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2275, 1, '2011-11-01 23:06:04', '2011-11-01 22:06:04', '\n<p>We are excited to announce that this winter all roads will lead to <a href="http://www.tob.rs/en/index.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.tob.rs\']);" target="_blank">the capital of Serbia</a>. This December, <strong>LC Belgrade</strong> is organizing our eagerly awaited winter exchange <strong>“Freeze the Time!”</strong>. The spotlight is on showing our fellow EESTECers why Begrade is known as “the city that never sleeps”.</p>\n<p>No matter when, if it is during the night or day, our participants will get the chance to see how hedonism is present in all aspects of life in Belgrade. Walking through the New Year’s decorations of Knez Mihajlova street and visiting numerous restaurants, bars and clubs are excellent ways to enjoy Belgrade, especially when the end of the year is approaching. Dressed in white, our city will show you that there is no such place in the whole world where passion and European elegance is so naturally connected. But don’t forget that you are coming to <a href="http://www.tesla-museum.org/meni_en.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.tesla-museum.org\']);" target="_blank">the land of Nikola Tesla</a> and that’s why you will also have the chance to enter the brilliant mind of this scientist. But that is not all! As the end of the year approaches, all students in Belgrade, which of course includes you, prepare for the well known <a href="http://kst.etf.rs/?p=14&amp;idv=2812" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://kst.etf.rs\']);" target="_blank">costume ball</a> in our favourite students’ club KST. So be ready to put some crazy costumes in your suitcase. And in case you’ve missed the Suit up Day, don’t worry, LC Belgrade is taking you to the traditional ball on our faculty where you’ll get to show your moves on the dance floor.</p>\n<p>Apart from world wide famous nightlife, you will have the chance to spend a few days out of Belgrade, try out our delicious cuisine and of course discover the spirit of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eASk9akIpvg&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Serbia</a> that lies in a bottle of our national drink rakija.</p>\n<p>Don’t think you’ve heard it all! We have plenty of surprises left for you. Just remember, when you come to the White City, the clock stops, time freezes and the party begins. Be ready for the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jAtf5obN3cc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Belgrade state of mind</a>!</p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Olja Majstorović</p>\n', 'Freeze the Time', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'freeze-the-time', '', '', '2011-11-01 23:06:04', '2011-11-01 22:06:04', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/freeze-the-time/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2276, 1, '2011-11-01 21:31:18', '2011-11-01 20:31:18', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Would you like to get out of your daily routine and try something new?</p>\n<p>Do you lure to get a sneak peak in the spectacular cutting edge robots?</p>\n<p>Well, fasten your seat-belts because you are about to have the journey of your lifetime in the Future Robot Republic of Macedonia or abbreviated RoboMAC!</p>\n<p>LC Skopje is proud to announce that in collaboration with IEEE for the third time we are organizing the RoboMAC! It will take place from 19-th to 26-th of February in Skopje, with 30 international participants (EESTEC people) and over 70 students from our faculty&#8230;<br />\nYes you read that right!!! 30 EESTECers means this is the third biggest EESTEC event after EESTEC Congress and ECM.</p>\n<p>Now let us tell you a little bit about RoboMAC…<br />\nRoboMAC means students creating scientific robots using off-the-shelf materials. What that means? That means that you will learn to build a robot that will do a specific job, with only the materials that you can buy in the local hardware store. Cool right !!! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  And at the end of the week in the biggest closed sport venture in Macedonia &#8211; our national arena you can start the thrilling competition and check out how good is your robot <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> . Racing, sumo wrestling, programming an AI task oriented algorithms, or simply play “hide and seek” with your robots in a maze, and all that in front of lot of audience and the media. It means you will be a TV star that day in Macedonia. But that’s not creative enough ??? No problem !!! Use your creative mind and take the challenge to program a Humanoid that will be capable of doing some crazy stuff, like Macarena dance <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> .</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aq1bkaMBp3w&amp;feature=player_profilepage#t=156s" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aq1bkaMBp3w&amp;feature=player_profilepage#t=156s</a></p>\n<p>You don’t know how to do this, but you want to learn? That’s why we have asked our professors from the robotics and AI (artificial intelligence) departments to teach you, and show you everything.</p>\n<p>Not ready to apply?<br />\nBut wait !!! We haven’t told you about the fun part !!!<br />\nIn Skopje we party only on New Year’s Eve and the days that end on “day”, like MonDAY, TuesDAY,…., SunDAY. And bear to forget to visit the local Kafanas. Also we promise to keep the tradition of organizing the glamorous wine night where you will be enjoying best wines in Macedonia! We also want to know more about your country, that’s why on the international party you will have the chance to introduce us to some of your local drinks and delicacies.</p>\n<p>Don’t worry we didn’t forget about giving you a tour throughout Skopje. You will be visiting:<br />\nThe Old Bazar <a href="http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6</a><br />\nThe Biggest Cross in the world on the top of mount Vodno, where you will have a cup of coffee with the best view on Skopje<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/66gyndu" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://tinyurl.com\']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/66gyndu</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942097" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.panoramio.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942097</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942204" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.panoramio.com\']);">http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942204</a><br />\nThe biggest statue of Alexander the Great in the world and its fountain below (believe me the animation does not give it justice)<br />\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=87DJ-LqYmHw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=87DJ-LqYmHw</a></p>\n<p>As you get it, we like big stuff so become part of the big fat RoboMAC…<br />\n…apply don&#8217;t wait!</p>\n', 'RoboMAC', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'robomac', '', '', '2011-11-01 21:31:18', '2011-11-01 20:31:18', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/robomac/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2277, 1, '2011-11-01 16:32:14', '2011-11-01 15:32:14', '\n<p>Dear shiny EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After quite a long brake, we are back with new ideas, energy and surprises for you <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif\' alt=\':P\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We, LC Wrocław, are proud and very happy to announce our workshop: “Microsystems around us”. This event will give you fat and juicy pill of microsystems, an all-around super-developing branch of electrical engineering. It’s a great opportunity for all of you to get to know what’s inside™</p>\n<p>Our experts from the University will show you the world. From their geeky perspective of course;) This means getting into it hard (ware) &#8211; how to fabricate the microsystems from silicon wafer to finished product (including photolithography, chemical etching and packaging process) and soft – latest achievements in the field and the opportunity to visit a cleanroom (if you thought of your toilet, check <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cleanroom" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cleanroom</a>). Already interested? Here you have some videos about this subject:</p>\n<p>• about microsystems: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CNmk-SeM0ZI&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CNmk-SeM0ZI&amp;feature=related</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8VFvlDySHU&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8VFvlDySHU&amp;feature=related</a></p>\n<p>• website of Wrocław University of Technology: <a href="http://www.pwr.wroc.pl/index.dhtml" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.pwr.wroc.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www.pwr.wroc.pl/index.dhtml</a></p>\n<p>• website of our MEMS laboratory: <a href="http://www.memslab.pl/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.memslab.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www.memslab.pl/</a></p>\n<p>• laboratories live – the Faculty of Microsystem Electronics and Photonics: <a href="http://www.wpanoramie.pl/wemifpwrwroc/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.wpanoramie.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www.wpanoramie.pl/wemifpwrwroc/</a></p>\n<p>• a video made in our laboratories: <a href="http://www-old.wemif.pwr.wroc.pl/m3/data/aktywnosc_kola.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www-old.wemif.pwr.wroc.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www-old.wemif.pwr.wroc.pl/m3/data/aktywnosc_kola.php</a></p>\n<p>• dessert link: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bp00IuVAheQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bp00IuVAheQ</a></p>\n<p>If you’ve read this far or skipped right to it, what you want the most, here it is: hedonism, tourism and partyism all the way! ;D During this weekly event you will have a lot of fun visiting our city and partying till dawn. To list some of the places we have scheduled for you (excluding party joints to keep the trump card – good luck for inquisitive souls at googling polish sites;):</p>\n<p>Ogród Japoński,</p>\n<p>Ostrów Tumski (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ostr%C3%B3w_Tumski,_Wroc%C5%82aw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ostr%C3%B3w_Tumski,_Wroc%C5%82aw</a>),</p>\n<p>Panorama Racławicka (<a href="http://www.panoramaraclawicka.pl/en/what_to_see.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.panoramaraclawicka.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www.panoramaraclawicka.pl/en/what_to_see.html</a>),</p>\n<p>ZOO (<a href="http://www.zoo.wroclaw.pl/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.zoo.wroclaw.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www.zoo.wroclaw.pl/</a>),</p>\n<p>Aquapark (<a href="http://www.parkwodny.wroc.pl/en/recreational-pools-gallery" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.parkwodny.wroc.pl\']);" target="_blank">http://www.parkwodny.wroc.pl/en/recreational-pools-gallery</a>),</p>\n<p>Wyspa Słodowa and others (<a href="http://www.facebook.com/wroclaw.wroclove" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.facebook.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/wroclaw.wroclove</a>).</p>\n<p>Also you will able to do some shopping on the polish Christmas fair (<a href="http://www.jarmarkbozonarodzeniowy.com/?lang=en" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.jarmarkbozonarodzeniowy.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.jarmarkbozonarodzeniowy.com/?lang=en</a>).</p>\n<p>For any questions don&#8217;t hesitate to ask! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Applications should be sent to <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a></span>.</p>\n<p>Apply now! Don&#8217;t miss the chance to take part in a truly amazing adventure with LC Wrocław.</p>\n', 'Microsystems around us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'microsystems-around-us', '', '', '2011-11-01 16:32:14', '2011-11-01 15:32:14', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/microsystems-around-us/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2278, 1, '2011-09-30 17:04:54', '2011-09-30 16:04:54', '\n<p>Hey EESTECers,</p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t want to miss this! LC Aachen is going to show you the Christmas time of your life – the Niko-event is here! Apply till 01.11.2011 and experience from 03.12. (arrival) to 10.12. (departure) 2011.</p>\n<p>This is not a workshop, so prepare for the best! In our great exchange atmosphere, without learning or smart clothes (people from Delft are still allowed to bring their tie <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> ), we promise you an amazing meeting in a romantic Christmas fair atmosphere with lots of hot mulled wine, gingerbread and EESTEC-spirit! Furthermore we will have a trip to Cologne, Maastricht and a lot of places you WILL enjoy!<br />\nAnd of course there is this great event: the Unicup, the annual ice-hockey tournament at our University. Your job will be to cheer our teams to victory and you&#8217;ll see that in Aachen nothing is usual!</p>\n<p>Should you have any questions, feel free to contact me at any time!</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m just about to finish my third beer for today, so I really hope you will join me <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Martin<br />\nCP LC Aachen</p>\n<p>PS: beercounter++</p>\n', 'Niko Exchange', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'niko-exchange', '', '', '2011-09-30 17:04:54', '2011-09-30 16:04:54', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/niko-exchange/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2279, 1, '2011-09-24 20:54:07', '2011-09-24 19:54:07', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers out there,</p>\n<p>You’ve been nagging and complaining so much that you miss the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vh2HQYVYR64&amp;feature=player_embedded#%21" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Happy Shiny People</a> that we are and now here’s your result: EESTEC LC Bucharest is happy to announce its workshop “Business Engineering School”.</p>\n<p>&#8220;To be or not to be an entrepreneur ? That is the question!&#8221;<br />\nThe event offers a week of student conferences that will provide guidance in the entrepreneurship and business environment powered by experts in the field. The workshop addresses a large number of young engineers that are eager to professionally develop their entrepreneurial skills. What will you practically learn throughout the week? How to do your own Start Up, as an engineer. It’s yet another chance for us as EESTECers to prove the world that we do mean serious stuff and that we are all suit up and ready to take on the world. You will have the chance to meet people having experience in working with organizations worldwide, sharing their insights gained from research and practice of business in industry.</p>\n<p>Our mission is&#8230;..to make a difference</p>\n<p>We want to encourage engineering students to implement their technical ideas gained in the college years, and to provide you with skills, knowledge and networks in order to assist in realizing their potential.</p>\n<p>So, do not hesitate to apply. Even if this is an academic event, we promise you will have a great time. Visiting Bucharest and parties are on the schedule. And of course, you will have the chance to dance the Happy Shiny People dance again. We know it’s been a long time and maybe many of you have forgotten about it or maybe didn’t get the chance to learn it, but all is not lost! And for the lucky 15 of you that will take part in our event we have an extra-spoil: you will be attending, at the end of the Workshop, an amazing “just for you” weekend in the mountains! Beautiful scenery, maybe even a little snow if we’re lucky, and late night BBQs, LC Bucharest style <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  And with no curfew!! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Apply now!<br />\nSee you in Romania!</p>\n', 'Business Engineering School', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'business-engineering-school', '', '', '2011-09-24 20:54:07', '2011-09-24 19:54:07', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/business-engineering-school/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2280, 1, '2011-08-26 21:16:11', '2011-08-26 20:16:11', '\n<p>How many times have you watched what robot can do and asked yourself how all that works? Have you ever tried to program anything like that? Would you like to peek deeper into the robotic world?</p>\n<p>LC Novi Sad is more than happy to announce that our workshop, called &#8220;We are all cyborgs now&#8221; will be held from 23 &#8211; 30. 10. 2011. In that period our experts will teach you as much as possible about programming and robot itself. We will try to do various interesting things such as writing, drawing, montage etc. Understandingly, we would learn all of that through fun and game.</p>\n<p>So far, I can tell you that we&#8217;re planning a weekend in the nature and traditional cooking and making barbecue, City Rally, sightseeing, clubbing and much, much more. And I have to mention that this event is for the people who love to learn (we will implant a lot of knowledge in your brain), for the ones who love noise ( &#8217;cause in the hustle and bustle of the city, nothing is ever silent) and for the ones who have a lot of energy (cause you will definitely need it <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> ).</p>\n<p>We are sure you will bring home a lot of great memories because Novi Sad will definitely make you feel awesome.</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is: 23. 09. 2011.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SOESSCXGhFo" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SOESSCXGhFo </a></p>\n', 'We are all cyborgs now', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'we-are-all-cyborgs-now', '', '', '2011-08-26 21:16:11', '2011-08-26 20:16:11', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/we-are-all-cyborgs-now/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2281, 1, '2011-08-11 08:26:01', '2011-08-11 07:26:01', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich/Awesome is proud to announce the 2011 Oktoberfest Exchange from<br />\nSeptember 20th until September 26th.<br />\nYou will have the honor of drinking the world&#8217;s finest beer in the world&#8217;s<br />\nfinest city with the most sophisticated soon-to-be engineers in Europe.</p>\n<p>Besides all these tempting facts we are also planning a cultural program, a<br />\nCity-Rally, sightseeing, and clubbing. There won&#8217;t be any lectures, however<br />\nplenty of entertainment during your stay in Munich is guaranteed.</p>\n<p>Since hostel prices are ridiculous during Oktoberfest, we will be<br />\naccommodating you privately. Unfortunately we have to ask for a participation<br />\nfee of 60€. This includes meals and local transportation. We have to warn you<br />\nthough, Munich is generally an expensive place during Oktoberfest. A liter of<br />\nbeer is 8.70€! But as usual, everything except for drinks is included for our<br />\nparticipants. No need to worry, we will not be spending the entire week at<br />\nOktoberfest itself, and you will have a lot of chances to get cheaper beer! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /><br />\nThis is a once in a lifetime chance to experience Oktoberfest at such<br />\naffordable prices!</p>\n<p>This year we will be able to host 11-13 participants.</p>\n<p>Again, this is the opportunity of your life to enjoy the world&#8217;s biggest beer<br />\nfestival (and party) with your fellow EESTECers! We strongly encourage you to<br />\napply! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>The deadline to apply for this awesome event is Saturday August 20th.</p>\n<p>P.S. Loving beer is a must <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Cheers,</p>\n', 'Oktoberfest Exchange 2011', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'oktoberfest-exchange-2011', '', '', '2011-08-11 08:26:01', '2011-08-11 07:26:01', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/oktoberfest-exchange-2011/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2282, 1, '2011-08-10 18:54:04', '2011-08-10 17:54:04', '\n<p>Dear EESTEC-ers,</p>\n<p>On behalf of the Grant Team and LC Belgrade we are glad to inform you that the <strong>1st Grant Team Operational Conference &#8211; GToc</strong> is coming to life this <strong>August 16th-22rd 2011 in Belgrade</strong>.</p>\n<p>This International Event is the <strong>first official event of EESTEC Grant Team (GT)</strong> that became an official EESTEC Body during last EESTEC Congress in Craiova.</p>\n<p>In the past year, which was the first pilot year of action for the GT, a lot of progress was made and the results were very promising. Now, it is time for the Grant Team to expand and get more members from various LCs to continue the work of the previous year and open up to road to its future. In short, the Grant Team needs motivated people that want to get involved with the rather tricky, but highly rewarding area of grants. In short, the Grant Team needs YOU! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>During this event, participants will be introduced to the actions of the Grant Team, the various grants EESTEC can benefit from and the more technical details of these grants. In addition, the participants will be given the opportunity to become junior members of the Grant Team, since GToc is the only official method of becoming part of the Grant Team.</p>\n<p>As can be understood, there will be some serious work done during the event to ensure the work quality of GT for the years to come and to assist all of EESTEC in  getting funding for its events.</p>\n<p>BUT let&#8217;s not forget the fun part! It IS going to be in beautiful Belgrade after all <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /><br />\nLC Belgrade will host the event and show everyone the crazy EESTEC spirit that makes every event in Belgrade an amazing experience!</p>\n<p>A morning of sightseeing and many crazy evening parties in the never-sleeping capital of Serbia will make up for all your hard work!<br />\nAnd of course, the Belgrade Beerfest (August 17th-21st) is no coincidence! It will fuel our inspiration and creativity to its MAX <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>So all of you interested in getting involved with the Grant Team and experiencing the incredible team spirit within make sure to <strong>apply before July 24th 2011 23.59</strong>.<br />\nA <strong>Motivational Letter</strong> with any past experience you may have with grants and the reasons for your interest in the Grant Team will also be needed to let us know why you would like to join the awesome Grant Team <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /><br />\nThe selection of participants will be made jointly by the Grant Team and the International Board to ensure the proper continuation of the Grant Team.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget, the Grant Team has as one of its primary goals to educate EESTEC members, so do not hesitate to apply even if your former grant experience is minimal. <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>On behalf of the Grant Team,<br />\nBest Regards,<br />\nSotiris Stasinopoulos</p>\n', 'Grant Team operational conference &#8211; GToc', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'grant-team-operational-conference-gtoc', '', '', '2011-08-10 18:54:04', '2011-08-10 17:54:04', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/grant-team-operational-conference-gtoc/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2283, 1, '2011-08-09 19:03:52', '2011-08-09 18:03:52', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>There is over a year now since the last Training for Trainers was organized and the time is coming for the 4th Training for Trainers – &#8220;T4T&#8221;.</p>\n<p>As you could see, this year LC Maribor will be the organizing LC and together with the Training Team everything will be done in order to prepare the best T4T till now!</p>\n<p><strong>What is the EESTEC Training Team? What are Trainings?</strong></p>\n<p>EESTEC Training Team is an official EESTEC body which is providing different services for EESTEC and through those services, based on trainings, constantly improving the work of EESTEC on international and local levels!</p>\n<p>Main goal of trainings is transfer of knowledge in an advanced way through different activities, techniques and methodologies.</p>\n<p>More information about the Training Team, Training System and Trainings you can find in the Official Training Team Document here.</p>\n<p><strong>What is T4T? Why is T4T being organized?</strong></p>\n<p>T4T – Training for Trainers is an international training event whose purpose is gaining new EESTEC trainers and it is the starting point for EESTECers to become a trainer.</p>\n<p>EESTECers which participate in T4T will go through intensive trainings, working sessions and practical parts and learn how to transfer knowledge, which methodologies to use and, very important, how to deliver trainings!</p>\n<p>As the transfer of knowledge is crucial for EESTEC, T4T is an event which assures new generations to continue with developing and providing Training Team services to EESTEC members. It is a stage through all Training team members have to go in order to gain different  soft skills like: leadership skills, presentation skills, communication skills and much more!</p>\n<p>Using these skills for transferring knowledge in EESTEC provides greater quality of different activities which are being organized in International and local levels.</p>\n<p>During T4T, 9 days of a lot of work is waiting for you so you will need to bring <strong>a lot of positive energy</strong> and <strong>enthusiasm</strong> in order to be effective all the time and to be able to endure the T4T.</p>\n<p><strong>Why become a Trainer? Why should you apply?</strong></p>\n<p>There are definitely a lot of reasons to apply. Becoming a trainer gives you an opportunity to contribute to EESTEC International, to contribute to LCs and to contribute to yourselves!</p>\n<p>As a trainer candidate (and optionally trainer) you will work in and create a positive atmosphere during T4T and after. If you become a trainer (for what you need to fulfill certain tasks) you will work on the transfer of knowledge to other EESTECers and you will have an opportunity to improve on personal level in different aspects.</p>\n<p>The skills you gain while being a trainer are needed in all aspects of life today and so in EESTEC. Because of that, members who participate in T4T have a big opportunity to develop themselves and to give a great contribution to the development of EESTEC!</p>\n<p><strong>Fun part <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </strong></p>\n<p>T4T is a hardworking event but there is no event in EESTEC which doesn&#8217;t provide a lot of great atmosphere and fun!</p>\n<p>Organizers from LC Maribor, together with trainers, will do their best to prepare great mood and different social activities for participants <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>As always you will meet great people from all around the world, enjoy great parties and enjoy in a beautiful city &#8211; Maribor!</p>\n<p>All this combined with effective work and personal development is surely an event which you will never forget!</p>\n<p>If you are an experienced EESTECer, if you participated in trainings, if you want to become a trainer, if you want to develop yourself and EESTEC or if you think that you could become a trainer &#8211; apply!</p>\n<p>All now is left is to fill the application form which you can find on the next <a href="http://goo.gl/VzMiw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://goo.gl\']);" target="_blank">link</a> and to send it to</p>\n<p><a href="mailto:trainings-coordinator@eestec.net" target="_blank">trainings-coordinator@eestec.net</a> !</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>The deadline for applications is 4th of August 2011.</strong></span></p>\n<p>I will be glad to answer any questions and you feel free to ask anything you have on your mind <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>We hope to see a lot of applications! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Best regards and enjoy!</p>\n<p>On behalf of LC Maribor and Training Team,</p>\n<p>Nermin Smajić</p>\n<p>EESTEC International Training Team Coordinator</p>\n', 'T4T 2011', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 't4t-2011', '', '', '2011-08-09 19:03:52', '2011-08-09 18:03:52', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/t4t-2011/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2284, 1, '2011-07-10 13:24:40', '2011-07-10 12:24:40', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Do you want to spend the end of summer time at the best possible way? Do you want to have fun 24/7? Do you want to experience wild beauty and enjoy in it?</p>\n<p>Then, don&#8217;t wait! LC Podgorica is happy to present you ‘’Montenegro Summer Exchange’’. We promise you a lot of great food and parties, as well as beach parties. There will be 7 days of an unforgettable atmosphere , 7 days of EESTEC spirit and of course 7 nights of crazy fun at our parties we are preparing for you!</p>\n<p>Fun will start in our capital city &#8211; Podgorica. Than you&#8217;ll visit re-desovered paradise of our country. Don&#8217;t forget to pack your sunglasses, bikini, shorts and skirts because Mediterranean spirit is waitng for you. For nature lovers we&#8217;ll organize visit to the <a href="http://www.discover-montenegro.com/Lovcen%20and%20Mausoleum%20Slideshow/index.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.discover-montenegro.com\']);" target="_blank">National park Lovćen and Njegoš mausoleum</a> on top of the mounatin Lovćen (1657 meters above the sea level). After that, EESTEC spirit will shake one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast – <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RlbgebQtCgk&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">Kotor</a>. You will have opportunity to experience last night of <a href="http://www.kotorkarneval.me/eng/eng.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.kotorkarneval.me\']);" target="_blank">Kotor Carnival</a>. We will organize cruise around Boka bay, and organize many day and night parties <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  Also, you will see the pearl of Mediterranean – city of Budva.</p>\n<p>This event will also have an educational part, as we all know the importance of Soft Skills. We will organize trainings on some of most important topics of Soft Skills.</p>\n<p>We are sure you&#8217;ll leave here with memories you&#8217;ll never forget! You only have to bring all of your EESTEC spirit with you!</p>\n<p>Montenegro is calling, holiday is rolling!</p>\n', 'Montenegro Summer Exchange &#8217;11', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'montenegro-summer-exchange-11', '', '', '2011-07-10 13:24:40', '2011-07-10 12:24:40', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/montenegro-summer-exchange-11/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2285, 1, '2011-06-26 14:00:16', '2011-06-26 13:00:16', '\n<p>We are proud to say that our event “JAZZ DO IT!” is becoming tradition.<br />\nSince it was great last year, we have decided to do it again! That&#8217;s why<br />\nwe are inviting you to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and<br />\nEastern Europe &#8220;<a href="http://www.nisville.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.nisville.com\']);" target="_blank">Nišville jazz festival</a>&#8220;. Together we will enjoy the good<br />\njazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchange<br />\ncan provide. Organized in the <a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://img704.imageshack.us\']);" target="_blank">medieval fortress</a> and visited by more than<br />\n100.000 people only last year, Nišville hosted some of the biggest stars<br />\nof jazz music: Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke,<br />\nBenny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove&#8230; This year there is no exception<br />\nbecause Steve Hans Dulfer, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell, Rick<br />\nMargitza and 50 other bands on 5 different stages will jazz it up for us!</p>\n<p>Regular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you<br />\nare getting it for free <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>And you will also learn some things about acoustics and making music.</p>\n<p>But, that’s not all. The City of Niš has great cultural and historical<br />\nheritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most<br />\nimportant persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>,<br />\nwas born in Niš (roman name NAISSUS) in 272 AD.</p>\n<p>You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niš_Fortress" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Fortress of Niš</a>, where “Nišville jazz festival”<br />\ntakes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years,<br />\nand has layers from different historical periods. That’s because Niš is<br />\non the road that connects Europe with Middle East (in roman times this<br />\nroad was called VIA MILITARIS), so many civilizations passed here and<br />\nthey left some trace in the fortress. It’s in this condition since XVII<br />\ncentury, and now it’s one of the best preserved fortifications of<br />\nOttoman style in Europe.</p>\n<p>In Niš exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was<br />\nbuilt from skulls of the warriors who died in the Čegar battle in the<br />\n1809. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Čegar" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);" target="_blank">Čegar monument</a> where this battle took place.</p>\n<p>We’ll show you one relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.nistourism.org.rs\']);" target="_blank">Niška Banja</a> spa which has radioactive<br />\nhealing water and we’ll go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!</p>\n<p>And if you think that we only have history, you’re wrong, because Niš is<br />\nknown as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old<br />\nhedonist legacy! Are you brave enough to try our traditional drink<br />\nrakija? And the best BBQ in the world including pljeskavica will help<br />\nyour body to work well with all that alcohol. There won’t be a single<br />\nmoment that you’ll be hungry, because Serbians like good food in big<br />\nquantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient<br />\nat the special night in kafana. If you don’t know what merak is (that<br />\nword has no translation to other languages), you will learn here!</p>\n<p>So the crazy summer cocktail with&#8230; traditional Serbian drinks and<br />\nfood… plenty of great music… nice town… a lot of EESTEC spirit… Mix all<br />\nthat in a summer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?</p>\n<p><a href="http://img404.imageshack.us/img404/5156/jazzdoitcopy.jpg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://img404.imageshack.us\']);" target="_blank">Jazz do it! 2011. </a></p>\n', 'JAZZ DO IT!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'jazz-do-it', '', '', '2011-06-26 14:00:16', '2011-06-26 13:00:16', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/jazz-do-it/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2286, 1, '2011-05-31 21:28:51', '2011-05-31 20:28:51', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Tuzla is proud to present you our new and first workshop for the 2011!</p>\n<p>Our workshop is called <strong>IPTV &#8211; The Next Generation TV</strong> and here is a summary of it, small clarification for the topic that we chose for our event and for you, our dearest participants. We hope you will find it interesting and that you&#8217; ll apply.</p>\n<p>We all watch TV, right? Have you ever asked yourself how, everything you see, actually comes to your TV screens? In how many ways it can be done and etc.?<br />\nWell, if you have, here is a great opportunity for you to get those answers .</p>\n<p>IPTV is defined as the secure and reliable delivery to subscribers of entertainment video and related services. These services may include, for example, Live TV, Video On Demand (VOD) and Interactive TV (iTV). These services are delivered across an acces agnostic, packet switched network that employs the IP protocol to transport the audio, video and control signals. In contrast to video over the public Internet, with IPTV deployments, network security and performance are tightly managed to ensure a superior entertainment experience, resulting in a compelling business environment for content providers, advertisers and customers alike.</p>\n<p><strong>Waaaaaaaaaiitttttt, waaiiittt &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>don&#8217;t click on the cLoSe button so soon =)</strong></p>\n<p>We also have even more interesting things to tell you about our workshop. First, you will have the chance to see <strong>Europe&#8217;s only salt lake</strong> as part of Tuzlas central park which has around 100,000 people visiting its shores every year. Second, we will do all kind of crazy things like <strong>rafting, paintball</strong> etc. And last but not least Bosnia is famous for its <strong>great food and drinks</strong> and you will get a lot of that in Tuzla for sure.<br />\nJust for you to know, we prepared one hell of a fun week that you don&#8217;t want to miss, trust us.<br />\nPrepare yourselves for a lot of other truly interesting stuff that we have for ya&#8217; .</p>\n<p><strong>Deadline for applying is 19.06.2011.</strong></p>\n<p>The official website of our workshop is: <a href="http://www.iptv.eestec-tz.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.iptv.eestec-tz.ba\']);" target="_blank">www.iptv.eestec-tz.ba</a><br />\nIf you have any questions, feel free to contact me on <a href="mailto:cp.tuzla@gmail.com" target="_blank">cp.tuzla@gmail.com</a>. I&#8217;ll be pleased to answer.</p>\n<p><strong>BRING GREAT MOOD, EESTEC FIRE AND EESTEC SPIRIT WITH YOU AND YOU ARE ALL WELCOME <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\' alt=\':D\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </strong></p>\n', 'IPTV &#8211; The Next Generation TV', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'iptv-the-next-generation-tv', '', '', '2011-05-31 21:28:51', '2011-05-31 20:28:51', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/iptv-the-next-generation-tv/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2287, 1, '2011-05-31 19:34:18', '2011-05-31 18:34:18', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>After great success in organizing Trainers Meeting in October 2010, LC Banja Luka is honored to present our next workshop called <strong>Let the penguin in</strong>!, that will be held from 23.07 – 29.07.2011.</p>\n<p>Topic of our workshop is <strong>virtualization</strong>. You will learn about major problems and development of this framework, implementation, purpose &#8211; server consolidation, load balancing, security, types of virtualization and concepts used alongside. Academic part will include interesting lectures from experienced teachers from the field and hands-on labs on GNU/Linux distribution – Debian.</p>\n<p>This week will be incredibly exciting because of three things:</p>\n<p>1. International Debian Conference – this year <strong>DebCon11</strong> will be held in Banja Luka. We will use this opportunity to introduce you to Debian distribution and go to Debian Day. There you will listen to experts from this field. You can find more about this conference on <a href="http://www.debconf.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.debconf.org\']);" target="_blank">http://www.debconf.org/</a></p>\n<p>2. This will be the most exciting week in Banja Luka because 4th <strong>Demofest</strong> festival is going to be held at the same time! Demofest is festival and competition of young demo bands from all over the Balkan. This year 438 bands applied and only 30 will get the chance to compete. Also, you will listen to Tricky’s, Kelis’ and Skindread’s concerts (type of music: rock, metal, punk, reggae).</p>\n<p>Read more about Demofest on <a href="http://www.demofest.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.demofest.org\']);" target="_blank">http://www.demofest.org/</a></p>\n<p>3. Our workshop J As always we promise you a lot of <strong>great food</strong> and <strong>crazy parties</strong>. We won’t miss the chance to take you to <strong>best RAFTING in the world</strong>, on one of the world’s best rivers for this kind of sport (there were European Championship 2005, Euro Cup 2007, World Championship 2009 in Banja Luka).</p>\n<p>There will be many more interesting things that you feel only when you are part of this event. Come and feel the beauty of summer in the city on Vrbas!</p>\n<p>We are waiting for you applications and hope to see you in Banja Luka!!</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, contact our CP Marija Racic at: <a href="mailto:elmaars@gmail.com" target="_blank">marija.racicc@gmail.com</a></p>\n', 'Let the penguin IN', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'let-the-penguin-in', '', '', '2011-05-31 19:34:18', '2011-05-31 18:34:18', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/let-the-penguin-in/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2288, 1, '2011-05-27 21:15:01', '2011-05-27 20:15:01', '\n<p>Hello my dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>LC Rijeka is again organizing the traditional summer exchange RiSEx 2011 in period 19.7-25.7.2011. Just like every year, we guarantee you a lot of fun, sun and the beach. Among all things, we have organized you an attractive trip, cruise with the tourist boat in the Kvarner bay, parties on the beach, crazy city relly, visit to Opatija, one of the most beautiful cities at the nothern Adriatic Sea, and many, many more.</p>\n<p>It is very easy to find us. You can travel to here by train, over Zagreb or Ljubljana, by car, bus (driving on new and high quality highways), or by plane via one of the nearby airports (Zagreb, Ljubljana, Venezia). Do not hesistate one single moment, but start slowly with packing the sunscreen in your bag and we are waiting for your applications. This year we are accepting 20 participants. See you in Rijeka. We are looking forward to your arrival.</p>\n<p>P.S. For all of you who need a little more persuation to sign up, we decided to post this video clip, &#8217;cause all you know a picture is worth thousand words <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QIiYY9jRnCw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QIiYY9jRnCw</a></p>\n', 'Rijeka Summer Exchange 2011', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rijeka-summer-exchange-2011', '', '', '2011-05-27 21:15:01', '2011-05-27 20:15:01', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/rijeka-summer-exchange-2011/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2289, 1, '2011-05-24 09:14:40', '2011-05-24 08:14:40', '\n<p><strong>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that eMovie Academy is becoming a tradition, and it&#8217;s your chance to make your dreams come true <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  7 days of glamour on one of the biggest European movie festivals, 7 days of an unforgettable atmosphere which one awesome LC will provide for you, 7 days of pure EESTEC spirit, 7 nights of crazy fun and a lot more! Deadline for applying is 15.06.2011. Don&#8217;t miss it!</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>How many times have you watched movie stars on the red carpet and wished to be one of them? You watch reports about film festivals on TV and you think you&#8217;ll never be able to be part of that world? Ever wanted to try to be an actor, screenwriter, producer or editor of a movie?</p>\n<p>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that <strong>eMovie Academy</strong> is becoming a tradition, and it&#8217;s your chance to make your dreams come true <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> . 7 days of glamour on one of the biggest European movie festivals, 7 days of an unforgettable atmosphere which one awesome LC will provide for you, 7 days of pure EESTEC spirit, 7 nights of crazy fun and a lot more!</p>\n<p>The academical part of the event will consist of lectures about movies, editing, and filming. You will learn about editing a movie in professional software tools. Lectures are going to be held by experienced people in the movie domain, meaning that after them you&#8217;ll be able to (and you will) make your own movie <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> .</p>\n<p>In the period from 22.07. until 29.07. Sarajevo becomes overflowed with people, visited by famous actors and movie lovers from many countries. This is the period of one of the most respected movie festivals in Europe &#8211; the Sarajevo Film Festival (<a href="http://www.sff.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.sff.ba\']);" target="_blank">www.sff.ba</a>). During these days Sarajevo lives 24/7, and we will make sure that you feel it from first hand experience through unforgettable nights, parties, people, and also by arranging accommodation at the center of the city.</p>\n<p>We will also present you cultural beauties of Sarajevo, the place where West and East meet, the diversity of our delicious food (like ćevapi, burek, baklava&#8230;), our natural wealth and our cultural and historical heritage&#8230;</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>15.06.2011</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The official website of eMovie Academy is already online: <a href="http://www.ema.eestec-sa.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.ema.eestec-sa.ba\']);" target="_blank">www.ema.eestec-sa.ba</a>.</p>\n<p>You can find more information about Sarajevo on:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.sarajevo.ba\']);" target="_blank">www.sarajevo.ba</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com\']);" target="_blank">www.sarajevo-tourism.com</a></p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact me on <a href="mailto:elmica.bh@gmail.com" target="_blank">elmica.bh@gmail.com</a>. I&#8217;ll be pleased to answer.</p>\n<p>So, don&#8217;t hesitate and apply now for the greatest fun you&#8217;ll have this summer!</p>\n<p>Can&#8217;t wait to see you all soon in the capital of The Heart-shaped Land!</p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'eMovie Academy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'emovie-academy', '', '', '2011-05-24 09:14:40', '2011-05-24 08:14:40', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/emovie-academy/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2290, 1, '2011-05-05 19:13:32', '2011-05-05 18:13:32', '\n<p>Dear EESTECER&#8217;s ;</p>\n<p>We proud to announce that our first Workshop,&#8221; Don&#8217;t hate it, Just do it!!&#8221; will be held</p>\n<p>on 5th-11th September 2011. Excellent city will have legendary Workshop!!</p>\n<p>In Turkey, electromagnetism and microwave topics are the most hated subjects . We</p>\n<p>thought that topics are not a big deal, we can handle them and we decide to do it &#8221; Don&#8217;t hate it, Just</p>\n<p>do it!!&#8221;. During Workshop we will learn what dipole antenna is and how we can build it. We will</p>\n<p>participate sessions about microwave and electromagnetism.</p>\n<p>I can hear that you are asking about social activities. We have great activities for you!</p>\n<p>We will have a boat trip for a day, beautiful bays, islands, sun and fun! Another day we will visit</p>\n<p>ancient Ephesus city and an old village which is Şirince, the village of vines!! and there is one more</p>\n<p>activity which is a big suprise for you!! Don&#8217;t forget to bring your swimming stuff</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry about parties because you will learn that what party really is.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t wait, let&#8217;s do it! Just Apply!!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Big Hugs from JLC İzmir!!</p>\n', 'Don&#8217;t Hate it, Just Do it!!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dont-hate-it-just-do-it', '', '', '2011-05-05 19:13:32', '2011-05-05 18:13:32', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/dont-hate-it-just-do-it/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2291, 1, '2011-04-30 17:04:06', '2011-04-30 16:04:06', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Do you know what a midsummer fest is? Do you know how it is celebrated in Latvia?</p>\n<p>The best way to find it out is to join real midsummer fest in Latvia. LC Riga is proud to present you our newest exchange “When the night meets day”. It will take place in Latvia from 22nd till 26th June.</p>\n<p>We want to show you how we Latvians celebrate our biggest fest all over the country.</p>\n<p>The first days and last we will spend discovering the beautiful city of Riga, located on the confluence of the river Daugava and at seaside. The participants will learn about the Latvian culture through sightseeing, enjoying the cuisine, seeing the nightlife and admiring city in the evening.</p>\n<p>And there are some reasons why you should come:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>to learn  from other students and share your knowledge, experiences, thoughts and ideas with the best EESTEC students.</li>\n<li>to take a look at the best technical university in Latvia- RTU, and see what student life is like here</li>\n<li>to see Latvia- small and beautiful country that just few years ago stepped into the EU</li>\n<li>to enjoy the capital of Latvia- Riga</li>\n<li>to practice and share your English skills and also learn some Latvian words and traditions</li>\n<li>to make unforgettable friends from different countries</li>\n<li>to have fun <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  -&gt; lots of fun!!!  :)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We can assure you that this will be unforgettable. So pack you summer clothing, ‘cause Latvia is waiting for you!</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>LC Riga <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </strong></p>\n', 'When night meets day', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'when-night-meets-day', '', '', '2011-04-30 17:04:06', '2011-04-30 16:04:06', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/when-night-meets-day/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2292, 1, '2011-04-07 20:39:05', '2011-04-07 19:39:05', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,<br />\nas you all must already know, we make awesome events (if you haven&#8217;t heard, just ask anybody who&#8217;s been to Zagreb!), and we know you have been waiting to apply to our next one <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  Well, the opportunity to come to Zagreb is finally here, and if you haven&#8217;t yet decided are you coming, read the rest of our invitation!</p>\n<p>This year&#8217;s theme will be <strong>&#8220;Modern Telecomunications: Linking people everywhere!&#8221;</strong> or as we like to call it <strong>&#8220;Kinky Linky&#8221;</strong> <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif\' alt=\':P\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  You will have several very interesting classes held by young professors from our telecommunications department, and some insight on how it looks like in reality, from a real company, so even the academic part will be fun!</p>\n<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">What else we&#8217;ve got you&#8217;re wondering? </span></em>OK, if you haven&#8217;t heard about wonderful Croatian nature you are really missing a lot! Google it and look at the pictures&#8230;[5 minutes later]You must be interested now <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We will show you some beautiful sights on our field trips and that is not all, &#8217;cause you also get to experience the Croatian culture and not to mention our awesome food and drinks!<br />\nYou will definitely not leave hungry or thirsty, but you will be eager to come back to taste Croatia again <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">You&#8217;re asking yourselves what about the real memorable having fun part which everyone forgets because of too much alcohol?</span></em><br />\nNow that&#8217;s our strongest card, so don&#8217;t come tired or wanting to rest, we are not going to allow that,<br />\n<strong>you ARE going to party every day and it IS going to be  legen&#8230;dary <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </strong> Word.</p>\n<p>It doesn&#8217;t matter where we take you, we will make your time here unforgettable, so come and meet us,<br />\nit will be a great spring week for you, we guarantee it!!<br />\nStart packing, we are waiting for you, and remember, wine is fine but whiskey is quicker!</p>\n<p>LC Zagreb <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Modern Telecomunications: Linking people everywhere!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'modern-telecomunications-linking-people-everywhere', '', '', '2011-04-07 20:39:05', '2011-04-07 19:39:05', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/modern-telecomunications-linking-people-everywhere/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2293, 1, '2011-04-01 17:39:53', '2011-04-01 16:39:53', '\n<p>Dear EESTEC-ers,</p>\n<p>We LC Skopje are delighted to announce you that we are organizing something special – the workshop &#8220;Feel the Energy 2&#8243;. We invite you to explore the possibilities of the renewable energy sources and the wittiness of the self sustainable philosophy. Besides the energy we intend to create some unforgettable memories while round tripping our small but beautiful country from 1st till 8th May.</p>\n<p>We have arranged a mix of experts – finest selection of professors, experts from the industry and members of the Macedonian Academy of Science and Arts.<br />\nPrepare your diving suits because we are going to dive in the world of renewables. From our starting point the “Global trends”, we will dive in the &#8211; ”How to create energetic strategy” lecture to get to the cliff called “Investments in renewables” and “Energetic world trends ”. Lots of corrals and pearls by the coast are guaranteed like visiting: solar farm, Biogas factory and hydro plant with high end automation.</p>\n<p>We intend to light up the Skopje nightlife with our glossy parties, so we have prepared some fuel for your alcohol driven generators. But read carefully, you will need to do the wiring, and we don’t have user manuals. And hey, did somebody mention clubbing, wine tasting and enjoying different meals and drinks during the international night?<br />\nShhhh, that supposed to be a secret. But it’s not a secret that you will feel the undying vibe of Macedonian tradition while visiting a traditional restaurant where archaic Macedonian songs and dances are performed by musical masters.</p>\n<p>And that is not all! At the end of the “4 day knowledge-gaining” marathon you may feel that your batteries are quite low&#8230; But don’t worry!  ! You&#8217;ll surely recharge the energy during the amazing weekend. How? LC Skopje is organizing a tour to the most gorgeous and peaceful city in Macedonia – Ohrid. OK it would not be that peaceful once we arrive. You can walk by the shores of the Balkan pearl – the lake of Ohrid holding hands with your new friend. You will visit the breathtaking old part of the city and take a boat trip to the St. Naum’s Monastery and its wonderful area. The beautiful sunset by the two romantic little isles make this location attractive spot for the tourists and renewables experts too J. And for the party animals don’t forget the clubs that we will visit during the endless nights to suck that little crumb of energy you have left over <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for, come to Macedonia and feel the timeless energy that flows in this wonderful land&#8230;</p>\n<p>Apply now! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>In addition to help you to know at least a little about Ohrid and Macedonia<br />\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t_sOTaG3FP8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t_sOTaG3FP8</a></p>\n<p>Kind Regards and see you in Skopje,<br />\nFor more information feel free and ask me whenever you want. <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Feel the Energy 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'feel-the-energy-2', '', '', '2011-04-01 17:39:53', '2011-04-01 16:39:53', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/feel-the-energy-2/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2294, 1, '2011-04-01 17:07:55', '2011-04-01 16:07:55', '\n<p><strong>EESTEC GOT THE POWER!</strong></p>\n<p>LC Famagusta proudly presents Power Island where the participants will be able to fullfill the power of eeStec to every part of their bodies.</p>\n<p>The workshop will contain, sessions about the Industrial Usage of High Voltage as well as technical trips to Thermic Plants all around the island. During the workshop, participants will be able to discover the latest technology in our Technopark such as 3D laser printers, robotix and other new developments of our university labs and realize the island technology.</p>\n<p>Do we need to mention about Parties ? We will bring our participants to our spring fest where they will enjoy the 2003 Eurovision Song Contest Winner and 2009 MTV European Music Award Winner. We are inviting you over to share the great fun in our tropical campus with more than 15000 students including people from 68 different countries. Yacht Party, City Rally, Windsurfing, Karaoke Parties, Discos, Sea, Sun, Beach Parties, Beaches and Beaches&#8230; what else do you need?</p>\n<p>You will miss a lot if you miss this event, that&#8217;s for sure but you are already aware of that, aren&#8217;t you? <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Any hesitation would be greatly not accepted! We will be more than glad to answer your questions about anything.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VRJtyYVMeUg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VRJtyYVMeUg</a></p>\n', 'Power Island', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'power-island', '', '', '2011-04-01 17:07:55', '2011-04-01 16:07:55', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/power-island/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2295, 1, '2011-03-24 13:46:46', '2011-03-24 12:46:46', '\n<p>Dear fellow EESTECers,</p>\n<p>EESTEC LC Budapest (MAVE) in cooperation with Siemens Healthcare and the Budapest University of Technology and Economics proudly presents a week-long professional event in Budapest, a place where future is present!</p>\n<p>If you want to participate in the most medtech workshop in the history of EESTEC, get prepared now! Submit your scientific abstract following the guidelines in the form and send it with your application!</p>\n<p>Participants will have to present their field of research or studies relevant to CIS. Applications must include a fully filled Application form, including the 2-page abstract supporting the proposed presentation sent to <a href="mailto: cis2011@eestec.hu" target="_blank">cis2011@eestec.hu</a> by 22th May. Selection will be made based on scientific merit and geographic variety.</p>\n<p>What kind of presentation are we awaiting from you? Topics include (but are not limited to) medical robot systems, mechatronics and control, medical imaging, image processing and registration, treatment planning, image-guided surgery, patient, rehabilitation and assistive robotics, surgery and diagnosis.</p>\n<p>The academic program will take 5 days, including tutorials from professors visiting from all over the world; your presentation, university and Siemens labs tours. Hands-on minimally-invasive surgical training session will also be included.</p>\n<p>After the hardworking days, we will take a train to our beloved lake Velence, and have time to rest and enjoy the beautiful Hungarian summer on the beach.</p>\n<p>During this week, you will spend time not only with people from EESTEC but will get a chance to meet other student organizations: learn with IEEE plus EMSA, party with AEGEE and train with ESTIEM.</p>\n<p>We are eagerly waiting for your application!</p>\n<p>On behalf of all the organizers,<br />\n<strong>Adam Kovacs-Veres</strong><br />\nVice-chairman, LC Budapest</p>\n', 'Computer Integrated Surgery', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'computer-integrated-surgery', '', '', '2011-03-24 13:46:46', '2011-03-24 12:46:46', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/computer-integrated-surgery/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2296, 1, '2011-03-19 19:15:47', '2011-03-19 18:15:47', '\n<p>Dear Eestecers <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>We are happy to inform you that LC Athens organises a workshop during 21st &#8211; 29th May called &#8221;Dreamers Become Winners&#8221; !!!!</p>\n<p>The subject of this workshop will be entrepreunership &#8211; a concept which gets more and more important for youth in these crazy days of crisis.</p>\n<p>Best professors of our faculty will  hold lectures designed to catch your full attention<br />\nand through interactive learning you will finally run your own business and maybe become rich and famous?! one day..</p>\n<p>Moreover,we will have some trainings so that you will be able to obtain the appropriate so-called soft skills and also get acquaired with green energy and innovations which are the latest trend. You will also have the chance to practice those soft skills through real activities.</p>\n<p>Last but not least you will have the opportunity to see our facilities, laboratories and come in contact with students and professors of National Technical University of Athens.</p>\n<p>Is that all???? NOOOO?? What about the entertainment part!?</p>\n<p>You  will have the chance to..</p>\n<p>- spend a memorable week in lively Athens that you ll never ever forget..</p>\n<p>- visit some of the most interesting historical sights and museums  of Athens, including the brand new Acropolis Museum</p>\n<p>- participate in some really crazy and wild parties</p>\n<p>- visit an exotic greek island (Agkistri) for a day ,swim ,get tanned, have a great beach party and make your friends green with envy</p>\n<p>- strengthen your eestec spirit and make amazing new friends all over Europe</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?!!</p>\n<p>Just apply <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Athens will be all yours!!</p>\n<p>PS. As you may already know this workshop will be funded by the Youth in Action programme. So don&#8217;t forget that we will refund 70% of participants&#8217; travel cost! (for those who have sent us Part 3 document:</p>\n<p>Ankara, Banja Luka, Belgrade, Budapest, East Sarajevo, Istanbul, Krakow, Ljubljana, Madrid, Maribor, Munich, Novi Sad,Podgorica,Riga,Trieste &amp; Zurich !! )</p>\n', 'Dreamers Become Winners', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dreamers-become-winners', '', '', '2011-03-19 19:15:47', '2011-03-19 18:15:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/dreamers-become-winners/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2297, 1, '2011-02-19 17:07:07', '2011-02-19 16:07:07', '\n<p>Fellow EESTECers!</p>\n<p>LC Kraków is more than just happy to announce third edition of workshop on IT Security &#8211; “KrakYourNet3”. This year our flag event will be held between 10th and 16th of April 2011, in Kraków, the jewel of polish cities and Zakopane, magnificent gate to Tatra Mountains and Tatra National Park. We have put our effort on educational part of the event. Our aim is to provide best lecturers and lectures to be as much consolidated as they can be. Of course to leave more time for our dear participants to party and see our beautiful country!</p>\n<p>If you are interested in IT and always aware of your safety in the net this event is for you! You will get the tools to stay safe and you will see how your on-line security is threatened in so many various ways&#8230; On the other hand if you do not have a clue about Internet security this event will open your eyes and give you a candle in the darkness of nowadays chambers of IT!</p>\n<p>Last but not least we have prepared awesome activities to keep you busy with parties, sightseeing and simply having fun all the time you are not at the lectures. I do not count sleeping time, cause there will be none! You will have opportunity to see Kraków, medieval city of polish kings and Zakopane, village in Tatra Mountains where we will go for excursion. To sum up: hiking, grilling, sightseeing, partying, no sleeping and more.</p>\n<p>Everyones invited! Apply, come, meet us, learn something about IT, see Kraków and party wildly with us!!!</p>\n', 'KrakYourNet3', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'krakyournet3', '', '', '2011-02-19 17:07:07', '2011-02-19 16:07:07', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/krakyournet3/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2298, 1, '2011-02-19 15:42:33', '2011-02-19 14:42:33', '\n<p>Search engines are the main instruments used for seeking information on the web. They have been subject to deep changes, such as the web, and for this reason LC Cosenza is pleased to announce that a workshop, whose title is &#8220;Search Engines: Indexing, Optimization And Marketing from Web 2.0 to Social Networks&#8221;, is taking place from May 16 to May 23. Deadline: April 16, 2011.</p>\n<p>The topics, which will be discussed, concern with the indexing techniques used to find out new e-contents, and SEO experts will be helping us to deepen optimization techniques to be adopted to improve web sites, blogs and extra resources presentations.</p>\n<p>Moreover, some marketing instruments provided from search engines will be introduced and compared to unconventional marketing techniques, taking into account the importance of social networks.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, you will be offered our warm Italian hospitality as well as funny times and parties.</p>\n<p>SEO, SEF, SEM, #HashTag and other keywords are waiting for you!!!</p>\n', 'Search Engines: Indexing, Optimization And Marketing from Web 2.0 to Social Networks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'search-engines-indexing-optimization-and-marketing-from-web-2-0-to-social-networks', '', '', '2011-02-19 15:42:33', '2011-02-19 14:42:33', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/search-engines-indexing-optimization-and-marketing-from-web-2-0-to-social-networks/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2299, 1, '2011-01-29 07:39:47', '2011-01-29 06:39:47', '\n<p>Hello my dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>This year again we are organizing &#8220;Rijeka Carnival Exchange 2011&#8243;. Rijeka&#8217;s Carnival has imposed to our city, region and Croatia like the fifth season &#8211; time of craziness and relaxation, and its rich entertainment, sports and cultural programs had satisfied all ages and tastes. Defiant to space and time, Carnival in a warm host to every person of good will who search escape from the gloomy everyday in the game, laughter, fun and vine <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  . LC Rijeka is again participating in main Carnival event as TNT dynamites (<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wn7ZGZn_sFw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wn7ZGZn_sFw</a>). The application form is in upper link.</p>\n<p>See you in Rijeka. Bye!</p>\n', 'Rijeka Carnival Exchange 2011', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rijeka-carnival-exchange-2011', '', '', '2011-01-29 07:39:47', '2011-01-29 06:39:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/rijeka-carnival-exchange-2011/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2300, 1, '2011-01-26 10:30:12', '2011-01-26 09:30:12', '\n<p>The event is organized in form of workshop with set of lectures followed by labs. The main focus is on developing Android applications. The entertainment part of the event is based on Rabadan Carnival in Bellinzona  (<a href="http://www.rabadan.ch/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.rabadan.ch\']);" target="_blank">http://www.rabadan.ch</a>), this is the most famous and the craziest event in Switzerland. We would kindly ask all the participants to bring carnival masks in order not to feel stupid there <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  Guided tours around beautiful Lugano lake are foreseen as well. Optionally skiing and chocolate museum visit are offered.</p>\n<p>We hope you will go back home with an unforgeable experience and a fancy (hopefully commercially exploitive) Android application that will change your lives and the world <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> )</p>\n<p>Location: <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Lugano,+Switzerland&amp;aq=0&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=55.411532,79.013672&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=Lugano,+Ticino,+Switzerland&amp;t=h&amp;z=13&amp;iwloc=A" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://maps.google.com\']);" target="_blank">Lugano, Switzerland</a></p>\n<p>More information on Lugano you may find at <a href="http://www.lugano-tourism.ch/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.lugano-tourism.ch\']);" target="_blank">http://www.lugano-tourism.ch</a></p>\n<p>We are eagerly waiting your applications!</p>\n<p>EESTEC LC Lugano</p>\n', 'Lugano goes mobile!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'lugano-goes-mobile', '', '', '2011-01-26 10:30:12', '2011-01-26 09:30:12', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/lugano-goes-mobile/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2301, 1, '2011-01-24 20:02:30', '2011-01-24 19:02:30', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers;</p>\n<p>LC Istanbul is happy and proud to announce our upcoming workshop “<strong>MANAGINATION’11</strong>”  (Management and Imagination ) which will be held on 6 &#8211; 13 March 2011, in Istanbul, Turkey. We have prepared you a fantastic event with the main subject project management and innovation.</p>\n<p>Have you ever wanted to be a leader? You have to organize some projects but there are lots of problems around you to solve? You take responsibilities but there is less time than you need?  Then, this event is for you because we prepared to give the secrets of these problems during seminars, presentations and trainings.  The aim of our event is improve your hidden talents and help you to have a good business career. On the other hand, we also want to show you how is important the creativity for an engineer.  The way of getting out the steps easily will be shared with our lucky participants by experienced trainers of world-famous companies.</p>\n<p>Do you think that we’ve forgotten the best part of our event? We have to confess; making extraordinary parties, knocking around and make people crazy is more and more easy for us when you compare with the academic part : )) You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population ; however,  you ‘ll have an unforgettable 7 days without doubt. Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places and nightlife of course <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':-)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  This city has become the capital of 3 biggest empires of the history (Roman, Byzantium and Ottoman). So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and richness it includes. We are going to take you to Topkapi and Dolmabahce Palaces where the Ottoman Sultans resided, the Hagia Sophia Museum from the 6th century, the Blue Mosque, Basilica Cistern and some more surprise places. Participants will also have the chance to watch both Asian and European Part from the middle of the Marmara sea when we are making Bosphorus Tour as usual. And the parties will be held in Istiklal Avenue which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see.</p>\n<p>Are you still waiting to apply ?  ? LC ISTANBUL is ready for you ! ! =)</p>\n<p>For more information feel free and ask me whenever you want. Our website (<a href="http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr\']);" target="_blank">www.eestec.itu.edu.tr</a>) will be update soon.</p>\n<p>In addition; to help you to know at least a little about Istanbul <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ&amp;feature=related</a> and Turkey <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk</a></p>\n<p>Kind Regards and see you in Istanbul,</p>\n<p>Melih Kürşat DEMİRDİREK</p>\n<p>Contact Person of LC ISTANBUL</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr\']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a>…</p>\n', 'Managination&#8217;11', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'managination11', '', '', '2011-01-24 20:02:30', '2011-01-24 19:02:30', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/managination11/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2302, 1, '2011-01-24 19:53:23', '2011-01-24 18:53:23', '\n<p>Please note that our EU grant application is still pending, so all EESTECers from LCs that have not sent us part3 documents are also encouraged to apply.<br />\nThe event will take place, <strong>regardless</strong> of the outcome of the EU grant.<br />\nAs for our applicants, we take your <strong>priority lists</strong> and <strong>motivational letters</strong><br />\ninto account when selecting participants.</p>\n<p>After the great success last year&#8217;s WiE, we are proud to announce that we and<br />\nour Gender Studies department (Gender Zentrum) are working together to make it<br />\nhappen again this year.</p>\n<p>The academic part of the workshop will cover the same topics as last year<br />\n(difficulties and barriers for women in engineering jobs, women&#8217;s networks as<br />\nwell as job- and life-planning), but these topics will be approached from a<br />\ndifferent angle this year, so, even if you participated last year, it might be<br />\nworth it to apply again.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, there will be a women&#8217;s contact forum during which you&#8217;ll have<br />\nthe opportunity to interact and exchange experiences with other women working<br />\nin engineering jobs.</p>\n<p>Apart from the lectures, we&#8217;ll of course be showing you the city of Munich,<br />\nit&#8217;s nightlife and cultural aspects.</p>\n<p>The workshop will conclude with the International Motivation Weekend. This<br />\nevent will be held at a house in Austria (near Salzburg) with a great view.<br />\nHere you&#8217;ll be participating in soft-skill training and, of course, some<br />\nunforgettable parties.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re looking forward to your application</p>\n<p>Important: <strong>Only women may apply!</strong></p>\n<p>Hope to see you in May!</p>\n', 'WiE &#8211; Women in Engineering', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'wie-women-in-engineering', '', '', '2011-01-24 19:53:23', '2011-01-24 18:53:23', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/wie-women-in-engineering/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2303, 1, '2011-01-24 19:46:58', '2011-01-24 18:46:58', '\n<p><strong>Please note</strong> that our EU grant application is still pending, so all EESTECers from LCs that<br />\nhave not sent us part3 documents are also encouraged to apply.<br />\nThe event will take place, <strong>regardless</strong> of the outcome of the EU grant.<br />\nAs for our applicants, we take your <strong>priority lists</strong> and <strong>motivational letters</strong><br />\ninto account when selecting participants.</p>\n<p>We are happy to announce our Dr. med. Nano workshop.</p>\n<p>This workshop will cover some interesting points about the interaction between<br />\nnano technology and medical engineering. There will be lectures, about both<br />\ntopics as well as a hands-on lab on the development of nanosensors on a<br />\nbimolecular basis during which you&#8217;ll learn how to build your own sensor.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll be cooperating with two departments in our university, so the lectures<br />\nwill be held by our professors.</p>\n<p>Of course you will also see the great city of Munich, experience the Bavarian<br />\nway of life and Bavarian hospitality. Also be prepared for Munich&#8217;s nightlife<br />\nand some unforgettable parties.</p>\n<p>The workshop will conclude with the International Motivation Weekend. This<br />\nevent will be held at a house in Austria (near Salzburg) with a great view.<br />\nHere you&#8217;ll be participating in soft-skill training and, of course, more<br />\npartying.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;ll be a great week&#8230; so don&#8217;t hesitate to apply!</p>\n<p>DEADLINE: 2011/04/08 18:00:00 GMT+2</p>\n', 'Dr. med. Nano', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dr-med-nano', '', '', '2011-01-24 19:46:58', '2011-01-24 18:46:58', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/dr-med-nano/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2304, 1, '2011-01-24 19:35:47', '2011-01-24 18:35:47', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Madrid is proud to present our new and first event for the 2011!<br />\nDue to the generational change at our local committee and the great change which our society is living, this year we decided to change our minds and focus on something that is closer to us: the SOCIETY. But nowadays everything is global, we all are interconnected with everything, so our society lives and works in NETWORKs.<br />\nFor all these reasons, we have created NETWORK SOCIETY, a new kind of event for us during which, through conferences, seminars and visits to laboratories and research centers, we will try to offer you a wide overview of what is being done in this fields and how our global society is growing up through the network.</p>\n<p>This amazing project will be held in Madrid from  3th April 2011 to 10th April 2011.</p>\n<p>Okay, okay, that all sounds very nice and interesting, but what about the party? WE WANT PARTY!</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry, as we always say: Madrid NEVER sleeps.<br />\nSo, during the whole week you&#8217;ll have a lot of chances to feel Madrid&#8217;s party and lifestyle, visit some of the landmarks of our city and participate in the traditional CityRally. And if that were not enough, during the weekend you will have the opportunity to enjoy some time out the city, practicing some sports and having crazy parties in the countryside!</p>\n<p>Besides, this year we have talked to a psychic who has confirmed that no other Eyjafjallajökull will wake up during our event. Now, what are you waiting for? Apply for the event ASAP, the deadline is 6th February 2011! =&#8217;D</p>\n<p>By the way, there&#8217;s another important point&#8230;<br />\nWe&#8217;re so sorry to have to say this, but as we don&#8217;t apply for EU grant, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although we are delighted with the result obtained in this area the last year, in previous events some years back, we had problems with some people showing a total lack of consideration for our work, sleeping during conferences with the sponsors and university professors, which made us lose all our credibility among them&#8230;</p>\n<p>Therefore, this time we expect a similar attitude to the last year and we won&#8217;t tolerate an irresponsible one. And in case of it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.</p>\n<p>When there is time to party, we party (and trust me, there will be! ;D), but when it&#8217;s time to work, we work (and later we have party! ^^).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.eestec.es/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.eestec.es\']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a>…</p>\n<p>We hope to see you all in Madrid!</p>\n<p>Greetings from LC Madrid&#8230;</p>\n', 'Network Society', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'network-society', '', '', '2011-01-24 19:35:47', '2011-01-24 18:35:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/network-society/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2305, 1, '2011-01-23 12:11:53', '2011-01-23 11:11:53', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s all prepare for magnificent and breathtaking mountain of Durmitor and enjoy an unexpected beautiful and picturesque winter wonderland!</p>\n<p>LC Podgorica is happy to invite eight of you to join 3 days long snowy party in tourist center of National Park Durmitor and winter sports of Montenegro &#8211; the town of Žabljak,  which is situated in the north-west of Montenegro, 1450 meters above sea level.</p>\n<p>Beside extremely good parties, visitation of National Park and other interesting activities, LC Podgorica will hold training on the topic of Team Building and Project Management. Accordingly, you will have a chance to meet a lot of your colleagues from Electrical Engineering Faculty Podgorica.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to ask me <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>7. February 2011</strong>.</p>\n<p>More information about Žabljak you can discover on: <a href="http://www.durmitorcg.com/opstina_eng.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.durmitorcg.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.durmitorcg.com/opstina_eng.php</a></p>\n<p><strong>It is no wonder that visiting Montenegro during the winter can be full of pleasant surprises.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Come to discover, experience and enjoy &#8221;Wild Beauty&#8221;!</strong> <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Durmitor Motivational Weekend', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'durmitor-motivational-weekend', '', '', '2011-01-23 12:11:53', '2011-01-23 11:11:53', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/durmitor-motivational-weekend/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2306, 1, '2011-01-18 20:38:17', '2011-01-18 19:38:17', '\n<p>Dear CPs,</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re happy to announce that LC Belgrade won EU grant and therefore is making preparations for a workshop called &#8221;<strong>Lead the way!</strong>&#8221;.<br />\nThe prime aim of this event is to prepare young people (meaning participants <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> ) with necessary skills and knowledge in order to improve themselves (more), to create successful business plans and start up their own businesses, find financing opportunities and become future leaders in their communities.<br />\nAll of these skills you&#8217;ll get by taking part in different activities, such as: lectures, presentations, working sessions, funny games&#8230;</p>\n<p>Apart from this academic activities, we&#8217;ll do our best to present you the beauties of <a href="http://www.tob.rs/en/index.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.tob.rs\']);" target="_blank">our capital</a> (is there anyone who haven&#8217;t heard about Kalish Challenge?!) and its world wide famous nightlife. You&#8217;ll have enough time to enjoy delights of Serbian cuisine and to find out why people fall in love with rakija with the first sip. <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /><br />\nOh, and&#8230;Prepare yourselves for a lot of winter magic, since we&#8217;re taking you to weekend trip to Kopaonik, one of our most attractive mountains.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;d like to thank to all LCs who signed part3 form and made this event possible by giving us their support.<br />\nPlease note that only LCs listed below can send their members to this event, paying respect to referred gender distribution.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;" rowspan="2"><strong>LC<br />\n</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;" rowspan="2"><strong>Number of participants<br />\n</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><strong>Distribution by gender<br />\n</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>M</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>F</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Ankara</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Munich</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Ljubljana</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Maribor</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Zagreb</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Sarajevo</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">East Sarajevo</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Belgrade</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Madrid</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Bucharest</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Tallinn</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Athens</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Podgorica</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Skopje</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Budapest</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Delft</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td style="text-align: left;">1</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n', 'Lead the way!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'lead-the-way', '', '', '2011-01-18 20:38:17', '2011-01-18 19:38:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/lead-the-way/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2307, 1, '2011-01-03 22:47:58', '2011-01-03 21:47:58', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After our third edition of “Conquer the markets” LC Zürich is proud to announce our new workshop “Zürich interactive”!</p>\n<p>Despite of the new subject many of the well-tried parts like our famous tram-party and the city rally will take place. In small groups you will design or program games and light animations on our self-made interactive dance floor, which detects movements on it and can be enlightened in all possible colors. Groups will be made according to your preferences and knowledge, so if you do not like to program, you can think about the next party game hit! And it will be played on a 4&#215;2.5m &#8220;Touchscreen&#8221;!</p>\n<p>Check out this video of Snake being played on a smaller version of the dance-floor: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=um1bMXSOXw8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=um1bMXSOXw8</a></p>\n<p>Besides playing with the dance floor we will visit a <strong>chocolate factory</strong> and go one <strong>whole day skiing</strong>! Like every year there will be <strong>many parties</strong> with much free alcohol <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';-)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  We are proud to announce that we got the “Youth in Action”-grant, which means a big part of the travel costs will be paid back to you. Additionally it enables us to organize some special activities you will not forget, ever!</p>\n<p>A temporary schedule can be found here: <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/zurich/zurich-interactive" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/zurich/zurich-interactive</a></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have skiing equipment and want to go on the ski-slopes it&#8217;s possible to rent everything. For us it is important that everybody who wants to ski gets the possibility- for this we will pay a part of the renting and ticket costs! And for those not wanting to try skiing, a beautiful day in the snow-covered alps with some sledging and some Glühwein is waiting!</p>\n<p>Best regards and see you in Zürich!!</p>\n<p>Your LC Zürich</p>\n', 'Zürich interactive', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'zurich-interactive', '', '', '2011-01-03 22:47:58', '2011-01-03 21:47:58', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/zurich-interactive/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2308, 1, '2011-01-03 22:40:19', '2011-01-03 21:40:19', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Dig out your earmuffs, gloves and other winter clothes and get ready for some mind-blowing fun in the snow!</p>\n<p>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that our EESTEC Winter Olympic Games Sarajevo are becoming a tradition! We are now even more focused on and excited about offering you more fun and entertainment!!</p>\n<p>Everyone knows that when it comes to EESTEC having fun is obligatory so let us prove once again that the EESTEC spirit is alive and kicking!</p>\n<p>It is time to hang up your thinking caps and get ready to party EESTEC STYLE! The parties are going to be crazier, the games more intense than anything you have EVER experienced. This is truly an exchange you will not want to miss out on! (I should also mention that there is no academical part <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> )</p>\n<p>Every night from 22.02.2011 to 27.02.2011 you will be able to experience the Great Spirit of Sarajevo. We will present you cultural beauties of Sarajevo, the place where West and East meet.</p>\n<p>Not only will you experience a cultural mix unlike anywhere in the world and have a chance to meet the friendliest people, but you will also enjoy a weekend on one of our beautiful mountains.</p>\n<p>A true winter wonderland.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact CP of event Džana Kujan on dzana.kujan@gmail.com.</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is 25th January 2011.</p>\n<p>More information about Sarajevo and last year’s EWOGS you can find on:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ewogs.com.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.ewogs.com.ba\']);" target="_blank">http://www.ewogs.com.ba</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.sarajevo.ba\']);" target="_blank">http://www.sarajevo.ba</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com\']);" target="_blank">http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'Winter Olympic Games Sarajevo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'winter-olympic-games-sarajevo', '', '', '2011-01-03 22:40:19', '2011-01-03 21:40:19', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/winter-olympic-games-sarajevo/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2309, 1, '2010-12-24 16:14:27', '2010-12-24 15:14:27', '\n<p>Did you ever want to stop the moment? Sometimes the words do not have any meaning,in at that moment an image becomes physical with photographing. If you are one of that people who wants to stop the moment, if your fever is not balanced and if you want to photograph intersection of European and Asian culter together. Then we will give a chance to you to fell more energetic and refreshing yourself with humanistic photosynthesis.</p>\n<p>The main topic of the event is &#8216;photograph&#8217; and &#8216;photoshop&#8217;. Event will be 2 parts; first part will be theoretical, we will give some sessions about how to produce a professional photograph, usage of a professional  camera, details of taking pictures and using photoshop professionally. Sessions will not be only informative but also funny. Second part will be practice, we will go to the area of Anadolu University, to the beautiful nature and historical places of Eskisehir and into the city, to take some good pictures together.</p>\n<p>Sessions will be really funny but also crazy nights of the Eskişehir will be waiting for you. Also we will give you a chance to see the best Turkish Bath in the Turkey, traditional Turkish drink Rakı, delicious Turkish foods, Turkish Nargile,and so on&#8230;We will not forget traditional EESTEC nights for sure, multi culture night&#8230;</p>\n<p>LC ESKİŞEHİR will host 15 participants, if there will be more applications, we will try to accept best number of the applications which we can do. <strong>If you have your own camera, recommended to take it with you, but if you do not have any camera we will give you one until the end of the event.</strong></p>\n<p>So <strong>we are waiting for you</strong> ,and <strong>what are you waiting for</strong>?</p>\n<p>If you have any question do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>SEE YOU!</p>\n', 'PhotosynthESis', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'photosynthesis', '', '', '2010-12-24 16:14:27', '2010-12-24 15:14:27', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/photosynthesis/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2310, 1, '2010-12-16 08:48:54', '2010-12-16 07:48:54', '\n<p>Are you interested in space? Do you like Star Wars movies? Would you like to experience Finland&#8217;s beautiful winter? Eestec LC Helsinki proudly presents the first workshop of the year 2011: ”StarWorks”! We have prepared you an awesome workshop about space technology and provided an opportunity to learn cool stuff from famous and crazy scientist guys like Esko Valtaoja!</p>\n<p>We will have super interesting lectures about space, remote sensing, northern lights and satellites. We will also have some fun sessions where you will learn how to study earth from space. Our Department of Radio Science and Engineering will provide you one ECTS (European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System) if you return a diary of the stuff you have learned during the week.</p>\n<p>And no.. we have not forgotten to spoil you with some parties as we are going to throw you to sauna, show you some naked people and teach you how to drink &amp; sing in Finnish academic student party called ”sitsit”. And furthermore, you&#8217;ll experience parties in Helsinki center, movie making with local TV-channel and weekend at a countryside where you can do ice swimming!</p>\n<p>So grab your lightsaber and make sure that you&#8217;ll be in Helsinki at 23rd of January 2011!</p>\n', 'StarWorks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'starworks', '', '', '2010-12-16 08:48:54', '2010-12-16 07:48:54', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/starworks/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2311, 1, '2010-11-14 14:53:17', '2010-11-14 13:53:17', '\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hello dear EESTECers,</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">LC Aachen is happy to invite you to this year&#8217;s edition of our traditional Niko-Event.</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It takes place from 5.12. (arrival) to 11.12. (departure) 2010. The deadline to apply is the 19.11.2010.</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">We have to apologize for announcing the event so late and for the short deadline!</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">However, we will try to present you some nice days: Instead of workshop-atmosphere with lots of learning and company-visiting, we promise you a small nice meeting in a Christmas fair atmosphere with lots of hot mulled wine, gingerbread and EESTEC-spirit! Furthermore we will have a trip to Cologne and tours around our nice little town.</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">And of course there is the main event: the Unicup, the annual icehockey-tournament at our University. Your job will be to cheer our teams to victory!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Should you have any questions, feel free to contact us at any time!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hopefully see you soon!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Andreea Siller (CP Aachen)</span></p>\n', 'Niko-Meeting', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'niko-meeting', '', '', '2010-11-14 14:53:17', '2010-11-14 13:53:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/niko-meeting/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2312, 1, '2010-10-22 23:23:41', '2010-10-22 22:23:41', '\n<p>Dear lovely EESTEC’ers;</p>\n<p>We’re sure that all of you wonder how to fly a plane? How can a pilot keep all of the aeronautical units in the cockpit under control? As we EESTEC’ers, planes are very important for us and you have a chance to know everything about them thanks to our great(will be) workshop <strong>“Above us only sky!”</strong> which will take place in Ankara between <strong>4.12.2010 </strong>and <strong>12.12.2010</strong>.</p>\n<p>The main topic of workshop is &#8220;Avionics&#8221; which is a combination of the words &#8220;aviation&#8221; and &#8220;electronics&#8221;. As you may know, especially with the development of unmanned aerial vehicle, avionics has become a very popular topic nowadays.<br />\nDuring the workshop, you&#8217;ll have comprehensive knowledge about avionics by taking lectures regarding subtopics which are navigation, unmanned aerial vehicle, control, avionics history and development, and every other detail you need to know. Trainings will be given by professors and their assistants in Aerospace Engineering Department of Middle East Technical University which is one of the best technical university in Turkey and trainers of TAI(Turkish Aerospace Industries) which is the biggest company in Turkey in aerospace industry. You&#8217;ll not only have lectures, but also visit production line in the factory of TAI, laboratories of Aerospace Engineering Department of Middle East Technical University, and aeronautic museums. In addition, you&#8217;ll have an opportunity to see a simulation of how unmanned aerial vehicle works.</p>\n<p>Now let’s move on to the fun part! We guarantee the enjoying part will be awesome as much as the academic part. You will have a great chance to get know &#8220;T<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kebab" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);">urkish Kebab</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nargile" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);">Turkish Nargile</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belly_dance" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);">Turkish Belly Dance</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rakı" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://en.wikipedia.org\']);">Turkish Raki</a>&#8221; and the most important one “Turkish Hospitality”. Accommodation will be in the guest house of Turkish Aeronautics Association; that is, you&#8217;re gonna stay with quite many planes. Every night we’ll enjoy with the non-stop and crazy parties with different themes such as masquerade party, aeronautics party where guys can be pilot and girls can be hostess for one night! But it&#8217;s for sure; we&#8217;ll not forget to have some EESTEC event traditions like sightseeing, international night as well.</p>\n<p>LC Ankara will host <strong>15 participants</strong>; however, we&#8217;ll do our best to accept more participants. <strong>Deadline to apply is the 1st of November</strong>.</p>\n<p>As you see, such a wonderful event in different continent, Asia is ready for you. So what you are supposed to do now is just to enter <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eestec.net\']);">eestec.net</a> and submit your application form!!</p>\n<p>If you have any question, feel free to ask via <strong>mervebilgic90@gmail.com</strong>.</p>\n<p>Looking forward to seeing you here!!</p>\n<p>Greetings from Turkey!</p>\n', 'Above us only Sky!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'above-us-only-sky', '', '', '2010-10-22 23:23:41', '2010-10-22 22:23:41', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/above-us-only-sky/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2313, 1, '2010-10-22 23:10:55', '2010-10-22 22:10:55', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Have you ever wondered what it would be like to build some robots? Or maybe you are curious about how amazing Riga and its’ nightlife is? JLC Riga has prepared for you our very first workshop “Plop, Plop, Fizz, Fizz, Oh, What a Robot it is?” and it will take place in Latvia, Riga from 5th till 12th December .</p>\n<p>With the help of experienced trainers you will be able to gain practical skills to operate electronical components and learn basic programming that will let the Robot you build become a real fighter! All the built robots will take part Baltic states robot contest „Robotika”.</p>\n<p>Besides that, we are planning to show you our best places in Riga and not only. You should know that Riga is famous with its architecture and skyline of 3 Church steeples, which has become a true visiting card. Well, of course when the sun goes down, the nightlife can begin and Old Riga is full of places to have fun – plenty of pubs and clubs. But you will have to see it all for yourselves.</p>\n<p>For the weekend we have prepared to you little trip to Sigulda (also called “The Switzerland of Latvia) which is famous for its Castles and adorable landscapes.</p>\n<p>Well, we cannot tell you all the details, but we can assure you that you will love it here. Don&#8217;t miss this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EO_9_Zd8pqk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://www.youtube.com\']);">beautiful city</a> !</p>\n<p>See you in Riga! <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n', 'Plop, Plop, Fizz, Fizz, Oh, What a Robot it is?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'plop-plop-fizz-fizz-oh-what-a-robot-it-is', '', '', '2010-10-22 23:10:55', '2010-10-22 22:10:55', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/plop-plop-fizz-fizz-oh-what-a-robot-it-is/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2314, 1, '2010-10-22 23:04:22', '2010-10-22 22:04:22', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich is proud to announce that we will organize an event never done<br />\nbefore: The soon-to-be-legendary Oktoberfest Exchange!<br />\nIt will take place between Wednesday the 29th September and Tuesday the<br />\n4th October.</p>\n<p>A few words regarding the concept of this exchange: There will be no<br />\nlectures, however, entertainment during your stay in Munich will be cared<br />\nfor. We will accommodate you privately, since there is no way to get a<br />\nhotel spot in Munich during Oktoberfest without paying ridiculous prices.<br />\nUnfortunately we have to ask a participation fee of 90€. This includes<br />\nbeer and food at the Oktoberfest worth 27€. Be advised, however, that you<br />\nwill very likely spend a lot more money on beer &#8212; one beer is 8.50€.<br />\nMunich is generally an expensive place during the Oktoberfest, but as<br />\nusual, everything except for drinks is included for our participants.<br />\nThe exchange will include two visits to the famous &#8220;Wiesn&#8221; along with<br />\nsightseeing to famous places such as Neuschwanstein, a nearby castle built<br />\nby Bavarian King Ludwig II.</p>\n<p>For various organisational reasons we unfortunately cannot accept more<br />\nthan 10-12 participants, the exact number is yet to be announced. We<br />\nencourage you very much to apply, after all this is a once in a lifetime<br />\nopportunity (unless we do it again next year) to visit the famous<br />\nOkotberfest with few fellow EESTECers!! Don&#8217;t miss out and send your<br />\napplication today <img src=\'http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':-)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /><br />\nDeadline to apply is Saturday, August 14th, 12 PM (noon).</p>\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Due to the nature of the event and the extraordinary<br />\ncircumstances, we reserve the right not to respect your priority list. We<br />\nencourage you, however, to send one anyway and apologize for the<br />\ninconvenience. We&#8217;ll try to fulfill your request as good as possible.</p>\n', 'Oktoberfest Exchange', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'oktoberfest-exchange', '', '', '2010-10-22 23:04:22', '2010-10-22 22:04:22', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/oktoberfest-exchange/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2315, 1, '2010-07-24 18:30:52', '2010-07-24 17:30:52', '\n<p><strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<h2>Green Week in Novi Sad  “Act Now &#8211; Change the Future”</h2>\n<p>eYouwins &#8211; The European Youth Week in Novi Sad is the one of the first and the largest youth festival with a thematic focus in Serbia. eYouwins is dedicated to youth in Serbia, Europe and worldwide, and its mission is to promote the spirit of cooperation, to link cultures, ideas and, above all, people. Festival has started in 2006 and in short time has gained popularity among young people all over Europe. During the last four years more than 5000 young people were involved in the Festival events and almost 400 guests from 25 countries visited Novi Sad and Serbia.</p>\n<p>In 2010 eYouwins celebrates 5th birthday and invites 150 participants to come to Novi Sad, between 17th and 24th August; to focus on green ways of life and sustainable development of our society. Therefore, this year eYouwins is greenWins.<br />\nProgram of the greenWins is structured as a combination of three elements: education, action and fun.<br />\nEducational part of greenWins will be composed of lectures and workshops. The main part of the thematic work of greenWins will be the group work on different topics organized in six different workshops which highlight the Festival theme from various aspects. The second segment of greenWins is Action. In this segment, participants will be directly involved in actions related to Festival topic, practicing ecological habits and raising awareness in Novi Sad and its surrounding. Finally, third segment of the Festival, Fun, covers activities relating to art, music and sport. Traditional Youth Carnival during Festival weekend will bring interesting concerts and dance performances organized for participants, citizens and other visitors of Novi Sad.</p>\n<p>Planned workshops<br />\nWS1 – reCycle it! (what, how &amp; where to recycle)<br />\nWS2 – Art of Waste (creative reuse of waste)<br />\nWS3 – Blue Gold (Water Scarcity )<br />\nWS4 – Ecology Hotspots (mapping ecology problems)<br />\nWS5–Energy (R)evolution (managing energy resources)<br />\nWS6 – Changing Clime (climate change)</p>\n<p>Participation fee for greenWins is 60 EURO for international participants and 3000 Dinars for the participants from Serbia.<br />\nThe participation fee covers accommodation, and meals during the Festival (light breakfast, lunch and dinner per day), organised excursions, sightseeing, entrance fees, and free participation in trips, conference programme, cultural and sport events of the Festival.<br />\nIn participants fee is not included travel costs and personal expenses!!!<br />\nAccepted participants will pay the participants fee on arrival, at the registration. If you want to take a part in the Festival fill the registration form as earlier as you can!!!</p>\n<p>Application deadline is 15th July 20010!!</p>\n<p>For more information on the festival please visit our website at: <a href="http://eyouwins.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\',\'outbound-article\',\'http://eyouwins.com\']);">http://eyouwins.com</a></p>\n<p>Should you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me at any time!</p>\n<p>We hope to see you in Novi Sad!!!</p>\n', 'greenWins 2010', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'greenwins-2010', '', '', '2010-07-24 18:30:52', '2010-07-24 17:30:52', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/greenwins-2010/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2488, 1, '2013-03-06 00:36:20', '2013-03-05 23:36:20', 'Greetings from The North.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEverything today is driven by computers, bigger or smaller ones. Almost everything that has any kind of electronics includes a computing unit also. So what are these, why they make so complex things work? We try to find this answer for you as we open the world of digital technology for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAND SO! We proudly announce our new workshop  "Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79". Our fellows at computer techlab are more than welcoming to take you for a tour in the world of computing with ones and zeros.<b></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor one week our LC is happy to host you to enjoy our beautiful city of Tampere, the northernmost LC in eestec. If you think this is going to be one of those easier workshops where you can sleep between lectures then you’re gravely mistaken. We indeed take our education seriously but we take our parties even more seriously. In one week we will introduce you to the whole new world of sauna, singing, Finnish culture, city life of “small town” and the right Finnish way of doing things wrong.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo, everyone who has any interest in digital designs, embedded systems, computers or just generally is trying to find something interesting to study, we openly welcome you.\r\n\r\nWe’d really appreciate those applications that have some information about what you generally study and what you know about digital designs and computer technologies as our professor may want people to have some degree of knowledge about the area.', 'Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'workshop-of-417373656d626c79', '', '', '2013-03-06 00:36:20', '2013-03-05 23:36:20', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2488', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2562, 1, '2013-03-12 02:30:11', '2013-03-12 01:30:11', 'Prepare every single cell in your body, cause you are going to become time traveller in Belgrade, and we will give our best to be great companions in this journey. We\'re happy to announce that this May you could be the part of "World Beyond Tomorrow".\r\n\r\nGuiding you through a regular family day, twenty years from now, lecturers will introduce you with new necessary technologies. Familiar with all the details and needed knowledge about 4G, hologram, must-have robots, and all innovations that strive to become a part of our everyday life, the future will seem like the present to you. In cooperation with ESTIEM, the organisation for European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management, we will show you admirable landscapes of our country and the way we define word <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=--c03roM4nI" target="_blank">party</a>. So, you will also have the opportunity to meet with members of their event which would be held side-by-side with our workshop.\r\n\r\nAfter a long time, we decided to show you the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Zu_tkk9be0" target="_blank">White city</a> in the period when you can see it in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring. Ada Ciganlija, oasis of nature in the busy city life, is waiting for you, as well as Kalemegdan, Skadarlija, Nikola Tesla Museum, Knez Mihailova street... You will have the chance to enjoy traditional <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" target="_blank">Serbian cuisine</a>, gibanica, ajvar, pljeskavica and of course rakija.\r\n\r\n\r\nApply now, and enjoy in knowledge and party time warp! :)\r\n\r\n\r\nSee you in Serbia,\r\nAnita Jović.', 'World Beyond Tomorrow', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'world-beyond-tomorrow', '', '', '2013-03-27 17:07:10', '2013-03-27 16:07:10', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2562', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2650, 1, '2013-03-16 14:01:52', '2013-03-16 13:01:52', '<div> Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>All of you probably remember one of the most known Latin phrases: "Historia est Magistra Vitae" :) We sure do and we are proud to announce our workshop which pretty much bases on this phrase. If you apply for “Back in Time” we can promise you won’t regret it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Have you ever wondered how stuff worked before almost everything went digital and computer controlled? All those interesting and smart solutions everyone has forgotten about? In Zagreb you will have a chance to get familiar with them. Old principles of automatics, programming, power engineering and wireless technology can always come in handy to today’s modern engineers. We will make comparisons between old and new, and make conclusions with pros and cons for each individual technology/solution/approach.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Now let’s get to the more interesting part of the workshop – our beautiful city of Zagreb. You will get in touch with every part of Croatian culture and have an opportunity to taste our delicious cousin and our inspiring drinks. Also, you will get a chance to enjoy our beautiful Adriatic coast and our crystal clear sea ;)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Our museums are going to give you a very good insight into our culture and you will spend time exploring Zagreb in a really interesting way. We will make sure you have enough time to enjoy the city and relax.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>And the most important part – you’ll attend the most awesome parties in Zagreb and we can assure you that you will remember them for your life.</div>\r\n<div>So, don’t hesitate to apply to our super duper workshop! We promise you good time :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>If you have any questions or need more convincing just contact us.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>With love from LC Zagreb &lt;3</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><br clear="all" /> </span></span></span></div>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Xsz49mzCVg0" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Back in Time', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'back-in-time', '', '', '2013-04-04 12:59:46', '2013-04-04 11:59:46', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2650', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2652, 1, '2013-03-16 14:08:48', '2013-03-16 13:08:48', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are proud to announce our next workshop. After a long tradition of successful workshops, we are still trying to do better and improve our offer! This time we will amuse you with a workshop related to Green and Eco Friendly Technologies.\r\nFuture Technologies are coming to be more and more green. Our lectures will deal with Green Computing technologies, having a deep practical insight: we will have the honor to host some successful StartUp in this field, that will explain how it works in real life.\r\n\r\nGreen Economy is the new challenge, and we are ready to catch it!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMoreover this year there will be an exclusive news! Our workshop will be held in collaboration with ESTIEM Association (European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management). Green supply chain will be the other topic that you will have the opportunity do deal with.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt means a double opportunity to meet and melt with Students from all Europe!!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAcademics activity will be just a short (but heaped) bracket in your experience here in Cosenza.\r\nCosenza is the biggest Campus in the South of Italy. A neighborhood made up exclusively of 2000 Students and 200 Erasmus Students, offers one of the most brave and challenging night life! <strong>Get ready for it!!!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou will have also the opportunity to visit the most stunning and breathtaking landscapes of our land! The land of the sun, the sea and the good food! All this delved in a rich cultural background ( don\'t forget that Pitagora was born in Calabria ;) ).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCalabria is waiting for you, see you there!!! :D\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPS: We will provide you a detailed programme as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'GECO (Green Engineering COmputing)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'geco-green-engineering-computing', '', '', '2013-03-16 14:08:48', '2013-03-16 13:08:48', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2652', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2664, 1, '2013-03-27 20:32:39', '2013-03-27 19:32:39', '<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Hello dear friends, students and other members of NGOs!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Leadership Summer School is coming!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Do you want to inspire people? Do you have plans to lead a project in your NGO? Do you think that the word “leader” describes you?</i></b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Interested?  </i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Apply to LSS`13.</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><i><span style="color: #000000;">Our project will help you discover your potential!</span></i></b>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Together we can change the world!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">==============================<wbr />==========================\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b> ==What is LSS?===</b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The Leadership Summer School is an intensive learning event and a networking platform, aiming at increasing skills and readiness of youth NGO leaders, sharing best practices and improving leadership skills among prominent members of each participating organisation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What are we looking for?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">We are looking for <b>70 highly motivated and active students and youth</b> who will participate to a challenging learning event.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> <b>===When and Where?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Sofia (Bulgaria)<i> f</i></span>rom <b>21st till 30th of July 2013</b>\r\n\r\n<img alt="Inline images 2" src="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/?ui=2&amp;ik=6c33839bd5&amp;view=att&amp;th=13dad4cf0ee7a16d&amp;attid=0.1&amp;disp=emb&amp;realattid=ii_13dad39a8865b14e&amp;zw&amp;atsh=1" width="420" height="310" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What about the fee? ===</b> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The fee will be <b>190 EUR </b>which includes:\r\n</span>- accommodation;\r\n- food (3 meals per day + coffee breaks);\r\n- transport for LSS activities;\r\n- and some social activities.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">If selected to participate in the event, it will be requested from you to pay 50% of the fee (95 EUR) as participation confirmation: this amount is <i><b>not refundable</b></i>. The rest can be paid anticipatively or at the event itself. More details will be communicated at that moment.</span>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;">We are not able to provide scholarship or any form of discount.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></i>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===How to apply?===</span></b>\r\n\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></b>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Fill the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1zqu6fpLsWGk9QtI5Ln72Pzlx2BWv9xWiEF6Ha19Qn2A/viewform" target="_blank">LSS 2013 Application form</a>.</span>\r\n<div><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<div><i><b>Deadline to apply: April  14th 23:59 CET</b></i></div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===And now ===</span></b>\r\nWe are looking forward to reading your applications and if you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to contact us by mail: <a href="mailto:contact@leadershipsummerschool.org" target="_blank">contact@<wbr />leadershipsummerschool.org</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Leadership Summer School 2013', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'leadership-summer-school-2013', '', '', '2013-03-27 20:36:33', '2013-03-27 19:36:33', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2664', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2670, 1, '2013-03-27 21:07:17', '2013-03-27 20:07:17', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe, LC Delft, are proud to announce our next workshop “Tie Another Day – A challange from Mars”,\r\n\r\nFirst of all, welcome to the <strong>Mars rover project</strong>! In this powerful workshop we give you a directive to design a complex system. We have taken a top-down approach. This way you can understand the operation of the increasingly larger parts within the whole system.\r\n\r\nIn the first part of the workshop you will design a mobile robot (the Mars Rover) in a group of students. This robot has to be able to search for a line and then track the line and take turns. Some <strong>additional intelligence </strong>has to be added as well. The design steps are not only useful for this workshop, but also for complex systems in general. First you focus at the problem as a whole, and then the problem is divided into even smaller parts which are then implemented. This is the so-called top-down approach.\r\n\r\nIn the design you have to deal with operation and readout of input signals (sensors), output actuators  the motors) and a controller. The robot is programmed in VHDL. VHDL is a Hardware Description Language (HDL), a language which is used to help design digital circuits.\r\n\r\nIn order to test the Mars Rover, <strong>a complex maze</strong> is available. Your Mars Rover has to find the way out as fast as possible. As an added challenge, the maze contains instructions for the Mars Rover for making sharp turns that allows a faster traversal of the maze.\r\n\r\nThe second part of the workshop focuses on the <strong>power supply of the Mars Rover</strong>. In the first part of the workshop, the robot will use batteries as its power supply. If the batteries run out of power, you can easily replace them. However, on Mars this would pose a problem. In order to be able to use the Mars rover for an extended amount of time, an alternative energy source is needed. On Mars it is possible to use solar energy to power the Mars rover. In the second part of the workshop you will examine a solar cell and design additional circuits in order to use the solar energy as the power supply of the Mars rover.\r\n\r\nObvious this is not everything in the weekend and at every evening there will be time to explore other things like Delft and The Netherlands.  So don’t hesitate and apply before Friday the 19<sup>th</sup> of april.\r\n\r\nFor Questions don’t hesitate to contact <a href="mailto:cp@etv.tudelft.nl">cp@etv.tudelft.nl</a> for further questions.', 'Tie Another Day - A Challenge from Mars', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tie-another-day-a-challange-from-mars', '', '', '2013-03-27 21:36:26', '2013-03-27 20:36:26', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2670', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2673, 1, '2013-03-27 21:23:26', '2013-03-27 20:23:26', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe’re proud to announce the second edition of a workshop entitled ‘Smart Energy for a Better World’, in cooperation with ABB Corporate Research Centre, which will be held in Krakow from 7th till 13th of July 2013.\r\n\r\nThis study tour is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science. The event will be a unique opportunity to visit one of the most advanced ABB Research Centers in the world and to broaden your knowledge on:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advanced numerical simulations</li>\r\n	<li>Power electronics</li>\r\n	<li>Transients phenomena</li>\r\n	<li>Smart Protection</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced diagnostics</li>\r\n	<li>Ferroresonance phenomena</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll students from European Universities are invited to join us in Krakow, one of Poland\'s most renown cities. This event will be a great occasion to meet experts on energy, electrical sciences and to visit Poland\'s well-known tourist attractions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are waiting for applications from students who have:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>electrical engineering profile</li>\r\n	<li>good academic results</li>\r\n	<li>good command of English</li>\r\n	<li>completed at least 3 years of university education</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMore information about the lectures and lab excercises can be found on the website of the event <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeel the EESTEC Spirit and join us in Kraków. See with your own eyes the beauty one of the biggest city in Poland with its historicial treasures and vivid nightlife. You’ve got an unusual opportunity to visit i.a.:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the Wawel Royal Castle - located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;</li>\r\n	<li>the Underground of the City’s Main Market Square – unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will go on a tour to Kryspinów lake, barbecue at the biggest student campus in Poland or have a bowling night. We won’t reveal all of the spicy attractions we’ve prepared. We can say you’ll certainly experience the amazing nightlife and many other activities so you won’t get chance to get bored. Apply now or regret through the lifetime.\r\n\r\nHow to apply:\r\n\r\n1. EESTEC members: via eestec.net, where you should write down your motivational letter and send your CV to <a href="mailto:krakow@eestec.net">krakow@eestec.net</a>\r\n\r\n2. Non-EESTECers: via website: <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">smart.eestec.pl</a>\r\n\r\nWe’re waiting for You in Krakow! ;)\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<a id="parent-fieldname-eventUrl" href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">More information about this event…</a>', 'Smart Energy for a Better World 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'smart-energy-for-a-better-world-2', '', '', '2013-05-15 14:15:43', '2013-05-15 13:15:43', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2673', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (2910, 1, '2013-04-08 20:19:59', '2013-04-08 19:19:59', '<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Dear EESTECers,\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">LC Belgrade is proud to announce its first <a href="http://tinyurl.com/cd2zv47" target="_blank">International Motivational Weekend</a>, which will be held from 17th to 19th May! We are bringing the participants of our workshop <strong>„World Beyond Tomorrow",</strong> as a conclusion to a great event! The best way to participate at the IMW is to apply for our workshop!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Prepare yourself to enjoy in the youth camp Đerdap, located in the tourist region Karataš, just in the period in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring! You will have the chance to enjoy in our beautiful countryside, visit Hydroelectric Power Station „Đerdap 1" - the largest and first producer of hydroelectricity in Southeast Europe, take part in many fun activities like the games without limits, indoor soccer tournaments, beach volleyball, beer pong in the evening, have great fun at the parties and a lot of other funny things!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">The participation fee is <strong>55€</strong>, which includes return journey from Belgrade to Karataš, accommodation, 3 meals a day, drinks and free theme parties. At the IMW we will be accompanied by members of association <i>ESTIEM LG Belgrade</i>, so we definitely need all of you to join us and show them our EESTEC spirit! Also, you can ask us to book a room for you at the hostel in Belgrade, if you want to stay few more days.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Our bus will leave Belgrade at 09:00 am on Friday and back from the location on a Sunday afternoon.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">We promise you won\'t regret it! <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/belgrade/imw-belgrade-2013" target="_blank">See you in Serbia</a>!</span></p>', 'IMW Belgrade 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'imw-belgrade-2013', '', '', '2013-04-08 20:19:59', '2013-04-08 19:19:59', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2910', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3044, 1, '2013-05-22 11:04:55', '2013-05-22 10:04:55', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAre you ready to Cross the Line with LC Podgorica one more time?\r\n\r\nBe prepared, this year there will be more action, more excitement and even more lines to cross! You will experience 7 days of unforgettable atmosphere, EESTEC spirit and memories for a lifetime.\r\n\r\nLC Podgorica is taking you to <b>Kotor</b>, which is situated in Europe\'s southernmost <a title="Fjord" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fjord" target="_blank">fjord</a> called - Boka Kotorska (The Bay of Kotor, or Boka Bay). Kotor is one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast (UNESCO protected) . You will be able to experience Mediterranean spirit, see one of the most beautiful bays in Europe during the cruise that we will organize, and visit Gospa od Škrpjela (Our Lady of the Rocks) island.\r\n\r\nYou will see <b>Budva</b>, a pearl of Mediterranean, and a <a title="Luxury yacht" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_yacht" target="_blank">luxury yacht</a> <a title="Marina" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marina" target="_blank">marina</a> <b>Porto</b> <b>Montenegro</b>. Beside sightseeing and city rally, you will also have a chance to enjoy your stay in Montenegro on beautiful beaches of Budva, Tivat and Kotor and do summer activities with us.\r\n\r\nBut wait, that’s not all... The most important thing is the <b>Kotor Carnival</b>, one of the biggest and craziest carnivals in Europe! We are preparing many more surprises that will remain a secret for now... Sooo APPLY !\r\n\r\nThis event will also have an educational part. Considering that you are probably tired of engineering, we decided to make  workshops on photography, journalism  and filmmaking where you will be able to release your creativity. Summer and sunny days will surely inspire you! Also two EESTEC trainers will give you some innovative and damn interesting trainings, in order to motivate and relax you more and more...\r\n\r\nSo pack up your swimsuits, good mood, EESTEC Spirit and <b>Cross the Line</b> in Montenegro! We are waiting for you!', 'Cross the Line 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cross-the-line-2', '', '', '2013-05-22 11:04:55', '2013-05-22 10:04:55', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3044', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3047, 1, '2013-05-22 11:09:48', '2013-05-22 10:09:48', '<p dir="ltr">Attention please!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>LC Athens</strong><strong> </strong>is organizing an exchange!  All EESTECers are kindly requested to pack their things and apply for "<strong>GREECE ME UP vol.2</strong>" now!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">LC Athens wants to come closer to the heart of Europe and most of LCs, therefore we are going to the second biggest city of Greece,  <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thessaloniki" target="_blank">Thessaloniki</a>, so as to continue last year\'s myth!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The queen of the North, as it\'s called, combines the old with the new. The White Tower, the byzantine castles, the roman forum, the arch of Galerius-Kamara are only some of the attractions  that make it irresistible. What\'s more, Thessaloniki is one of the best student cities because of the crazy and awesome nightlife. As you will experience at first hand, people there are so relaxed, one of their favourite phrases is "halara", which means relaxed, chilled.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Of course we won\'t be staying in Thessaloniki all day, but we will also visit some very beautiful places too, like<a href="http://www.greecevirtual.gr/en/pella/edessa#/_18_kataraktes_%208/" target="_blank"> Edessa</a> which is well-known for its waterfalls and its flora, the historical city of<a href="http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/780" target="_blank"> Vergina</a> , the baths of Aridaia  and  one of the biggest <a href="http://www.waterland.gr/en" target="_blank">waterparks</a> of Εurope!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Last but not least, every participant will have the chance to participate in our <strong>International Motivational Weekend</strong> in Chalkidiki in the camp of the university of Thessaloniki next to an amazing and divine beach (yeah it‘s not a dream, you read correctly).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Don’t let this big opportunity go and just think of the sun, the beach, the fun and EESTEC.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">So the question is, are you ready to experience one of the ultimate forms of  “tourism” organised by, the one of its kind, LC Athens? As I think the answer is “Yes”, get your bathing suit, suit up and get ready to GREECE YOU UP . . . !</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/greece_me_up_vol2.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-3048 aligncenter" alt="greece_me_up_vol2" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/greece_me_up_vol2.png" width="400" height="230" /></a></p>', 'Greece Me Up vol.2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'greece-me-up-vol-2', '', '', '2013-05-22 11:09:48', '2013-05-22 10:09:48', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3047', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3078, 1, '2013-05-31 10:42:54', '2013-05-31 09:42:54', '<p dir="ltr">Dear EESTECers,</p>\r\nwe are back again with new and exciting ideas. Are you ready guys??? We are!!! LC Trieste is so so glad to announce the second EESTEC Summer School, entitled “Smart Mobile City”!\r\n\r\nWe promise to offer you the best Summer School ever, if you are brave enough to risk spending a week in summer LEARNING!\r\n<p dir="ltr">EESTECers will have the opportunity to attend a high quality academic event combined with the awesome EESTEC Spirit. You will have the chance to get in touch with top expertise speakers and participants.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The School will have two main threads: <strong>backend and frontend of Android applications</strong>, using open data and user experience guidelines, <strong>each with its own classes schedule</strong>. In addition there will also be a common schedule, to let participants work in teams and be involved in innovative and constructive challenges. Level classes will be intermediate.</p>\r\nWe are also planning a <strong>competition between teams</strong> of 5, picked randomly from both designers and developers.\r\n\r\nAfter the end of the ESS will start the <strong>second phase of the project</strong>, during which the groups have to complete their applications (even remotely of course) before the end of this year (deadline to be specified). But don’t worry, this effort <strong>will be very well rewarded</strong>!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe will work hard, but we will have fun too! No worries about this…you will be in Italy,  DON’T FORGET IT!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor more details visit our website: <a href="http://ess.eestec.it" target="_blank">http://ess.eestec.it</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe hope to see you all in Italy!\r\n<p dir="ltr">Greetings from LC Trieste!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">For any question:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Alessandra Laderchi</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Contact Person – LC Trieste</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">cp@ts.eestec.it</p>', '2nd EESTEC Summer School - "Smart Mobile City"', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '2nd-eestec-summer-school-smart-mobile-city', '', '', '2013-05-31 10:43:45', '2013-05-31 09:43:45', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3078', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3099, 1, '2013-06-08 08:33:49', '2013-06-08 07:33:49', '<p dir="ltr">Welcome on board to flight 86 to Chalkidiki (<em><a href="https://maps.google.gr/maps?q=poseidi&amp;gbv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=el&amp;authuser=0" target="_blank">Possidi</a></em>). This is your captain <strong>LC Athens</strong>. We will be cruising at a crazy student altitude where everybody has fun and unforgettable memories at a “halara” (hint: relaxed, cool)  airspeed of reggae rhythm and not only... The weather is clear and sunny and with the tailwind on our side we are expecting a high temperature which will increase as more and more people apply for this <strong>IMW</strong>. If the parties cooperate we should get a great view of the city as we descend... The cabin crew will be coming around to offer you a snack and a drink, and the experience of your lifetime will begin shortly after that. I\'ll talk to you again before we reach our destination.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Translation:\r\nYes, ladies and gentlemen you are already on a plane or on a bus (or who knows where else) and you are heading to Possidi where the <em>IMW of Greece Me Up vol.2</em> is going to be held.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Possidi is the camp of the university of Thessaloniki and as you can imagine, it is full of students who want to take a rest after a tough year and have some fun...like you! You will have the chance to enjoy the greek sunny weather, the beach, crazy activities, awesome parties and of course the Greek hospitality.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The participation fee is 50€ without the tent and transportation from Thessaloniki to Possidi and backwards. Concerning transportation to and from Possidi, it will be announced near the deadline, but arriving with your own means of transport is acceptable.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to be a part of this awesome experience apply now in <a href="https://gmuv2-unof-form.typeform.com/to/ON9pUS" target="_blank">this form</a>  in which you can find all the information and the details you may need.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Until then, sit back, halara (hint: relax) and enjoy the rest of the flight.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>P.S.</strong> You can find more information in our site <a href="http://greecemeup.net/" target="_blank">http://greecemeup.net/</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><b>Contact mail:</b> Giannis Sotiropoulos (C.P.): <a>js.lcathens@gmail.com</a>\r\nEleni Santorinaiou (H.O.)   : <a>elsantor8@gmail.com</a></p>', 'IMW in Greece 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'imw-in-greece-2013', '', '', '2013-06-08 08:33:49', '2013-06-08 07:33:49', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3099', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3104, 1, '2013-06-17 12:36:40', '2013-06-17 11:36:40', '<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Dear  EESTECers,</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Have glamorous events and movie spotlights always been out of reach? Have you always dreamt of experiencing the spirit of Hollywood? If so, you’re in luck! LC Sarajevo will provide you the ideal opportunity to learn everything you have ever wanted to know about movies: producing, editing, acting and much more.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Europe\'s most awesome LC is proud to invite you to the <b>3rd eMovie Academy</b>, which is becoming a tradition appealing to many potential artists and movie fanatics. We are offering you a week of fun, a week of glamour, a week of learning and most of all a week of <b>EESTEC Spirit</b>! Join us from <b>15th to 22nd of August </b>and enjoy the best experience of your life!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">The academical aspect will contain lectures and workshops about elements of movie making. You will learn to use professional software tools for movie-making, and at the end you will be able to make your own movie!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">In the period from 16th to 24th of August Sarajevo will gather movie elite from all over the world in one place, and bring them closer to fans and movie lovers. This is the period of one of the most respected movie festivals in Europe - the <b>Sarajevo Film Festival</b>. During the festival, Sarajevo becomes the center of Europe\'s best cinema and entertainment! Movie stars such as Angelina Jolie, Morgan Freeman, Brad Pitt and Kevin Spacey are amongst the lucky people who have experienced Sarajevo at its best - don’t miss this opportunity to become one of them!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">But that’s not all! You will be able to explore Sarajevo’s nightlife, cultural diversity, our delicious food, and the hospitality of our citizens. If you\'re still having second thoughts, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" target="_blank">take a look at the atmosphere during eMovie Academy \'11</a>!</span></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">We guarantee you a week of unforgettable experiences, education and excitement!</span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Feel free to ask any questions you might have, and dare to join us in this adventure!</span>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">We are waiting for you!</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'eMovie Academy \'13', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'emovie-academy-13', '', '', '2013-06-17 12:36:40', '2013-06-17 11:36:40', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3104', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3106, 1, '2013-06-17 12:39:34', '2013-06-17 11:39:34', 'Dear Eestecers,\r\n<div>It has come to our knowledge that the period between <strong>July 18th</strong> to <strong>July 21th</strong> is the time you will have the most fun this summer, period full with tourists and a lot of parties. Well, probably because it’s time for LC Skopje to announce and invite you to its first International Motivational Weekend, held in Ohrid, one of the most beautiful cities in Macedonia.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc" target="_blank"><strong>Ohrid</strong></a> is known as the pearl of the Balkan and if you want to party until the morning hours it is definitely a place to be with its numerous beach parties. Because of the uniqueness of Ohrid Lake and the city, they are part of UNESCO, as one of the few places on the list “World Inheritance”.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>This IMW is extremely important for our LC, not only because we are organizing for the first time but also this year we are celebrating our “The number of your fingers” Birthday :P So we will be very pleased if you come to celebrate it with us on EESTEC commonly known way :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>It’s not only our birthday associated with the number 10. This year is coming <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/143474625847806/?context=create" target="_blank"><strong>EESTECers Gone Wild 2</strong></a> , but this time even wilder :P The adventurous crew of LC Skopje is offering you 10 days (including the IMW) of crazy summer vacation and a chance to see the nature beauty of our country.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The participation fee for the IMW is <strong>50€</strong> and it includes both ways ticket from Skopje to Ohrid, accommodation, 3 meals per day and of course drinks. Also it includes a little surprise which we guarantee you will like it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>So EESTECers, this means all you have to do is apply, bring yourself here in Macedonia and take your EESTEC Spirit with you to have a wild summer break.</div>\r\n<div>We promise you will feel all summer joys…</div>\r\n<div></div>', 'IMW: 10 years LC Skopje', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'imw-10-years-lc-skopje', '', '', '2013-06-17 12:39:34', '2013-06-17 11:39:34', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3106', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3108, 1, '2013-06-17 12:43:53', '2013-06-17 11:43:53', '<p dir="ltr">Ladies and gentlemen,</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The rumours you heard are true. EESTEC LC Skopje is proud to announce its second summer exchange, EESTECers Gone Wild 2. Motivated from the successful last year exchange, this time we offer you even more rocking summer.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">What is better time for exam get-away then summer? Sunny days, traveling round the country, tones of fun, parties 24/7 and all that with EESTECers from around Europe are just a few of the things included in our EESTEC vacation. Start planning now your wild get-away time!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Well Eestecers, the only thing that is obligatory to bring is your EESTEC spirit.The rest you can do is pack your swim suits and get your camera, because it’s time for shooting priceless moments from the wildest trip in the history.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir="ltr">Let us present you the unknown cities you will visit...</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/skopje.nspx" target="_blank">Skopje</a> (2 days)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- Probistip (1 day fun in the <a href="http://www.aquaparkmacedonia.mk/gallery-wts/?lang=en" target="_blank">Aquapark</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://travel2macedonia.com.mk/destinations/kavadarci" target="_blank">Kavadarci</a> (2 days tasting Macedonian wine and rakija)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/krusevo.nspx" target="_blank">Krusevo</a> (1 day breathing fresh mountain air with a stop in <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/prilep.nspx" target="_blank">Prilep</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/ohrid.nspx" target="_blank">Ohrid</a> (4 days - all night, all day, partying with participants from International Motivational Weekend)</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir="ltr">For more details, visit this <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1hkXjhrJ60qKPPN0xXEM_jr-yAbNrfMgtidNCz2AaxLQ/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">link</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Just to be on clear, during this EESTEC vacation we provide all the logistic and organization, but we can not provide the food and the accommodation. On this <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0Ahm5dmgMu2KBdERlMkV5bUtqZ1pDdlhLdjFTWlJ3SWc#gid=0" target="_blank">link</a> you can find price list for  average prices for the food, drinks and other expenses.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you are brave enough to be part of EesteCers Gone Wild 2, then fill this <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1nqTmy1YRZf5C6d5IWKHG28x6YgvQs9V6ZqlnonSnPGE/viewform" target="_blank">form</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Let your spirit do the walkin\' through the party rockin\'!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you have any kind of question or maybe suggestion or wishes what to visit or what to do you can contact us :  <a href="mailto:lcskopjecontact@gmail.com" target="_blank">lcskopjecontact@gmail.com</a></p>', 'EESTECers Gone Wild 2 - LC Skopje', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'eestecers-gone-wild-2-lc-skopje', '', '', '2013-06-17 12:43:53', '2013-06-17 11:43:53', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3108', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3112, 1, '2013-06-19 00:15:03', '2013-06-18 23:15:03', '<div>\r\n\r\n“<i>When we define the Photograph as a motionless image, this does not mean only that the figures it represents do not move; it means that they do not emerge, do not leave: they are anesthetized and fastened down, like butterflies.</i>”\r\n\r\nRoland Barthes define the photograph with these sentences in Camera Lucida. I’m sure that most of you interested in “Photography” in some way, try to save some memories and feelings in frame, look to huge world from a little viewfinder.\r\n\r\nNow, LC Eskişehir organizing an amazing workshop about Photography for the second time. We’re proud to invite you to “Photosynthesis 2” We’re offering you an amazing week, lots of fun, useful trainings, great parties, delicious Turkish food and chance to recognize other cultures with photography.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nIn this workshop, you will get basic knowledge and useful tips about photography and then you will practice on historical and cultural places. And at the end, best photos will be displayed in the most popular place in Eskişehir. On the other hand, you will be able to explore Eskişehir’s nightlife, historical places around Eskişehir, Turkish cuisine and beauties of a student city.\r\n\r\nOne more thing; as you know we applied to Grant for this workshop. But results hasn’t been announced. If it will be accepted, we can pay to you your travels costs’ %70 as a standard procedure. We will share the news with you as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSee you in Eskişehir.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Apply : </b>As you know <a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> is not reachable. So you can fill this <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">form</a> and send us to apply until <a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> is on again.\r\n<div>\r\n<i>For additional information please contact me.</i>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Photosynthesis 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'photosynthesis-2', '', '', '2013-06-19 00:15:03', '2013-06-18 23:15:03', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3112', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3129, 1, '2013-07-03 18:32:30', '2013-07-03 17:32:30', 'Dear EESTEC-ers,\r\n\r\nWe are proud to invite you to our traditional event “JAZZ DO IT!”, because it’s 3<sup>rd</sup> edition! It was great previous times, so we have decided to do it again! That\'s why you are welcome to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and Eastern Europe "<a href="http://www.nisville.com/" target="_blank">Nišville jazz festival</a>". Together we will enjoy the good jazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchange can provide. Organized in the medieval <a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" target="_blank">fortress</a> and visited by more than <b>100.000 people</b> only last year, Nišville hosted some of the biggest stars of jazz music: Hans &amp; Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke, Benny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell, Rick Margitza and many others. World’s best jazz musicians and 50 other bands will jazz up on 5 different stages for us!\r\n\r\nParticipants will also have unique opportunity to participate at <a href="http://www.nisville.com/index.php/en/workshop" target="_blank">workshops</a> held by the best jazz musicians.\r\n\r\nRegular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you are getting it for <b>free</b> :)\r\n\r\nBut, that’s not all. The City of Niš has great cultural and historical heritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most important persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Niš (roman name <b>NAISSUS</b>) in 272AD. We are very proud of him, because he was the greatest among all Roman emperors and certainly the person who changed the course of human civilization. And this year is very special because we celebrate 1700 years of issuing the Edict of Milan, which proclaimed religious tolerance in the Empire and stopped numerous persecutions. He had also built a new imperial capital Constantinople, was first Christian emperor in Europe, his mother Saint Helena found True Cross. And by being a birth town of such important person, Niš is also called imperial city. You are going to visit his villa <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediana" target="_blank">Mediana</a> and many other sights that testify rich history of this place between East and West.\r\n\r\nYou will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni%C5%A1_Fortress" target="_blank">Fortress of Niš</a>, where “Nišville jazz festival” takes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. It’s in this condition since XVII century, and now it’s one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe. In Niš exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was built from skulls of the warriors who died in the Čegar battle. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_%C4%8Cegar" target="_blank">Čegar monument</a> where this famous battle took place. We’ll show you one very nice relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" target="_blank">Niška Banja</a> spa which has radioactive healing water and we’ll go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!\r\n\r\nAnd if you think that we only have history, you’re wrong, because Niš is known as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old hedonist legacy! You will enjoy the best Serbian food (world-known barbeque, special burek of Niš and many others), drinks (rakija, wine etc.) and of course a lot of good music. There won’t be a single moment that you’ll be hungry, because Serbs like good food in big quantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient at the special night in <b>kafana</b>. You will certainly learn what is traditional southern <b>merak</b>.\r\n\r\nThis event is completely financed with grant given by Serbian Oil Company <b>NIS</b>, the most profitable Serbian company, so you will be treated like emperors in imperial city!\r\n\r\nSo the crazy summer cocktail with... traditional Serbian drinks and food… plenty of great music… nice town… a lot of EESTEC spirit… Mix all that in a summer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.\r\n\r\nWhat are you waiting for?\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://img404.imageshack.us/img404/5156/jazzdoitcopy.jpg" target="_blank">JAZZ DO IT!</a></span>\r\n\r\n<b>Application </b>by sending this <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">form</a> to <a href="mailto:nis@eestec.net" target="_blank">nis@eestec.net</a>; later maybe via <a href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>', 'Jazz do it 2013!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'jazz-do-it-2013', '', '', '2013-07-03 18:32:30', '2013-07-03 17:32:30', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3129', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3132, 1, '2013-07-16 21:33:40', '2013-07-16 20:33:40', '<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Would you like to end this summer with the best exchange of EESTEC history?</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We know that many of you are thinking ‘Of course I would love to come to Ankara, the capital city which is in the heart of the Anatolia but how about somewhere by the sea to get refreshed?’. Well, you don’t have to worry much longer because LC Ankara is asking you to occupy<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marmaris" target="_blank"> Marmaris</a>!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">LC Ankara is taking you to Marmaris, situated in the southwest coast of Turkish Riviera. Marmaris is one of the most beautiful cities of Turkey and also one of the biggest touristic centrals. The harbor and the marina, the beautiful old town and the <a href="http://www.kulturvarliklari.gov.tr/Resim/32522,muze01jpg.png?0" target="_blank">historical castle</a> are just a few of the greatest things that make it irresistible. Besides that, there is the crazy night life of Marmaris with non-ending foam parties, discos at the beaches and the bar street with lots of clubs. In addition, we will take you to a Turkish night where you will have the chance to taste <a href="http://galeri.uludagsozluk.com/8/rak%C4%B1_20990.jpg" target="_blank">Turkish Raki, </a>eat<a href="http://www.nationalturk.com/en/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/turkish-kebab-nationalturk.jpg" target="_blank"> Kebab</a> and maybe even see <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hCP0yeuo4QQ" target="_blank">belly dancers.</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Of course you won’t spend all your time in the city center. One day we will go to a <a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?hl=en&amp;authuser=0&amp;site=imghp&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=hp&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=664&amp;q=tekne+turu&amp;oq=tekne+turu&amp;gs_l=img.3..0j0i5l2j0i24.2042.3163.0.3709.10.8.0.0.0.0.244.1102.2j5j1.8.0....0...1ac.1.19.img.5mkbu_RvkMQ#hl=en&amp;authuser=0&amp;site=imghp&amp;tbm=isch&amp;sa=1&amp;q=marmaris+boat+trips&amp;oq=marmaris+boat+trips&amp;gs_l=img.3..0j0i5j0i24l4.20890.27785.10.27934.20.14.6.0.0.1.254.2020.1j12j1.14.0....0...1c.1.19.img.t54EAmJgxCY&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;fp=59f2cb1f24a4b371&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=664" target="_blank">boat trip </a>where we will swim in 5 different bays, see the<a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?gs_rn=17&amp;gs_ri=psy-ab&amp;tok=vdBjoKuU2GvzBcTk45oNWQ&amp;pq=fosforlu+ma%C4%9Fara&amp;cp=17&amp;gs_id=1e&amp;xhr=t&amp;q=fosforlu+ma%C4%9Fara+marmaris&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;ion=1&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=1mncUcznIMrYtAbgj4CACA" target="_blank"> phosphoric cave</a> , walk through 2 villages and will barbeque on the boat. In the meantime you can try some <a href="http://tripsinmarmaris.com/turlar/water-Sports/1.jpg" target="_blank">water sport</a>s too. This trip is called ‘Lazy Trip’ because we will have many time to swim, to sunbathe, to drink and to dance. Another day we will go to <a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?q=marmaris+jeep+safari&amp;ion=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=h3LcUZDSHsnWOaPhgYgN" target="_blank">safari trip</a> where we will be taken from our hotel with jeeps and climb up to the mountains. Afterwards we will dive into cold waterfall ponds,<a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?q=k%C4%B1z+kumu&amp;ion=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=iGncUbCIL4OetAbpk4G4BQ" target="_blank"> walk through the sea</a>, have lunch at traditional villages and many more.  At the last day of the exchange we will go to the<a href="https://www.google.com.tr/search?biw=1366&amp;bih=643&amp;q=marmaris+milli+park%C4%B1&amp;ion=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=tr&amp;tbm=isch&amp;source=og&amp;sa=N&amp;tab=wi&amp;authuser=0&amp;ei=KmrcUde1GoLWtAadkoFA#um=1&amp;hl=tr&amp;authuser=0&amp;tbm=isch&amp;sa=1&amp;q=marmaris+milli+park%C4%B1+g%C3%BCnn%C3%BCcek&amp;oq=marmaris+milli+park%C4%B1+g%C3%BCnn%C3%BCcek&amp;gs_l=img.3...1220.3312.2.3530.4.4.0.0.0.0.151.457.1j3.4.0...0.0.0..1c.1.17.img.4t5Q9CZboLI&amp;bav=on.2,or.r_cp.r_qf.&amp;bvm=bv.48705608,d.Yms&amp;fp=f73320e873d882bf&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=643" target="_blank"> Marmaris Natural Park</a> and there will be many surprises waiting for you.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">With all these attractions we will also have an educational part with 3 interesting trainings from EESTEC’s and ESTIEM’s trainers. As well as Motivation and Body Language, we will give you a training on Turkish Language which will help you in many ways ;)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Don’t forget to take a look at this video as well : <a href="http://vimeo.com/56977743" target="_blank">http://vimeo.com/56977743</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Last but not least, don’t worry you will be selected or not, we are preparing a great unofficial package for you guys as well!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">So prepare your swimsuits and bags to have the greatest time of your life!</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Mail: <a href="mailto:ankara@eestec.net" target="_blank">ankara@eestec.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n<div>Application: via sending <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">this form</a> to <a href="mailto:ankara@eestec.net" target="_blank">ankara@eestec.net</a> until <a href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> is reachable again.</div>', '#occupyMarmaris', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'occupymarmaris', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:33:40', '2013-07-16 20:33:40', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3132', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3135, 1, '2013-08-05 14:30:36', '2013-08-05 13:30:36', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAfter the success of LC Hamburg\'s last workshop - "The EesteCube", we are presenting our brand new production “DiscoTech”\r\n\r\nThe curtains haven\'t been raised yet, but our short "trailer" will give you some hints of what awaits you.\r\n\r\nIn the main role are starring ten (eventually more) professional Eestecers.\r\n\r\nAgain the story takes place in the greenest and probably most beautiful city in Europe - Hamburg.\r\n\r\nThe plot consists of unforgettable nights at the famous ‘Reeperbahn’ street, a trip to one of the biggest airline companies - Lufthansa, as well as, visiting the second biggest harbor in Europe. Moreover, there will be an adventurous city rally and a canoe ride in our favorite lake in the middle of the city - the Alster, all accompanied by "tasting" of German beer. And all these amazing scenes will be enlightened by the unique devices that our smart main characters are going to build.\r\n\r\nRegarding the academical part, this time the actors will have to show how music and lights combine through technology. Their task will be to make frequency analysis of audio files and with the help of digital signal processing and some RGB LEDs make the music shine. Therefore, you can take your talent our of the closet, record yourself singing, playing your favorite instruments, or just making silly noises.. eestec style.. and see what kind of beautiful enlightment would come out.\r\n\r\nThe scenario will be presented by our professors and co-students, however in order to pass the casting the actors should have basic C programming knowledge.\r\n\r\nSo put your costumes and makeup on, get your mp3 players and apply for this fascinating workshop.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">We are waiting for you!</span>', 'DiscoTech', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'discotech', '', '', '2013-08-05 14:30:36', '2013-08-05 13:30:36', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3135', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3140, 1, '2013-08-23 18:06:58', '2013-08-23 17:06:58', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The wait is finally over!</div>\r\n<div>LC Ljubljana is happy to announce its dual workshop "<strong>Facebook CPR</strong>"!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That\'s right.</div>\r\n<div>This year we\'re offering you not one, but TWO ways to improve your skills in EESTEC!</div>\r\n<div>Coding or Public Relations.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Are you a programmer? Do you want to become one? If you value order, structure and problem-solving, you can choose to enter the fun and innovative world of Facebook apps! Programming is one of the most valuable abilities a person can have today and the market is becoming huge! Imagine! The next Angry Birds might just as well be yours.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>What is the topic?</div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to teach attendees a basic understanding of facebook app programming and acquaint them with the developmental options that facebook supports. As a participant you will get a chance to develop your own application and implement facebook supported functions as well as work closely with professionals from successful app companies. You will also work on other aspects, such as public speaking and teamwork. Although you can join without any prior knowledge of programming, a basic understanding of HTML and Javascript is appreciated. The workshop itself will consist of lectures and programming sessions, where you will team up with other EESTECers to work on your application.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>But that\'s not all! We at LC Ljubljana know that a student\'s mind can\'t work properly without some kind of release. A head full of knowledge can collapse under its own weight. So we took care of that too! We have prepared a number of fun social activities that take care of your mind and soul. On top of that you will be able to explore the beautiful streets of Ljubljana, enjoy its charming and vibrant nightlife and even attend the legendary City Rally!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That has to be it, right?</div>\r\n<div>WRONG!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After the workshop, you\'ll also get to attend the International Motivational Weekend. It is a huge EESTEC event with people all across Europe. It includes soft-skill training, socializing with EESTECers from numerous LCs, crazy themed parties and best of all: it\'s free for all workshop attendees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 19th (arrival day) to the 27th (departure day) of October 2013 and become part of another unforgettable EESTEC experience here in Ljubljana, Slovenia.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We\'re hearing some rumours (hint: 404) that <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> still doesn\'t function as it\'s supposed to, so we\'ve put up a <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1J6zrtOzwy89qMmjsQSdU74yGlMYL2oZO6vPkp6xN9as/viewform" target="_blank">form where you can apply</a>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>See you all in Ljubljana!</div>\r\n</div>', 'Facebook CPR: FB Apps ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'facebook-cpr-fb-apps', '', '', '2013-08-23 18:06:58', '2013-08-23 17:06:58', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3140', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3142, 1, '2013-08-23 18:08:32', '2013-08-23 17:08:32', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The wait is finally over!</div>\r\n<div>LC Ljubljana is happy to announce its dual workshop "<strong>Facebook</strong> <strong>CPR</strong>"!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That\'s right.</div>\r\n<div>This year we\'re offering you not one, but TWO ways to improve your skills in EESTEC!</div>\r\n<div>Coding or Public Relations.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Have you ever organized an event? Do you know how to use modern media to communicate with the public? Are you interested in what the public has to say and want to maintain a healthy dialogue? If you are interested in the above activities, you might have what it takes to become a Public Relations specialist. At our workshop you can choose to become a master of PR and learn how to inform, communicate with, captivate and even amaze the public. Such skills are extremely valuable in every EESTEC LC, not to mention they will make you look awesome and super attractive to future employers.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>What is the topic?</div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to acquaint the attendees with all the tools needed to maintain proper public relations. We will focus mostly on social network usage because this has become a staple of PR communication. The workshop will include cooperation with successful companies which will help you improve on all areas of PR. You will also work on other aspects, such as public speaking, working with an international team, general communication and leadership skills. The end result will of course be powerful and useful new knowledge that is also directly applicable to any future EESTEC projects.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>But that\'s not all! We at LC Ljubljana know that a student\'s mind can\'t work properly without some kind of release. A head full of knowledge can collapse under its own weight. So we took care of that too! We have prepared a number of fun social activities that take care of your mind and soul. On top of that you will be able to explore the beautiful streets of Ljubljana, enjoy its charming and vibrant nightlife and even attend the legendary City Rally!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That has to be it, right?</div>\r\n<div>WRONG!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After the workshop, you\'ll also get to attend the International Motivational Weekend. It is a huge EESTEC event with people all across Europe. It includes soft-skill training, socializing with EESTECers from numerous LCs, crazy themed parties and best of all: it\'s free for all workshop attendees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 19th (arrival day) to the 27th (departure day) of October 2013 and become part of another unforgettable EESTEC experience here in Ljubljana, Slovenia.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We\'re hearing some rumours (hint: 404) that <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> still doesn\'t function as it\'s supposed to, so we\'ve put up a <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1m1sO7hb5M0pw32stqKFi64ZSNmxSQNVTueiGew1TyTU/viewform" target="_blank">form where you can apply</a>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>See you all in Ljubljana!</div>\r\n</div>', 'Facebook CPR: PR Tools', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'facebook-cpr-pr-tools', '', '', '2013-08-23 18:08:32', '2013-08-23 17:08:32', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3142', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3144, 1, '2013-08-23 18:11:04', '2013-08-23 17:11:04', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\nEESTEC Chairpersons\' Meeting is the second biggest event of EESTEC. This year it will be held by <strong>LC Tallinn </strong>from <strong>3-9 November</strong>. Each LC, JLC and Observer has the right for<strong> one place</strong> on ECM. Therefore, we would kindly ask you to discuss with your Local Board and decide on the representative.\r\n\r\nApplications must be submitted via eestec.net and by sending an email to chairwoman[at]eestec[dot]net with the following information:\r\nFull name, LC, Position in your Local Board or LC\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you use the following tags in the subject of your email:\r\n[ECM\'13][Representative Application][LC \'NAME OF LC\']\r\n\r\nDeadline for applications is the <strong>7th of September</strong>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Main Goals of ECM 2013</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe main focus of ECM 2013 is both Local and International Level. First goal is to strengthen the (J)LCs and Observers by educating Board members via trainings and by sharing knowledge. Second goal is to improve the international awareness and involvement of the members.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to reach those Goals?</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nFollowing sessions/trainings will be held during ECM 2013 :\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n- GMs : 2 GMs will be held this year. Reports on the activities of the association on the past six months as well as RoP change proposals will be presented.\r\n\r\n- International awareness session : This session will be designed in 2 levels. The beginner level session, destined for less experienced representatives, will be an introduction to the structure and international projects in EESTEC. The advanced level, destined for experienced members, will be an introduction to challenges that EESTEC faces and also discussions will be held on how to overcome them.\r\n\r\n- LC Hangout : Evening Hangout with all LCs, where they can discuss with each other.\r\n\r\n- Open Space Technology (OST) : During this session, representatives will suggest topics to be discussed. Afterwards, they will vote on the topics they want to discuss and the most voted ones will be analyzed.\r\n\r\n- Trainings : 3 Soft Skills trainings for less experienced participants. Topics of those trainings will be announced later on.\r\n\r\n- Working sessions : In parallel with the Trainings, the experienced members will be invited to collect best practices of LCs into a document which will be presented and shared with the rest of the members at the end and after ECM. The topics of the working sessions will be announced later on.\r\n\r\n- EDUDay will be held on the 5th of November.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Profile of participants of ECM</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nConsidering the fact that there is only one place per LC and important decisions will be taken during ECM, the chairperson is highly recommended to attend. However, if it is not possible, then an experienced member or a future candidate for your board should attend.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>For any questions or clarifications, please send an email at board[at]eestec[dot]net.</div>\r\n</div>', 'EESTEC Chairpersons\' Meeting 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'eestec-chairpersons-meeting-2013', '', '', '2013-08-23 18:11:04', '2013-08-23 17:11:04', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3144', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3163, 1, '2013-09-21 13:54:02', '2013-09-21 12:54:02', '<p dir="ltr">Dear EESTECers,</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Short story: Excited about NEW things? We can do better than that. This Autumn, <b>LC Bucharest</b> gives you<b> RENEWABLE energies</b>!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Long story: Energy Always a Challenge is an event with a lot of history in our LC, because it’s the first international workshop we have ever organized. This autumn, between the 24th of November and 1st December, we’re having the 4th edition of this event, focusing on renewable energies.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The workshop consists of two parts:<b> three days of conferences </b>on different topics regarding our planet’s green resources and their exploitation potential and a ‘hands on’ week, in which the participants will work in teams to integrate a renewable power plant into the national energy system using the <b>SCADA software</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you are passionate about this subject, if you want to take part in an interactive experience combining fields like: energy management, electrical engineering, IT and programming - you’re the right person for this workshop!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Prior SCADA knowledge is welcome, but not necessary.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The myth: All work and no play make EESTECers dull boys and girls.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The truth: Is that we totally agree with the myth. Therefore, while we will be working hard on our projects, we’ll party with the same amount of enthusiasm! We have prepared for you a week of hardcore entertainment, starting with the <b>City Rally</b> (a thrilling race in which you’ll discover the history and landmarks of our city, such as the largest administrative building in the world, the Palace of the Parliament) and ending with the <b>motivational weekend</b>, where you’ll get a breath of fresh air <b>outside Bucharest</b> -  not to mention the <b>daily parties and outings</b>, the incredible food and the <b>brain-melting traditional drinks</b> (ţuică, palincă).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Bucharest is well known for its <b>flourishing nightlife</b> and <b>fun people </b>(translation: hot girls and boys), so we can guarantee you that you’ll never spend a dull moment during this workshop.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We are waiting for your applications <span style="color: #000000;">u</span><span style="color: #000000;">ntil</span> the<b> 22nd of October 2013</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We’ll work hard to make sure that it’s going to be an unforgettable experience for you :D</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Long story short: APPLY!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Hope to see you soon in Bucharest!</p>', 'Energy Always a Challenge 4', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'energy-always-a-challenge-4', '', '', '2013-09-21 14:07:05', '2013-09-21 13:07:05', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3163', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3171, 18, '2013-09-23 11:58:25', '2013-09-23 10:58:25', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nThe 6th T4T is in front of us and as you had the chance to see it will be organized by amazing LC Skopje between <b>20th </b>and <b>30th October</b>, who decided to take the organization and contribute to our EESTEC family!\r\n\r\nBelow you can find more information about EESTEC\'s Training Team, the event itself, the purpose of organizing it and the benefits of becoming an EESTEC Trainer. Have fun! :)\r\n\r\n<b>What is the EESTEC Training Team? What are Trainings?</b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>EESTEC Training Team is an official EESTEC body which is providing different services for EESTEC and through those services, based on trainings, constantly improving the work of EESTEC on international and local levels!\r\n\r\nMain goal of trainings is transfer of knowledge in an advanced way through different activities, techniques and methodologies.\r\n\r\nMore details and information about the Training Team, Training System and Trainings you can find in the Official Training Team Document <a href="http://eestec.net/workspaces/training-team/training-material/Training%20Team%20Official%20documents/1st%20Official%20Training%20Team%20Document.pdf/view?searchterm=training%20document" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>What is T4T? Why is T4T being organized?</b>\r\n\r\nT4T – Training for Trainers is an international training event whose purpose is gaining new EESTEC trainers and it is the starting point for EESTECers to become a trainer.\r\n\r\nEESTECers which participate in T4T will go through intensive trainings, working sessions and practical parts and learn how to transfer knowledge, which methodologies to use and, very important, how to deliver trainings!\r\n\r\nAs the transfer of knowledge is crucial for EESTEC, T4T is an event which assures new generations to continue with developing and providing Training Team services to EESTEC members. It is a stage through all Training team members have to go in order to gain different soft skills like: leadership skills, presentation skills, communication skills and much more!\r\n\r\nUsing these skills for transferring knowledge in EESTEC provides greater quality of different activities which are being organized in International and local levels.\r\n\r\nDuring T4T, <b>10 days</b> of a lot of work is waiting for you so you will need to bring <b>a lot of positive energy</b> and <b>enthusiasm</b> in order to be effective all the time and to be able to endure the T4T.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Why become a Trainer? Why should you apply?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are definitely a lot of reasons to apply. Becoming a trainer gives you an opportunity to contribute to EESTEC International, to contribute to LCs and to contribute to yourselves!\r\n\r\nAs a trainer candidate (and optionally trainer) you will work in and create a positive atmosphere during T4T and after. If you become a trainer (for what you need to fulfill certain tasks) you will work on the transfer of knowledge to other EESTECers and you will have an opportunity to improve on personal level in different aspects. Besides the opportunities to deliver trainings afterwards, you will become member of the EESTEC Training Team where you will opportunities to work on different projects together with other teammates and to contribute to the further development of the Team!\r\n\r\nThe skills you gain while being a trainer are needed in all aspects of life today and so in EESTEC. Because of that, members who participate in T4T have a big opportunity to develop themselves and to give a great contribution to the development of EESTEC!\r\n\r\n<b> </b><b>Fun part :)</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">If you had a chance to talk with somebody who is from Skopje or who was on an event in Skopje you probably heard all the best. LC Skopje will be in charge for the fun part during evenings and free time and according to the previous events which have been organized on a high level and we believe that LC Skopje will continue this tradition and contribute in making this T4T extraordinary! Below you can find few words from our host LC:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n"<i> LC Skopje is honored to be the organizing committee of such an important event for EESTEC as the 6-th Training for Trainers.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>As a Local Committee that is strongly devoted to the growth and development of the EESTEC network, we believe that answering the Call for this important operational event was not only our wish, but also an utmost duty.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>This year, for the first time, T4T will be held in two cities: Skopje &amp; Ohrid (The balkan Jerusalem). After the success of 2 international events this calendar year, we are more than prepared to organize our third event, but don\'t worry another one is coming up.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>If T4T alone is not enough motivation to apply, we offer you great Macedonian cuisine, hospitality and parties!!!</i>\r\n\r\n<i>Cheers, LC Skopje.</i> "\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<i>If you are an experienced EESTECer, if you participated in trainings, if you want to become a trainer, if you want to develop yourself and EESTEC or if you think that you could become a trainer - <b>apply</b>!</i>\r\n\r\n<i> </i>\r\n\r\n<i></i><i>All now is left is to fill the <a href="http://eestec.net/workspaces/training-team/training-material/Calls%20and%20Forms/T4T/6th-t4t-in-skopje/Application%20form%20for%20participants%20-%206th%20T4T%20in%20Skopje.docx/view" target="_blank"><b>application form</b></a> (<b>not apply over <a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a></b>) and to send it to<a href="mailto:trainings-coordinator@eestec.net" target="_blank">trainings-coordinator@eestec.<wbr />net</a> !</i>\r\n\r\n<i></i><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b> </b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>The deadline for applications is 10th of September 2013.</b></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI will be glad to answer any questions and you feel free to ask anything you have on your mind (<i><a href="mailto:smajic.nermin@gmail.com" target="_blank">smajic.nermin@gmail.com</a></i>).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe hope to see a lot of applications! :)\r\n\r\nBest regards and enjoy!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOn behalf of LC Skopje and Training Team,', 'The 6th Training for Trainers – T4T', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'the-6th-training-for-trainers-t4t-lc-skopje', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:52:59', '2013-09-23 11:52:59', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3171', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3177, 18, '2013-09-23 12:46:50', '2013-09-23 11:46:50', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Munich/Awesome is proud to announce the<strong><i> Oktoberfest Exchange</i></strong> 2013 from <strong>October 1st</strong> until <strong>October 6th</strong>.\r\nYou will have the honor of drinking the world\'s finest beer in the world\'s finest city with the most sophisticated soon-to-be engineers in Europe.\r\n\r\nBesides all these tempting facts we are also planning a cultural program, a City-Rally, sightseeing, and clubbing. There won\'t be any lectures, however plenty of entertainment during your stay in Munich is guaranteed.\r\n\r\nSince hostel prices are ridiculous during Oktoberfest, we will be accommodating you privately. This year we won’t ask you for a participation fee, but we need to ask you to pay everything yourself. This is not an official EESTEC event, it’s just a meeting among friends. We have to warn you though, Munich is generally an expensive place during Oktoberfest. A liter of beer (on Oktoberfest) is <strong>9.40€ </strong>to<strong> 9.85€</strong>! No need to worry, we will not be spending the entire week at Oktoberfest itself, and you will have a lot of chances to get cheaper beer! :)\r\n\r\n<strong>This is a once in a lifetime chance to experience Oktoberfest!</strong>\r\n\r\nAsk your EESTEC friends from Munich first, if they can host you. Then you can talk to them about how long to stay and some other activities. If some of you want to explore the vicinity of Munich, i.e. Castle Neuschwanstein or one of the lakes in the Alps, we can make such trips too! We plan to go to Oktoberfeston Wednesday and Friday.\r\n\r\nAgain, this is the opportunity of your life to enjoy the world\'s biggest beer festival (and party) with your fellow EESTECers! We strongly encourage you to apply! :) If you have any questions, feel free to ask me (<a href="mailto:Andreas.albrecht@fs.ei.tum.de" target="_blank">Andreas.albrecht@fs.ei.tum.de</a><wbr />) or any EESTECer from Munich you know.\r\n\r\nP.S. Loving beer is a must ;)\r\n\r\nSee you in Munich,\r\nAndreas Albrecht', 'Oktoberfest Exchange 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'oktoberfest-exchange-2013', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:52:24', '2013-09-23 11:52:24', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3177', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3183, 18, '2013-09-23 12:56:09', '2013-09-23 11:56:09', '<div><strong>Dear EESTECers</strong>,</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>It\'s true! Observer Xanthi is finally proud to announce its first workshop!! So behold and get ready to Rock-the-bit!!</div>\r\n<div>We have prepared for you a unique event, with lots of innovative ideas, that promises you a refreshing escape from university courses and studying obligations, right in the middle of November!!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><strong>What\'s the topic?</strong></div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to familiarize attendees with the Arduino platform and teach them how to develop an Arduino-based code, in order to create several musical instruments and eventually form a rock-band!!! The practical sessions will consist of four main teams, each one responsible for a different instrument. Therefore, except from the academic part, you will also be able to improve your social and teamwork skills. In case you don\'t have any prior knowledge of programming do not be alarmed! Alongside with the labs, there will be lectures focused on both the Arduino project and miscellaneous technological topics, like sound and music technology.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><strong>Is that all?</strong></div>\r\n<div>Of course not!</div>\r\n<div>Xanthi is one of the most beautiful cities of northern Greece, best known for the quaint Old-Town. Through the City Rally you will explore every hidden treasure of every narrow street of the “city with the 1000 colors”. Get ready to experience the world\'s famous greek hospitality, taste the local drinks and visit the landscape of outstanding natural beauty during the Motivational Weekend right at the end of our Workshop. You should definitely prepare yourself for more surprises to come..!!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 17th to 24th of November 2013 and promise you an unforgettable week here in Xanthi, Greece.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><strong>See you all in Xanthi!</strong></div>', 'Rock the bit', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rock-the-bit', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:01:16', '2013-09-23 12:01:16', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3183', 0, 'events', '', 0),
 (3190, 18, '2013-09-23 13:06:10', '2013-09-23 12:06:10', '<strong>Dear EESTECers !</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LC İzmir</strong> represents brand new workshop Braintrainer in cooperation with LG İzmir. As a joint project of EESTEC and ESTIEM , Braintrainer will take place on the dates 1-7 December.\r\n\r\n<strong>During this workshop</strong> you\'re going to improve your management skills and also as we always do you will have fun, meet new people and see fancy places.\r\n\r\nFirst 3 days of the workshop we\'re going to be in a nice hotel which is out of city and we will relax a bit while we are away from the stress of the city life. On those days our lovely trainers from ESTIEM and EESTEC will give you training sessions and then nights will be ours !\r\n\r\n<strong>After enjoying</strong> those 3 days we will turn back to the city life, case will be open for us . Get ready business people ! Who solves the case first , wins the price! Do you wanna know who will be responsible for case studies here is just 2 examples : Schneider Electric , Bosch and there are even better companies ! May be if you are good enough you can get an internship offer too.\r\n\r\nWhen business is done , it\'s time for pleasure we\'ll have some visits to surroundings of the city. You need to know where ? Then here is a hint : One of them is Şirince where you can find unique kind of wines that\'s why Şirince is called as a village of wines !\r\n\r\n<strong>Last but not least</strong> we guarantee you that you\'re gonna have great parties over here. We\'ll have our parties with our erasmus students in here and internationality level will grow up !', 'EESTEC & ESTIEM Joint Workshop BrainTrainer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'eestec-estiem-joint-workshop-braintrainer', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:13:45', '2013-09-23 12:13:45', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3190', 0, 'events', '', 0),
